5938  if (checkPlaceholderForOverload(*this, From))
5939  return ExprError();
5940 
5941  QualType Ty = Context.getObjCIdType();
5942  ImplicitConversionSequence ICS =
5943  TryContextuallyConvertToObjCPointer(*this, From);
5944  if (!ICS.isBad())
5945  return PerformImplicitConversion(From, Ty, ICS, AA_Converting);
5946  return ExprResult();
5947 }
5948 
5949 /// Determine whether the provided type is an integral type, or an enumeration
5950 /// type of a permitted flavor.
5951 bool Sema::ICEConvertDiagnoser::match(QualType T) {
5952  return AllowScopedEnumerations ? T->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()
5953  : T->isIntegralOrUnscopedEnumerationType();
5954 }
5955 
5956 static ExprResult
5957 diagnoseAmbiguousConversion(Sema &SemaRef, SourceLocation Loc, Expr *From,
5958  Sema::ContextualImplicitConverter &Converter,
5959  QualType T, UnresolvedSetImpl &ViableConversions) {
5960 
5961  if (Converter.Suppress)
5962  return ExprError();
5963 
5964  Converter.diagnoseAmbiguous(SemaRef, Loc, T) << From->getSourceRange();
5965  for (unsigned I = 0, N = ViableConversions.size(); I != N; ++I) {
5966  CXXConversionDecl *Conv =
5967  cast<CXXConversionDecl>(ViableConversions[I]->getUnderlyingDecl());
5968  QualType ConvTy = Conv->getConversionType().getNonReferenceType();
5969  Converter.noteAmbiguous(SemaRef, Conv, ConvTy);
5970  }
5971  return From;
5972 }
5973 
5974 static bool
5975 diagnoseNoViableConversion(Sema &SemaRef, SourceLocation Loc, Expr *&From,
5976  Sema::ContextualImplicitConverter &Converter,
5977  QualType T, bool HadMultipleCandidates,
5978  UnresolvedSetImpl &ExplicitConversions) {
5979  if (ExplicitConversions.size() == 1 && !Converter.Suppress) {
5980  DeclAccessPair Found = ExplicitConversions[0];
5981  CXXConversionDecl *Conversion =
5982  cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Found->getUnderlyingDecl());
5983 
5984  // The user probably meant to invoke the given explicit
5985  // conversion; use it.
5986  QualType ConvTy = Conversion->getConversionType().getNonReferenceType();
5987  std::string TypeStr;
5988  ConvTy.getAsStringInternal(TypeStr, SemaRef.getPrintingPolicy());
5989 
5990  Converter.diagnoseExplicitConv(SemaRef, Loc, T, ConvTy)
5991  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(From->getBeginLoc(),
5992  "static_cast<" + TypeStr + ">(")
5993  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
5994  SemaRef.getLocForEndOfToken(From->getEndLoc()), ")");
5995  Converter.noteExplicitConv(SemaRef, Conversion, ConvTy);
5996 
5997  // If we aren't in a SFINAE context, build a call to the
5998  // explicit conversion function.
5999  if (SemaRef.isSFINAEContext())
6000  return true;
6001 
6002  SemaRef.CheckMemberOperatorAccess(From->getExprLoc(), From, nullptr, Found);
6003  ExprResult Result = SemaRef.BuildCXXMemberCallExpr(From, Found, Conversion,
6004  HadMultipleCandidates);
6005  if (Result.isInvalid())
6006  return true;
6007  // Record usage of conversion in an implicit cast.
6008  From = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(SemaRef.Context, Result.get()->getType(),
6009  CK_UserDefinedConversion, Result.get(),
6010  nullptr, Result.get()->getValueKind(),
6011  SemaRef.CurFPFeatureOverrides());
6012  }
6013  return false;
6014 }
6015 
6016 static bool recordConversion(Sema &SemaRef, SourceLocation Loc, Expr *&From,
6017  Sema::ContextualImplicitConverter &Converter,
6018  QualType T, bool HadMultipleCandidates,
6019  DeclAccessPair &Found) {
6020  CXXConversionDecl *Conversion =
6021  cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Found->getUnderlyingDecl());
6022  SemaRef.CheckMemberOperatorAccess(From->getExprLoc(), From, nullptr, Found);
6023 
6024  QualType ToType = Conversion->getConversionType().getNonReferenceType();
6025  if (!Converter.SuppressConversion) {
6026  if (SemaRef.isSFINAEContext())
6027  return true;
6028 
6029  Converter.diagnoseConversion(SemaRef, Loc, T, ToType)
6030  << From->getSourceRange();
6031  }
6032 
6033  ExprResult Result = SemaRef.BuildCXXMemberCallExpr(From, Found, Conversion,
6034  HadMultipleCandidates);
6035  if (Result.isInvalid())
6036  return true;
6037  // Record usage of conversion in an implicit cast.
6038  From = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(SemaRef.Context, Result.get()->getType(),
6039  CK_UserDefinedConversion, Result.get(),
6040  nullptr, Result.get()->getValueKind(),
6041  SemaRef.CurFPFeatureOverrides());
6042  return false;
6043 }
6044 
6045 static ExprResult finishContextualImplicitConversion(
6046  Sema &SemaRef, SourceLocation Loc, Expr *From,
6047  Sema::ContextualImplicitConverter &Converter) {
6048  if (!Converter.match(From->getType()) && !Converter.Suppress)
6049  Converter.diagnoseNoMatch(SemaRef, Loc, From->getType())
6050  << From->getSourceRange();
6051 
6052  return SemaRef.DefaultLvalueConversion(From);
6053 }
6054 
6055 static void
6056 collectViableConversionCandidates(Sema &SemaRef, Expr *From, QualType ToType,
6057  UnresolvedSetImpl &ViableConversions,
6058  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet) {
6059  for (unsigned I = 0, N = ViableConversions.size(); I != N; ++I) {
6060  DeclAccessPair FoundDecl = ViableConversions[I];
6061  NamedDecl *D = FoundDecl.getDecl();
6062  CXXRecordDecl *ActingContext = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getDeclContext());
6063  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D))
6064  D = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(D)->getTargetDecl();
6065 
6066  CXXConversionDecl *Conv;
6067  FunctionTemplateDecl *ConvTemplate;
6068  if ((ConvTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D)))
6069  Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(ConvTemplate->getTemplatedDecl());
6070  else
6071  Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D);
6072 
6073  if (ConvTemplate)
6074  SemaRef.AddTemplateConversionCandidate(
6075  ConvTemplate, FoundDecl, ActingContext, From, ToType, CandidateSet,
6076  /*AllowObjCConversionOnExplicit=*/false, /*AllowExplicit*/ true);
6077  else
6078  SemaRef.AddConversionCandidate(Conv, FoundDecl, ActingContext, From,
6079  ToType, CandidateSet,
6080  /*AllowObjCConversionOnExplicit=*/false,
6081  /*AllowExplicit*/ true);
6082  }
6083 }
6084 
6085 /// Attempt to convert the given expression to a type which is accepted
6086 /// by the given converter.
6087 ///
6088 /// This routine will attempt to convert an expression of class type to a
6089 /// type accepted by the specified converter. In C++11 and before, the class
6090 /// must have a single non-explicit conversion function converting to a matching
6091 /// type. In C++1y, there can be multiple such conversion functions, but only
6092 /// one target type.
6093 ///
6094 /// \param Loc The source location of the construct that requires the
6095 /// conversion.
6096 ///
6097 /// \param From The expression we're converting from.
6098 ///
6099 /// \param Converter Used to control and diagnose the conversion process.
6100 ///
6101 /// \returns The expression, converted to an integral or enumeration type if
6102 /// successful.
6103 ExprResult Sema::PerformContextualImplicitConversion(
6104  SourceLocation Loc, Expr *From, ContextualImplicitConverter &Converter) {
6105  // We can't perform any more checking for type-dependent expressions.
6106  if (From->isTypeDependent())
6107  return From;
6108 
6109  // Process placeholders immediately.
6110  if (From->hasPlaceholderType()) {
6111  ExprResult result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(From);
6112  if (result.isInvalid())
6113  return result;
6114  From = result.get();
6115  }
6116 
6117  // If the expression already has a matching type, we're golden.
6118  QualType T = From->getType();
6119  if (Converter.match(T))
6120  return DefaultLvalueConversion(From);
6121 
6122  // FIXME: Check for missing '()' if T is a function type?
6123 
6124  // We can only perform contextual implicit conversions on objects of class
6125  // type.
6126  const RecordType *RecordTy = T->getAs<RecordType>();
6127  if (!RecordTy || !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
6128  if (!Converter.Suppress)
6129  Converter.diagnoseNoMatch(*this, Loc, T) << From->getSourceRange();
6130  return From;
6131  }
6132 
6133  // We must have a complete class type.
6134  struct TypeDiagnoserPartialDiag : TypeDiagnoser {
6135  ContextualImplicitConverter &Converter;
6136  Expr *From;
6137 
6138  TypeDiagnoserPartialDiag(ContextualImplicitConverter &Converter, Expr *From)
6139  : Converter(Converter), From(From) {}
6140 
6141  void diagnose(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc, QualType T) override {
6142  Converter.diagnoseIncomplete(S, Loc, T) << From->getSourceRange();
6143  }
6144  } IncompleteDiagnoser(Converter, From);
6145 
6146  if (Converter.Suppress ? !isCompleteType(Loc, T)
6147  : RequireCompleteType(Loc, T, IncompleteDiagnoser))
6148  return From;
6149 
6150  // Look for a conversion to an integral or enumeration type.
6151  UnresolvedSet<4>
6152  ViableConversions; // These are *potentially* viable in C++1y.
6153  UnresolvedSet<4> ExplicitConversions;
6154  const auto &Conversions =
6155  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordTy->getDecl())->getVisibleConversionFunctions();
6156 
6157  bool HadMultipleCandidates =
6158  (std::distance(Conversions.begin(), Conversions.end()) > 1);
6159 
6160  // To check that there is only one target type, in C++1y:
6161  QualType ToType;
6162  bool HasUniqueTargetType = true;
6163 
6164  // Collect explicit or viable (potentially in C++1y) conversions.
6165  for (auto I = Conversions.begin(), E = Conversions.end(); I != E; ++I) {
6166  NamedDecl *D = (*I)->getUnderlyingDecl();
6167  CXXConversionDecl *Conversion;
6168  FunctionTemplateDecl *ConvTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D);
6169  if (ConvTemplate) {
6170  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14)
6171  Conversion = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(ConvTemplate->getTemplatedDecl());
6172  else
6173  continue; // C++11 does not consider conversion operator templates(?).
6174  } else
6175  Conversion = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D);
6176 
6177  assert((!ConvTemplate || getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14) &&
6178  "Conversion operator templates are considered potentially "
6179  "viable in C++1y");
6180 
6181  QualType CurToType = Conversion->getConversionType().getNonReferenceType();
6182  if (Converter.match(CurToType) || ConvTemplate) {
6183 
6184  if (Conversion->isExplicit()) {
6185  // FIXME: For C++1y, do we need this restriction?
6186  // cf. diagnoseNoViableConversion()
6187  if (!ConvTemplate)
6188  ExplicitConversions.addDecl(I.getDecl(), I.getAccess());
6189  } else {
6190  if (!ConvTemplate && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14) {
6191  if (ToType.isNull())
6192  ToType = CurToType.getUnqualifiedType();
6193  else if (HasUniqueTargetType &&
6194  (CurToType.getUnqualifiedType() != ToType))
6195  HasUniqueTargetType = false;
6196  }
6197  ViableConversions.addDecl(I.getDecl(), I.getAccess());
6198  }
6199  }
6200  }
6201 
6202  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14) {
6203  // C++1y [conv]p6:
6204  // ... An expression e of class type E appearing in such a context
6205  // is said to be contextually implicitly converted to a specified
6206  // type T and is well-formed if and only if e can be implicitly
6207  // converted to a type T that is determined as follows: E is searched
6208  // for conversion functions whose return type is cv T or reference to
6209  // cv T such that T is allowed by the context. There shall be
6210  // exactly one such T.
6211 
6212  // If no unique T is found:
6213  if (ToType.isNull()) {
6214  if (diagnoseNoViableConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter, T,
6215  HadMultipleCandidates,
6216  ExplicitConversions))
6217  return ExprError();
6218  return finishContextualImplicitConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter);
6219  }
6220 
6221  // If more than one unique Ts are found:
6222  if (!HasUniqueTargetType)
6223  return diagnoseAmbiguousConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter, T,
6224  ViableConversions);
6225 
6226  // If one unique T is found:
6227  // First, build a candidate set from the previously recorded
6228  // potentially viable conversions.
6229  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(Loc, OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
6230  collectViableConversionCandidates(*this, From, ToType, ViableConversions,
6231  CandidateSet);
6232 
6233  // Then, perform overload resolution over the candidate set.
6234  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
6235  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, Loc, Best)) {
6236  case OR_Success: {
6237  // Apply this conversion.
6238  DeclAccessPair Found =
6239  DeclAccessPair::make(Best->Function, Best->FoundDecl.getAccess());
6240  if (recordConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter, T,
6241  HadMultipleCandidates, Found))
6242  return ExprError();
6243  break;
6244  }
6245  case OR_Ambiguous:
6246  return diagnoseAmbiguousConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter, T,
6247  ViableConversions);
6248  case OR_No_Viable_Function:
6249  if (diagnoseNoViableConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter, T,
6250  HadMultipleCandidates,
6251  ExplicitConversions))
6252  return ExprError();
6253  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
6254  case OR_Deleted:
6255  // We'll complain below about a non-integral condition type.
6256  break;
6257  }
6258  } else {
6259  switch (ViableConversions.size()) {
6260  case 0: {
6261  if (diagnoseNoViableConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter, T,
6262  HadMultipleCandidates,
6263  ExplicitConversions))
6264  return ExprError();
6265 
6266  // We'll complain below about a non-integral condition type.
6267  break;
6268  }
6269  case 1: {
6270  // Apply this conversion.
6271  DeclAccessPair Found = ViableConversions[0];
6272  if (recordConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter, T,
6273  HadMultipleCandidates, Found))
6274  return ExprError();
6275  break;
6276  }
6277  default:
6278  return diagnoseAmbiguousConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter, T,
6279  ViableConversions);
6280  }
6281  }
6282 
6283  return finishContextualImplicitConversion(*this, Loc, From, Converter);
6284 }
6285 
6286 /// IsAcceptableNonMemberOperatorCandidate - Determine whether Fn is
6287 /// an acceptable non-member overloaded operator for a call whose
6288 /// arguments have types T1 (and, if non-empty, T2). This routine
6289 /// implements the check in C++ [over.match.oper]p3b2 concerning
6290 /// enumeration types.
6291 static bool IsAcceptableNonMemberOperatorCandidate(ASTContext &Context,
6292  FunctionDecl *Fn,
6293  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args) {
6294  QualType T1 = Args[0]->getType();
6295  QualType T2 = Args.size() > 1 ? Args[1]->getType() : QualType();
6296 
6297  if (T1->isDependentType() || (!T2.isNull() && T2->isDependentType()))
6298  return true;
6299 
6300  if (T1->isRecordType() || (!T2.isNull() && T2->isRecordType()))
6301  return true;
6302 
6303  const auto *Proto = Fn->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
6304  if (Proto->getNumParams() < 1)
6305  return false;
6306 
6307  if (T1->isEnumeralType()) {
6308  QualType ArgType = Proto->getParamType(0).getNonReferenceType();
6309  if (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(T1, ArgType))
6310  return true;
6311  }
6312 
6313  if (Proto->getNumParams() < 2)
6314  return false;
6315 
6316  if (!T2.isNull() && T2->isEnumeralType()) {
6317  QualType ArgType = Proto->getParamType(1).getNonReferenceType();
6318  if (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(T2, ArgType))
6319  return true;
6320  }
6321 
6322  return false;
6323 }
6324 
6325 /// AddOverloadCandidate - Adds the given function to the set of
6326 /// candidate functions, using the given function call arguments. If
6327 /// @p SuppressUserConversions, then don't allow user-defined
6328 /// conversions via constructors or conversion operators.
6329 ///
6330 /// \param PartialOverloading true if we are performing "partial" overloading
6331 /// based on an incomplete set of function arguments. This feature is used by
6332 /// code completion.
6333 void Sema::AddOverloadCandidate(
6334  FunctionDecl *Function, DeclAccessPair FoundDecl, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
6335  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet, bool SuppressUserConversions,
6336  bool PartialOverloading, bool AllowExplicit, bool AllowExplicitConversions,
6337  ADLCallKind IsADLCandidate, ConversionSequenceList EarlyConversions,
6338  OverloadCandidateParamOrder PO) {
6339  const FunctionProtoType *Proto
6340  = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(Function->getType()->getAs<FunctionType>());
6341  assert(Proto && "Functions without a prototype cannot be overloaded");
6342  assert(!Function->getDescribedFunctionTemplate() &&
6343  "Use AddTemplateOverloadCandidate for function templates");
6344 
6345  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Function)) {
6346  if (!isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method)) {
6347  // If we get here, it's because we're calling a member function
6348  // that is named without a member access expression (e.g.,
6349  // "this->f") that was either written explicitly or created
6350  // implicitly. This can happen with a qualified call to a member
6351  // function, e.g., X::f(). We use an empty type for the implied
6352  // object argument (C++ [over.call.func]p3), and the acting context
6353  // is irrelevant.
6354  AddMethodCandidate(Method, FoundDecl, Method->getParent(), QualType(),
6355  Expr::Classification::makeSimpleLValue(), Args,
6356  CandidateSet, SuppressUserConversions,
6357  PartialOverloading, EarlyConversions, PO);
6358  return;
6359  }
6360  // We treat a constructor like a non-member function, since its object
6361  // argument doesn't participate in overload resolution.
6362  }
6363 
6364  if (!CandidateSet.isNewCandidate(Function, PO))
6365  return;
6366 
6367  // C++11 [class.copy]p11: [DR1402]
6368  // A defaulted move constructor that is defined as deleted is ignored by
6369  // overload resolution.
6370  CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Function);
6371  if (Constructor && Constructor->isDefaulted() && Constructor->isDeleted() &&
6372  Constructor->isMoveConstructor())
6373  return;
6374 
6375  // Overload resolution is always an unevaluated context.
6376  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6377  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
6378 
6379  // C++ [over.match.oper]p3:
6380  // if no operand has a class type, only those non-member functions in the
6381  // lookup set that have a first parameter of type T1 or "reference to
6382  // (possibly cv-qualified) T1", when T1 is an enumeration type, or (if there
6383  // is a right operand) a second parameter of type T2 or "reference to
6384  // (possibly cv-qualified) T2", when T2 is an enumeration type, are
6385  // candidate functions.
6386  if (CandidateSet.getKind() == OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator &&
6387  !IsAcceptableNonMemberOperatorCandidate(Context, Function, Args))
6388  return;
6389 
6390  // Add this candidate
6391  OverloadCandidate &Candidate =
6392  CandidateSet.addCandidate(Args.size(), EarlyConversions);
6393  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
6394  Candidate.Function = Function;
6395  Candidate.Viable = true;
6396  Candidate.RewriteKind =
6397  CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().getRewriteKind(Function, PO);
6398  Candidate.IsSurrogate = false;
6399  Candidate.IsADLCandidate = IsADLCandidate;
6400  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument = false;
6401  Candidate.ExplicitCallArguments = Args.size();
6402 
6403  // Explicit functions are not actually candidates at all if we're not
6404  // allowing them in this context, but keep them around so we can point
6405  // to them in diagnostics.
6406  if (!AllowExplicit && ExplicitSpecifier::getFromDecl(Function).isExplicit()) {
6407  Candidate.Viable = false;
6408  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_explicit;
6409  return;
6410  }
6411 
6412  if (Function->isMultiVersion() && Function->hasAttr<TargetAttr>() &&
6413  !Function->getAttr<TargetAttr>()->isDefaultVersion()) {
6414  Candidate.Viable = false;
6415  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_non_default_multiversion_function;
6416  return;
6417  }
6418 
6419  if (Constructor) {
6420  // C++ [class.copy]p3:
6421  // A member function template is never instantiated to perform the copy
6422  // of a class object to an object of its class type.
6423  QualType ClassType = Context.getTypeDeclType(Constructor->getParent());
6424  if (Args.size() == 1 && Constructor->isSpecializationCopyingObject() &&
6425  (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ClassType, Args[0]->getType()) ||
6426  IsDerivedFrom(Args[0]->getBeginLoc(), Args[0]->getType(),
6427  ClassType))) {
6428  Candidate.Viable = false;
6429  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_illegal_constructor;
6430  return;
6431  }
6432 
6433  // C++ [over.match.funcs]p8: (proposed DR resolution)
6434  // A constructor inherited from class type C that has a first parameter
6435  // of type "reference to P" (including such a constructor instantiated
6436  // from a template) is excluded from the set of candidate functions when
6437  // constructing an object of type cv D if the argument list has exactly
6438  // one argument and D is reference-related to P and P is reference-related
6439  // to C.
6440  auto *Shadow = dyn_cast<ConstructorUsingShadowDecl>(FoundDecl.getDecl());
6441  if (Shadow && Args.size() == 1 && Constructor->getNumParams() >= 1 &&
6442  Constructor->getParamDecl(0)->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
6443  QualType P = Constructor->getParamDecl(0)->getType()->getPointeeType();
6444  QualType C = Context.getRecordType(Constructor->getParent());
6445  QualType D = Context.getRecordType(Shadow->getParent());
6446  SourceLocation Loc = Args.front()->getExprLoc();
6447  if ((Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(P, C) || IsDerivedFrom(Loc, P, C)) &&
6448  (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(D, P) || IsDerivedFrom(Loc, D, P))) {
6449  Candidate.Viable = false;
6450  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_inhctor_slice;
6451  return;
6452  }
6453  }
6454 
6455  // Check that the constructor is capable of constructing an object in the
6456  // destination address space.
6457  if (!Qualifiers::isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(
6458  Constructor->getMethodQualifiers().getAddressSpace(),
6459  CandidateSet.getDestAS())) {
6460  Candidate.Viable = false;
6461  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_object_addrspace_mismatch;
6462  }
6463  }
6464 
6465  unsigned NumParams = Proto->getNumParams();
6466 
6467  // (C++ 13.3.2p2): A candidate function having fewer than m
6468  // parameters is viable only if it has an ellipsis in its parameter
6469  // list (8.3.5).
6470  if (TooManyArguments(NumParams, Args.size(), PartialOverloading) &&
6471  !Proto->isVariadic() &&
6472  shouldEnforceArgLimit(PartialOverloading, Function)) {
6473  Candidate.Viable = false;
6474  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_too_many_arguments;
6475  return;
6476  }
6477 
6478  // (C++ 13.3.2p2): A candidate function having more than m parameters
6479  // is viable only if the (m+1)st parameter has a default argument
6480  // (8.3.6). For the purposes of overload resolution, the
6481  // parameter list is truncated on the right, so that there are
6482  // exactly m parameters.
6483  unsigned MinRequiredArgs = Function->getMinRequiredArguments();
6484  if (Args.size() < MinRequiredArgs && !PartialOverloading) {
6485  // Not enough arguments.
6486  Candidate.Viable = false;
6487  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_too_few_arguments;
6488  return;
6489  }
6490 
6491  // (CUDA B.1): Check for invalid calls between targets.
6492  if (getLangOpts().CUDA)
6493  if (const FunctionDecl *Caller = getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true))
6494  // Skip the check for callers that are implicit members, because in this
6495  // case we may not yet know what the member's target is; the target is
6496  // inferred for the member automatically, based on the bases and fields of
6497  // the class.
6498  if (!Caller->isImplicit() && !IsAllowedCUDACall(Caller, Function)) {
6499  Candidate.Viable = false;
6500  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_target;
6501  return;
6502  }
6503 
6504  if (Function->getTrailingRequiresClause()) {
6505  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
6506  if (CheckFunctionConstraints(Function, Satisfaction) ||
6507  !Satisfaction.IsSatisfied) {
6508  Candidate.Viable = false;
6509  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_constraints_not_satisfied;
6510  return;
6511  }
6512  }
6513 
6514  // Determine the implicit conversion sequences for each of the
6515  // arguments.
6516  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx < Args.size(); ++ArgIdx) {
6517  unsigned ConvIdx =
6518  PO == OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed ? 1 - ArgIdx : ArgIdx;
6519  if (Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx].isInitialized()) {
6520  // We already formed a conversion sequence for this parameter during
6521  // template argument deduction.
6522  } else if (ArgIdx < NumParams) {
6523  // (C++ 13.3.2p3): for F to be a viable function, there shall
6524  // exist for each argument an implicit conversion sequence
6525  // (13.3.3.1) that converts that argument to the corresponding
6526  // parameter of F.
6527  QualType ParamType = Proto->getParamType(ArgIdx);
6528  Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx] = TryCopyInitialization(
6529  *this, Args[ArgIdx], ParamType, SuppressUserConversions,
6530  /*InOverloadResolution=*/true,
6531  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/
6532  getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount, AllowExplicitConversions);
6533  if (Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx].isBad()) {
6534  Candidate.Viable = false;
6535  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
6536  return;
6537  }
6538  } else {
6539  // (C++ 13.3.2p2): For the purposes of overload resolution, any
6540  // argument for which there is no corresponding parameter is
6541  // considered to ""match the ellipsis" (C+ 13.3.3.1.3).
6542  Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx].setEllipsis();
6543  }
6544  }
6545 
6546  if (EnableIfAttr *FailedAttr =
6547  CheckEnableIf(Function, CandidateSet.getLocation(), Args)) {
6548  Candidate.Viable = false;
6549  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_enable_if;
6550  Candidate.DeductionFailure.Data = FailedAttr;
6551  return;
6552  }
6553 }
6554 
6555 ObjCMethodDecl *
6556 Sema::SelectBestMethod(Selector Sel, MultiExprArg Args, bool IsInstance,
6557  SmallVectorImpl<ObjCMethodDecl *> &Methods) {
6558  if (Methods.size() <= 1)
6559  return nullptr;
6560 
6561  for (unsigned b = 0, e = Methods.size(); b < e; b++) {
6562  bool Match = true;
6563  ObjCMethodDecl *Method = Methods[b];
6564  unsigned NumNamedArgs = Sel.getNumArgs();
6565  // Method might have more arguments than selector indicates. This is due
6566  // to addition of c-style arguments in method.
6567  if (Method->param_size() > NumNamedArgs)
6568  NumNamedArgs = Method->param_size();
6569  if (Args.size() < NumNamedArgs)
6570  continue;
6571 
6572  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumNamedArgs; i++) {
6573  // We can't do any type-checking on a type-dependent argument.
6574  if (Args[i]->isTypeDependent()) {
6575  Match = false;
6576  break;
6577  }
6578 
6579  ParmVarDecl *param = Method->parameters()[i];
6580  Expr *argExpr = Args[i];
6581  assert(argExpr && "SelectBestMethod(): missing expression");
6582 
6583  // Strip the unbridged-cast placeholder expression off unless it's
6584  // a consumed argument.
6585  if (argExpr->hasPlaceholderType(BuiltinType::ARCUnbridgedCast) &&
6586  !param->hasAttr<CFConsumedAttr>())
6587  argExpr = stripARCUnbridgedCast(argExpr);
6588 
6589  // If the parameter is __unknown_anytype, move on to the next method.
6590  if (param->getType() == Context.UnknownAnyTy) {
6591  Match = false;
6592  break;
6593  }
6594 
6595  ImplicitConversionSequence ConversionState
6596  = TryCopyInitialization(*this, argExpr, param->getType(),
6597  /*SuppressUserConversions*/false,
6598  /*InOverloadResolution=*/true,
6599  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/
6600  getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount,
6601  /*AllowExplicit*/false);
6602  // This function looks for a reasonably-exact match, so we consider
6603  // incompatible pointer conversions to be a failure here.
6604  if (ConversionState.isBad() ||
6605  (ConversionState.isStandard() &&
6606  ConversionState.Standard.Second ==
6607  ICK_Incompatible_Pointer_Conversion)) {
6608  Match = false;
6609  break;
6610  }
6611  }
6612  // Promote additional arguments to variadic methods.
6613  if (Match && Method->isVariadic()) {
6614  for (unsigned i = NumNamedArgs, e = Args.size(); i < e; ++i) {
6615  if (Args[i]->isTypeDependent()) {
6616  Match = false;
6617  break;
6618  }
6619  ExprResult Arg = DefaultVariadicArgumentPromotion(Args[i], VariadicMethod,
6620  nullptr);
6621  if (Arg.isInvalid()) {
6622  Match = false;
6623  break;
6624  }
6625  }
6626  } else {
6627  // Check for extra arguments to non-variadic methods.
6628  if (Args.size() != NumNamedArgs)
6629  Match = false;
6630  else if (Match && NumNamedArgs == 0 && Methods.size() > 1) {
6631  // Special case when selectors have no argument. In this case, select
6632  // one with the most general result type of 'id'.
6633  for (unsigned b = 0, e = Methods.size(); b < e; b++) {
6634  QualType ReturnT = Methods[b]->getReturnType();
6635  if (ReturnT->isObjCIdType())
6636  return Methods[b];
6637  }
6638  }
6639  }
6640 
6641  if (Match)
6642  return Method;
6643  }
6644  return nullptr;
6645 }
6646 
6647 static bool convertArgsForAvailabilityChecks(
6648  Sema &S, FunctionDecl *Function, Expr *ThisArg, SourceLocation CallLoc,
6649  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args, Sema::SFINAETrap &Trap, bool MissingImplicitThis,
6650  Expr *&ConvertedThis, SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &ConvertedArgs) {
6651  if (ThisArg) {
6652  CXXMethodDecl *Method = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Function);
6653  assert(!isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method) &&
6654  "Shouldn't have `this` for ctors!");
6655  assert(!Method->isStatic() && "Shouldn't have `this` for static methods!");
6656  ExprResult R = S.PerformObjectArgumentInitialization(
6657  ThisArg, /*Qualifier=*/nullptr, Method, Method);
6658  if (R.isInvalid())
6659  return false;
6660  ConvertedThis = R.get();
6661  } else {
6662  if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Function)) {
6663  (void)MD;
6664  assert((MissingImplicitThis || MD->isStatic() ||
6665  isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD)) &&
6666  "Expected `this` for non-ctor instance methods");
6667  }
6668  ConvertedThis = nullptr;
6669  }
6670 
6671  // Ignore any variadic arguments. Converting them is pointless, since the
6672  // user can't refer to them in the function condition.
6673  unsigned ArgSizeNoVarargs = std::min(Function->param_size(), Args.size());
6674 
6675  // Convert the arguments.
6676  for (unsigned I = 0; I != ArgSizeNoVarargs; ++I) {
6677  ExprResult R;
6678  R = S.PerformCopyInitialization(InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(
6679  S.Context, Function->getParamDecl(I)),
6680  SourceLocation(), Args[I]);
6681 
6682  if (R.isInvalid())
6683  return false;
6684 
6685  ConvertedArgs.push_back(R.get());
6686  }
6687 
6688  if (Trap.hasErrorOccurred())
6689  return false;
6690 
6691  // Push default arguments if needed.
6692  if (!Function->isVariadic() && Args.size() < Function->getNumParams()) {
6693  for (unsigned i = Args.size(), e = Function->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i) {
6694  ParmVarDecl *P = Function->getParamDecl(i);
6695  if (!P->hasDefaultArg())
6696  return false;
6697  ExprResult R = S.BuildCXXDefaultArgExpr(CallLoc, Function, P);
6698  if (R.isInvalid())
6699  return false;
6700  ConvertedArgs.push_back(R.get());
6701  }
6702 
6703  if (Trap.hasErrorOccurred())
6704  return false;
6705  }
6706  return true;
6707 }
6708 
6709 EnableIfAttr *Sema::CheckEnableIf(FunctionDecl *Function,
6710  SourceLocation CallLoc,
6711  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
6712  bool MissingImplicitThis) {
6713  auto EnableIfAttrs = Function->specific_attrs<EnableIfAttr>();
6714  if (EnableIfAttrs.begin() == EnableIfAttrs.end())
6715  return nullptr;
6716 
6717  SFINAETrap Trap(*this);
6718  SmallVector<Expr *, 16> ConvertedArgs;
6719  // FIXME: We should look into making enable_if late-parsed.
6720  Expr *DiscardedThis;
6721  if (!convertArgsForAvailabilityChecks(
6722  *this, Function, /*ThisArg=*/nullptr, CallLoc, Args, Trap,
6723  /*MissingImplicitThis=*/true, DiscardedThis, ConvertedArgs))
6724  return *EnableIfAttrs.begin();
6725 
6726  for (auto *EIA : EnableIfAttrs) {
6727  APValue Result;
6728  // FIXME: This doesn't consider value-dependent cases, because doing so is
6729  // very difficult. Ideally, we should handle them more gracefully.
6730  if (EIA->getCond()->isValueDependent() ||
6731  !EIA->getCond()->EvaluateWithSubstitution(
6732  Result, Context, Function, llvm::makeArrayRef(ConvertedArgs)))
6733  return EIA;
6734 
6735  if (!Result.isInt() || !Result.getInt().getBoolValue())
6736  return EIA;
6737  }
6738  return nullptr;
6739 }
6740 
6741 template <typename CheckFn>
6742 static bool diagnoseDiagnoseIfAttrsWith(Sema &S, const NamedDecl *ND,
6743  bool ArgDependent, SourceLocation Loc,
6744  CheckFn &&IsSuccessful) {
6745  SmallVector<const DiagnoseIfAttr *, 8> Attrs;
6746  for (const auto *DIA : ND->specific_attrs<DiagnoseIfAttr>()) {
6747  if (ArgDependent == DIA->getArgDependent())
6748  Attrs.push_back(DIA);
6749  }
6750 
6751  // Common case: No diagnose_if attributes, so we can quit early.
6752  if (Attrs.empty())
6753  return false;
6754 
6755  auto WarningBegin = std::stable_partition(
6756  Attrs.begin(), Attrs.end(),
6757  [](const DiagnoseIfAttr *DIA) { return DIA->isError(); });
6758 
6759  // Note that diagnose_if attributes are late-parsed, so they appear in the
6760  // correct order (unlike enable_if attributes).
6761  auto ErrAttr = llvm::find_if(llvm::make_range(Attrs.begin(), WarningBegin),
6762  IsSuccessful);
6763  if (ErrAttr != WarningBegin) {
6764  const DiagnoseIfAttr *DIA = *ErrAttr;
6765  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_diagnose_if_succeeded) << DIA->getMessage();
6766  S.Diag(DIA->getLocation(), diag::note_from_diagnose_if)
6767  << DIA->getParent() << DIA->getCond()->getSourceRange();
6768  return true;
6769  }
6770 
6771  for (const auto *DIA : llvm::make_range(WarningBegin, Attrs.end()))
6772  if (IsSuccessful(DIA)) {
6773  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_diagnose_if_succeeded) << DIA->getMessage();
6774  S.Diag(DIA->getLocation(), diag::note_from_diagnose_if)
6775  << DIA->getParent() << DIA->getCond()->getSourceRange();
6776  }
6777 
6778  return false;
6779 }
6780 
6781 bool Sema::diagnoseArgDependentDiagnoseIfAttrs(const FunctionDecl *Function,
6782  const Expr *ThisArg,
6783  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args,
6784  SourceLocation Loc) {
6785  return diagnoseDiagnoseIfAttrsWith(
6786  *this, Function, /*ArgDependent=*/true, Loc,
6787  [&](const DiagnoseIfAttr *DIA) {
6788  APValue Result;
6789  // It's sane to use the same Args for any redecl of this function, since
6790  // EvaluateWithSubstitution only cares about the position of each
6791  // argument in the arg list, not the ParmVarDecl* it maps to.
6792  if (!DIA->getCond()->EvaluateWithSubstitution(
6793  Result, Context, cast<FunctionDecl>(DIA->getParent()), Args, ThisArg))
6794  return false;
6795  return Result.isInt() && Result.getInt().getBoolValue();
6796  });
6797 }
6798 
6799 bool Sema::diagnoseArgIndependentDiagnoseIfAttrs(const NamedDecl *ND,
6800  SourceLocation Loc) {
6801  return diagnoseDiagnoseIfAttrsWith(
6802  *this, ND, /*ArgDependent=*/false, Loc,
6803  [&](const DiagnoseIfAttr *DIA) {
6804  bool Result;
6805  return DIA->getCond()->EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(Result, Context) &&
6806  Result;
6807  });
6808 }
6809 
6810 /// Add all of the function declarations in the given function set to
6811 /// the overload candidate set.
6812 void Sema::AddFunctionCandidates(const UnresolvedSetImpl &Fns,
6813  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
6814  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
6815  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs,
6816  bool SuppressUserConversions,
6817  bool PartialOverloading,
6818  bool FirstArgumentIsBase) {
6819  for (UnresolvedSetIterator F = Fns.begin(), E = Fns.end(); F != E; ++F) {
6820  NamedDecl *D = F.getDecl()->getUnderlyingDecl();
6821  ArrayRef<Expr *> FunctionArgs = Args;
6822 
6823  FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D);
6824  FunctionDecl *FD =
6825  FunTmpl ? FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl() : cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
6826 
6827  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FD) && !cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)->isStatic()) {
6828  QualType ObjectType;
6829  Expr::Classification ObjectClassification;
6830  if (Args.size() > 0) {
6831  if (Expr *E = Args[0]) {
6832  // Use the explicit base to restrict the lookup:
6833  ObjectType = E->getType();
6834  // Pointers in the object arguments are implicitly dereferenced, so we
6835  // always classify them as l-values.
6836  if (!ObjectType.isNull() && ObjectType->isPointerType())
6837  ObjectClassification = Expr::Classification::makeSimpleLValue();
6838  else
6839  ObjectClassification = E->Classify(Context);
6840  } // .. else there is an implicit base.
6841  FunctionArgs = Args.slice(1);
6842  }
6843  if (FunTmpl) {
6844  AddMethodTemplateCandidate(
6845  FunTmpl, F.getPair(),
6846  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(FunTmpl->getDeclContext()),
6847  ExplicitTemplateArgs, ObjectType, ObjectClassification,
6848  FunctionArgs, CandidateSet, SuppressUserConversions,
6849  PartialOverloading);
6850  } else {
6851  AddMethodCandidate(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD), F.getPair(),
6852  cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)->getParent(), ObjectType,
6853  ObjectClassification, FunctionArgs, CandidateSet,
6854  SuppressUserConversions, PartialOverloading);
6855  }
6856  } else {
6857  // This branch handles both standalone functions and static methods.
6858 
6859  // Slice the first argument (which is the base) when we access
6860  // static method as non-static.
6861  if (Args.size() > 0 &&
6862  (!Args[0] || (FirstArgumentIsBase && isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FD) &&
6863  !isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(FD)))) {
6864  assert(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)->isStatic());
6865  FunctionArgs = Args.slice(1);
6866  }
6867  if (FunTmpl) {
6868  AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(FunTmpl, F.getPair(),
6869  ExplicitTemplateArgs, FunctionArgs,
6870  CandidateSet, SuppressUserConversions,
6871  PartialOverloading);
6872  } else {
6873  AddOverloadCandidate(FD, F.getPair(), FunctionArgs, CandidateSet,
6874  SuppressUserConversions, PartialOverloading);
6875  }
6876  }
6877  }
6878 }
6879 
6880 /// AddMethodCandidate - Adds a named decl (which is some kind of
6881 /// method) as a method candidate to the given overload set.
6882 void Sema::AddMethodCandidate(DeclAccessPair FoundDecl, QualType ObjectType,
6883  Expr::Classification ObjectClassification,
6884  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
6885  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
6886  bool SuppressUserConversions,
6887  OverloadCandidateParamOrder PO) {
6888  NamedDecl *Decl = FoundDecl.getDecl();
6889  CXXRecordDecl *ActingContext = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Decl->getDeclContext());
6890 
6891  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(Decl))
6892  Decl = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(Decl)->getTargetDecl();
6893 
6894  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *TD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Decl)) {
6895  assert(isa<CXXMethodDecl>(TD->getTemplatedDecl()) &&
6896  "Expected a member function template");
6897  AddMethodTemplateCandidate(TD, FoundDecl, ActingContext,
6898  /*ExplicitArgs*/ nullptr, ObjectType,
6899  ObjectClassification, Args, CandidateSet,
6900  SuppressUserConversions, false, PO);
6901  } else {
6902  AddMethodCandidate(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Decl), FoundDecl, ActingContext,
6903  ObjectType, ObjectClassification, Args, CandidateSet,
6904  SuppressUserConversions, false, None, PO);
6905  }
6906 }
6907 
6908 /// AddMethodCandidate - Adds the given C++ member function to the set
6909 /// of candidate functions, using the given function call arguments
6910 /// and the object argument (@c Object). For example, in a call
6911 /// @c o.f(a1,a2), @c Object will contain @c o and @c Args will contain
6912 /// both @c a1 and @c a2. If @p SuppressUserConversions, then don't
6913 /// allow user-defined conversions via constructors or conversion
6914 /// operators.
6915 void
6916 Sema::AddMethodCandidate(CXXMethodDecl *Method, DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
6917  CXXRecordDecl *ActingContext, QualType ObjectType,
6918  Expr::Classification ObjectClassification,
6919  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
6920  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
6921  bool SuppressUserConversions,
6922  bool PartialOverloading,
6923  ConversionSequenceList EarlyConversions,
6924  OverloadCandidateParamOrder PO) {
6925  const FunctionProtoType *Proto
6926  = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(Method->getType()->getAs<FunctionType>());
6927  assert(Proto && "Methods without a prototype cannot be overloaded");
6928  assert(!isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method) &&
6929  "Use AddOverloadCandidate for constructors");
6930 
6931  if (!CandidateSet.isNewCandidate(Method, PO))
6932  return;
6933 
6934  // C++11 [class.copy]p23: [DR1402]
6935  // A defaulted move assignment operator that is defined as deleted is
6936  // ignored by overload resolution.
6937  if (Method->isDefaulted() && Method->isDeleted() &&
6938  Method->isMoveAssignmentOperator())
6939  return;
6940 
6941  // Overload resolution is always an unevaluated context.
6942  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6943  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
6944 
6945  // Add this candidate
6946  OverloadCandidate &Candidate =
6947  CandidateSet.addCandidate(Args.size() + 1, EarlyConversions);
6948  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
6949  Candidate.Function = Method;
6950  Candidate.RewriteKind =
6951  CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().getRewriteKind(Method, PO);
6952  Candidate.IsSurrogate = false;
6953  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument = false;
6954  Candidate.ExplicitCallArguments = Args.size();
6955 
6956  unsigned NumParams = Proto->getNumParams();
6957 
6958  // (C++ 13.3.2p2): A candidate function having fewer than m
6959  // parameters is viable only if it has an ellipsis in its parameter
6960  // list (8.3.5).
6961  if (TooManyArguments(NumParams, Args.size(), PartialOverloading) &&
6962  !Proto->isVariadic() &&
6963  shouldEnforceArgLimit(PartialOverloading, Method)) {
6964  Candidate.Viable = false;
6965  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_too_many_arguments;
6966  return;
6967  }
6968 
6969  // (C++ 13.3.2p2): A candidate function having more than m parameters
6970  // is viable only if the (m+1)st parameter has a default argument
6971  // (8.3.6). For the purposes of overload resolution, the
6972  // parameter list is truncated on the right, so that there are
6973  // exactly m parameters.
6974  unsigned MinRequiredArgs = Method->getMinRequiredArguments();
6975  if (Args.size() < MinRequiredArgs && !PartialOverloading) {
6976  // Not enough arguments.
6977  Candidate.Viable = false;
6978  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_too_few_arguments;
6979  return;
6980  }
6981 
6982  Candidate.Viable = true;
6983 
6984  if (Method->isStatic() || ObjectType.isNull())
6985  // The implicit object argument is ignored.
6986  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument = true;
6987  else {
6988  unsigned ConvIdx = PO == OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed ? 1 : 0;
6989  // Determine the implicit conversion sequence for the object
6990  // parameter.
6991  Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx] = TryObjectArgumentInitialization(
6992  *this, CandidateSet.getLocation(), ObjectType, ObjectClassification,
6993  Method, ActingContext);
6994  if (Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx].isBad()) {
6995  Candidate.Viable = false;
6996  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
6997  return;
6998  }
6999  }
7000 
7001  // (CUDA B.1): Check for invalid calls between targets.
7002  if (getLangOpts().CUDA)
7003  if (const FunctionDecl *Caller = getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true))
7004  if (!IsAllowedCUDACall(Caller, Method)) {
7005  Candidate.Viable = false;
7006  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_target;
7007  return;
7008  }
7009 
7010  if (Method->getTrailingRequiresClause()) {
7011  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
7012  if (CheckFunctionConstraints(Method, Satisfaction) ||
7013  !Satisfaction.IsSatisfied) {
7014  Candidate.Viable = false;
7015  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_constraints_not_satisfied;
7016  return;
7017  }
7018  }
7019 
7020  // Determine the implicit conversion sequences for each of the
7021  // arguments.
7022  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx < Args.size(); ++ArgIdx) {
7023  unsigned ConvIdx =
7024  PO == OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed ? 0 : (ArgIdx + 1);
7025  if (Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx].isInitialized()) {
7026  // We already formed a conversion sequence for this parameter during
7027  // template argument deduction.
7028  } else if (ArgIdx < NumParams) {
7029  // (C++ 13.3.2p3): for F to be a viable function, there shall
7030  // exist for each argument an implicit conversion sequence
7031  // (13.3.3.1) that converts that argument to the corresponding
7032  // parameter of F.
7033  QualType ParamType = Proto->getParamType(ArgIdx);
7034  Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx]
7035  = TryCopyInitialization(*this, Args[ArgIdx], ParamType,
7036  SuppressUserConversions,
7037  /*InOverloadResolution=*/true,
7038  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/
7039  getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount);
7040  if (Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx].isBad()) {
7041  Candidate.Viable = false;
7042  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
7043  return;
7044  }
7045  } else {
7046  // (C++ 13.3.2p2): For the purposes of overload resolution, any
7047  // argument for which there is no corresponding parameter is
7048  // considered to "match the ellipsis" (C+ 13.3.3.1.3).
7049  Candidate.Conversions[ConvIdx].setEllipsis();
7050  }
7051  }
7052 
7053  if (EnableIfAttr *FailedAttr =
7054  CheckEnableIf(Method, CandidateSet.getLocation(), Args, true)) {
7055  Candidate.Viable = false;
7056  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_enable_if;
7057  Candidate.DeductionFailure.Data = FailedAttr;
7058  return;
7059  }
7060 
7061  if (Method->isMultiVersion() && Method->hasAttr<TargetAttr>() &&
7062  !Method->getAttr<TargetAttr>()->isDefaultVersion()) {
7063  Candidate.Viable = false;
7064  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_non_default_multiversion_function;
7065  }
7066 }
7067 
7068 /// Add a C++ member function template as a candidate to the candidate
7069 /// set, using template argument deduction to produce an appropriate member
7070 /// function template specialization.
7071 void Sema::AddMethodTemplateCandidate(
7072  FunctionTemplateDecl *MethodTmpl, DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
7073  CXXRecordDecl *ActingContext,
7074  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs, QualType ObjectType,
7075  Expr::Classification ObjectClassification, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
7076  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet, bool SuppressUserConversions,
7077  bool PartialOverloading, OverloadCandidateParamOrder PO) {
7078  if (!CandidateSet.isNewCandidate(MethodTmpl, PO))
7079  return;
7080 
7081  // C++ [over.match.funcs]p7:
7082  // In each case where a candidate is a function template, candidate
7083  // function template specializations are generated using template argument
7084  // deduction (14.8.3, 14.8.2). Those candidates are then handled as
7085  // candidate functions in the usual way.113) A given name can refer to one
7086  // or more function templates and also to a set of overloaded non-template
7087  // functions. In such a case, the candidate functions generated from each
7088  // function template are combined with the set of non-template candidate
7089  // functions.
7090  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(CandidateSet.getLocation());
7091  FunctionDecl *Specialization = nullptr;
7092  ConversionSequenceList Conversions;
7093  if (TemplateDeductionResult Result = DeduceTemplateArguments(
7094  MethodTmpl, ExplicitTemplateArgs, Args, Specialization, Info,
7095  PartialOverloading, [&](ArrayRef<QualType> ParamTypes) {
7096  return CheckNonDependentConversions(
7097  MethodTmpl, ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet, Conversions,
7098  SuppressUserConversions, ActingContext, ObjectType,
7099  ObjectClassification, PO);
7100  })) {
7101  OverloadCandidate &Candidate =
7102  CandidateSet.addCandidate(Conversions.size(), Conversions);
7103  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
7104  Candidate.Function = MethodTmpl->getTemplatedDecl();
7105  Candidate.Viable = false;
7106  Candidate.RewriteKind =
7107  CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().getRewriteKind(Candidate.Function, PO);
7108  Candidate.IsSurrogate = false;
7109  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument =
7110  cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Candidate.Function)->isStatic() ||
7111  ObjectType.isNull();
7112  Candidate.ExplicitCallArguments = Args.size();
7113  if (Result == TDK_NonDependentConversionFailure)
7114  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
7115  else {
7116  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_deduction;
7117  Candidate.DeductionFailure = MakeDeductionFailureInfo(Context, Result,
7118  Info);
7119  }
7120  return;
7121  }
7122 
7123  // Add the function template specialization produced by template argument
7124  // deduction as a candidate.
7125  assert(Specialization && "Missing member function template specialization?");
7126  assert(isa<CXXMethodDecl>(Specialization) &&
7127  "Specialization is not a member function?");
7128  AddMethodCandidate(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Specialization), FoundDecl,
7129  ActingContext, ObjectType, ObjectClassification, Args,
7130  CandidateSet, SuppressUserConversions, PartialOverloading,
7131  Conversions, PO);
7132 }
7133 
7134 /// Determine whether a given function template has a simple explicit specifier
7135 /// or a non-value-dependent explicit-specification that evaluates to true.
7136 static bool isNonDependentlyExplicit(FunctionTemplateDecl *FTD) {
7137  return ExplicitSpecifier::getFromDecl(FTD->getTemplatedDecl()).isExplicit();
7138 }
7139 
7140 /// Add a C++ function template specialization as a candidate
7141 /// in the candidate set, using template argument deduction to produce
7142 /// an appropriate function template specialization.
7143 void Sema::AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(
7144  FunctionTemplateDecl *FunctionTemplate, DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
7145  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
7146  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet, bool SuppressUserConversions,
7147  bool PartialOverloading, bool AllowExplicit, ADLCallKind IsADLCandidate,
7148  OverloadCandidateParamOrder PO) {
7149  if (!CandidateSet.isNewCandidate(FunctionTemplate, PO))
7150  return;
7151 
7152  // If the function template has a non-dependent explicit specification,
7153  // exclude it now if appropriate; we are not permitted to perform deduction
7154  // and substitution in this case.
7155  if (!AllowExplicit && isNonDependentlyExplicit(FunctionTemplate)) {
7156  OverloadCandidate &Candidate = CandidateSet.addCandidate();
7157  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
7158  Candidate.Function = FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl();
7159  Candidate.Viable = false;
7160  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_explicit;
7161  return;
7162  }
7163 
7164  // C++ [over.match.funcs]p7:
7165  // In each case where a candidate is a function template, candidate
7166  // function template specializations are generated using template argument
7167  // deduction (14.8.3, 14.8.2). Those candidates are then handled as
7168  // candidate functions in the usual way.113) A given name can refer to one
7169  // or more function templates and also to a set of overloaded non-template
7170  // functions. In such a case, the candidate functions generated from each
7171  // function template are combined with the set of non-template candidate
7172  // functions.
7173  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(CandidateSet.getLocation());
7174  FunctionDecl *Specialization = nullptr;
7175  ConversionSequenceList Conversions;
7176  if (TemplateDeductionResult Result = DeduceTemplateArguments(
7177  FunctionTemplate, ExplicitTemplateArgs, Args, Specialization, Info,
7178  PartialOverloading, [&](ArrayRef<QualType> ParamTypes) {
7179  return CheckNonDependentConversions(
7180  FunctionTemplate, ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet, Conversions,
7181  SuppressUserConversions, nullptr, QualType(), {}, PO);
7182  })) {
7183  OverloadCandidate &Candidate =
7184  CandidateSet.addCandidate(Conversions.size(), Conversions);
7185  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
7186  Candidate.Function = FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl();
7187  Candidate.Viable = false;
7188  Candidate.RewriteKind =
7189  CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().getRewriteKind(Candidate.Function, PO);
7190  Candidate.IsSurrogate = false;
7191  Candidate.IsADLCandidate = IsADLCandidate;
7192  // Ignore the object argument if there is one, since we don't have an object
7193  // type.
7194  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument =
7195  isa<CXXMethodDecl>(Candidate.Function) &&
7196  !isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Candidate.Function);
7197  Candidate.ExplicitCallArguments = Args.size();
7198  if (Result == TDK_NonDependentConversionFailure)
7199  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
7200  else {
7201  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_deduction;
7202  Candidate.DeductionFailure = MakeDeductionFailureInfo(Context, Result,
7203  Info);
7204  }
7205  return;
7206  }
7207 
7208  // Add the function template specialization produced by template argument
7209  // deduction as a candidate.
7210  assert(Specialization && "Missing function template specialization?");
7211  AddOverloadCandidate(
7212  Specialization, FoundDecl, Args, CandidateSet, SuppressUserConversions,
7213  PartialOverloading, AllowExplicit,
7214  /*AllowExplicitConversions*/ false, IsADLCandidate, Conversions, PO);
7215 }
7216 
7217 /// Check that implicit conversion sequences can be formed for each argument
7218 /// whose corresponding parameter has a non-dependent type, per DR1391's
7219 /// [temp.deduct.call]p10.
7220 bool Sema::CheckNonDependentConversions(
7221  FunctionTemplateDecl *FunctionTemplate, ArrayRef<QualType> ParamTypes,
7222  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args, OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
7223  ConversionSequenceList &Conversions, bool SuppressUserConversions,
7224  CXXRecordDecl *ActingContext, QualType ObjectType,
7225  Expr::Classification ObjectClassification, OverloadCandidateParamOrder PO) {
7226  // FIXME: The cases in which we allow explicit conversions for constructor
7227  // arguments never consider calling a constructor template. It's not clear
7228  // that is correct.
7229  const bool AllowExplicit = false;
7230 
7231  auto *FD = FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl();
7232  auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD);
7233  bool HasThisConversion = Method && !isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method);
7234  unsigned ThisConversions = HasThisConversion ? 1 : 0;
7235 
7236  Conversions =
7237  CandidateSet.allocateConversionSequences(ThisConversions + Args.size());
7238 
7239  // Overload resolution is always an unevaluated context.
7240  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
7241  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
7242 
7243  // For a method call, check the 'this' conversion here too. DR1391 doesn't
7244  // require that, but this check should never result in a hard error, and
7245  // overload resolution is permitted to sidestep instantiations.
7246  if (HasThisConversion && !cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)->isStatic() &&
7247  !ObjectType.isNull()) {
7248  unsigned ConvIdx = PO == OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed ? 1 : 0;
7249  Conversions[ConvIdx] = TryObjectArgumentInitialization(
7250  *this, CandidateSet.getLocation(), ObjectType, ObjectClassification,
7251  Method, ActingContext);
7252  if (Conversions[ConvIdx].isBad())
7253  return true;
7254  }
7255 
7256  for (unsigned I = 0, N = std::min(ParamTypes.size(), Args.size()); I != N;
7257  ++I) {
7258  QualType ParamType = ParamTypes[I];
7259  if (!ParamType->isDependentType()) {
7260  unsigned ConvIdx = PO == OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed
7261  ? 0
7262  : (ThisConversions + I);
7263  Conversions[ConvIdx]
7264  = TryCopyInitialization(*this, Args[I], ParamType,
7265  SuppressUserConversions,
7266  /*InOverloadResolution=*/true,
7267  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/
7268  getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount,
7269  AllowExplicit);
7270  if (Conversions[ConvIdx].isBad())
7271  return true;
7272  }
7273  }
7274 
7275  return false;
7276 }
7277 
7278 /// Determine whether this is an allowable conversion from the result
7279 /// of an explicit conversion operator to the expected type, per C++
7280 /// [over.match.conv]p1 and [over.match.ref]p1.
7281 ///
7282 /// \param ConvType The return type of the conversion function.
7283 ///
7284 /// \param ToType The type we are converting to.
7285 ///
7286 /// \param AllowObjCPointerConversion Allow a conversion from one
7287 /// Objective-C pointer to another.
7288 ///
7289 /// \returns true if the conversion is allowable, false otherwise.
7290 static bool isAllowableExplicitConversion(Sema &S,
7291  QualType ConvType, QualType ToType,
7292  bool AllowObjCPointerConversion) {
7293  QualType ToNonRefType = ToType.getNonReferenceType();
7294 
7295  // Easy case: the types are the same.
7296  if (S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ConvType, ToNonRefType))
7297  return true;
7298 
7299  // Allow qualification conversions.
7300  bool ObjCLifetimeConversion;
7301  if (S.IsQualificationConversion(ConvType, ToNonRefType, /*CStyle*/false,
7302  ObjCLifetimeConversion))
7303  return true;
7304 
7305  // If we're not allowed to consider Objective-C pointer conversions,
7306  // we're done.
7307  if (!AllowObjCPointerConversion)
7308  return false;
7309 
7310  // Is this an Objective-C pointer conversion?
7311  bool IncompatibleObjC = false;
7312  QualType ConvertedType;
7313  return S.isObjCPointerConversion(ConvType, ToNonRefType, ConvertedType,
7314  IncompatibleObjC);
7315 }
7316 
7317 /// AddConversionCandidate - Add a C++ conversion function as a
7318 /// candidate in the candidate set (C++ [over.match.conv],
7319 /// C++ [over.match.copy]). From is the expression we're converting from,
7320 /// and ToType is the type that we're eventually trying to convert to
7321 /// (which may or may not be the same type as the type that the
7322 /// conversion function produces).
7323 void Sema::AddConversionCandidate(
7324  CXXConversionDecl *Conversion, DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
7325  CXXRecordDecl *ActingContext, Expr *From, QualType ToType,
7326  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet, bool AllowObjCConversionOnExplicit,
7327  bool AllowExplicit, bool AllowResultConversion) {
7328  assert(!Conversion->getDescribedFunctionTemplate() &&
7329  "Conversion function templates use AddTemplateConversionCandidate");
7330  QualType ConvType = Conversion->getConversionType().getNonReferenceType();
7331  if (!CandidateSet.isNewCandidate(Conversion))
7332  return;
7333 
7334  // If the conversion function has an undeduced return type, trigger its
7335  // deduction now.
7336  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 && ConvType->isUndeducedType()) {
7337  if (DeduceReturnType(Conversion, From->getExprLoc()))
7338  return;
7339  ConvType = Conversion->getConversionType().getNonReferenceType();
7340  }
7341 
7342  // If we don't allow any conversion of the result type, ignore conversion
7343  // functions that don't convert to exactly (possibly cv-qualified) T.
7344  if (!AllowResultConversion &&
7345  !Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(Conversion->getConversionType(), ToType))
7346  return;
7347 
7348  // Per C++ [over.match.conv]p1, [over.match.ref]p1, an explicit conversion
7349  // operator is only a candidate if its return type is the target type or
7350  // can be converted to the target type with a qualification conversion.
7351  //
7352  // FIXME: Include such functions in the candidate list and explain why we
7353  // can't select them.
7354  if (Conversion->isExplicit() &&
7355  !isAllowableExplicitConversion(*this, ConvType, ToType,
7356  AllowObjCConversionOnExplicit))
7357  return;
7358 
7359  // Overload resolution is always an unevaluated context.
7360  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
7361  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
7362 
7363  // Add this candidate
7364  OverloadCandidate &Candidate = CandidateSet.addCandidate(1);
7365  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
7366  Candidate.Function = Conversion;
7367  Candidate.IsSurrogate = false;
7368  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument = false;
7369  Candidate.FinalConversion.setAsIdentityConversion();
7370  Candidate.FinalConversion.setFromType(ConvType);
7371  Candidate.FinalConversion.setAllToTypes(ToType);
7372  Candidate.Viable = true;
7373  Candidate.ExplicitCallArguments = 1;
7374 
7375  // Explicit functions are not actually candidates at all if we're not
7376  // allowing them in this context, but keep them around so we can point
7377  // to them in diagnostics.
7378  if (!AllowExplicit && Conversion->isExplicit()) {
7379  Candidate.Viable = false;
7380  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_explicit;
7381  return;
7382  }
7383 
7384  // C++ [over.match.funcs]p4:
7385  // For conversion functions, the function is considered to be a member of
7386  // the class of the implicit implied object argument for the purpose of
7387  // defining the type of the implicit object parameter.
7388  //
7389  // Determine the implicit conversion sequence for the implicit
7390  // object parameter.
7391  QualType ImplicitParamType = From->getType();
7392  if (const PointerType *FromPtrType = ImplicitParamType->getAs<PointerType>())
7393  ImplicitParamType = FromPtrType->getPointeeType();
7394  CXXRecordDecl *ConversionContext
7395  = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ImplicitParamType->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
7396 
7397  Candidate.Conversions[0] = TryObjectArgumentInitialization(
7398  *this, CandidateSet.getLocation(), From->getType(),
7399  From->Classify(Context), Conversion, ConversionContext);
7400 
7401  if (Candidate.Conversions[0].isBad()) {
7402  Candidate.Viable = false;
7403  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
7404  return;
7405  }
7406 
7407  if (Conversion->getTrailingRequiresClause()) {
7408  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
7409  if (CheckFunctionConstraints(Conversion, Satisfaction) ||
7410  !Satisfaction.IsSatisfied) {
7411  Candidate.Viable = false;
7412  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_constraints_not_satisfied;
7413  return;
7414  }
7415  }
7416 
7417  // We won't go through a user-defined type conversion function to convert a
7418  // derived to base as such conversions are given Conversion Rank. They only
7419  // go through a copy constructor. 13.3.3.1.2-p4 [over.ics.user]
7420  QualType FromCanon
7421  = Context.getCanonicalType(From->getType().getUnqualifiedType());
7422  QualType ToCanon = Context.getCanonicalType(ToType).getUnqualifiedType();
7423  if (FromCanon == ToCanon ||
7424  IsDerivedFrom(CandidateSet.getLocation(), FromCanon, ToCanon)) {
7425  Candidate.Viable = false;
7426  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_trivial_conversion;
7427  return;
7428  }
7429 
7430  // To determine what the conversion from the result of calling the
7431  // conversion function to the type we're eventually trying to
7432  // convert to (ToType), we need to synthesize a call to the
7433  // conversion function and attempt copy initialization from it. This
7434  // makes sure that we get the right semantics with respect to
7435  // lvalues/rvalues and the type. Fortunately, we can allocate this
7436  // call on the stack and we don't need its arguments to be
7437  // well-formed.
7438  DeclRefExpr ConversionRef(Context, Conversion, false, Conversion->getType(),
7439  VK_LValue, From->getBeginLoc());
7440  ImplicitCastExpr ConversionFn(ImplicitCastExpr::OnStack,
7441  Context.getPointerType(Conversion->getType()),
7442  CK_FunctionToPointerDecay, &ConversionRef,
7443  VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
7444 
7445  QualType ConversionType = Conversion->getConversionType();
7446  if (!isCompleteType(From->getBeginLoc(), ConversionType)) {
7447  Candidate.Viable = false;
7448  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_final_conversion;
7449  return;
7450  }
7451 
7452  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ConversionType);
7453 
7454  // Note that it is safe to allocate CallExpr on the stack here because
7455  // there are 0 arguments (i.e., nothing is allocated using ASTContext's
7456  // allocator).
7457  QualType CallResultType = ConversionType.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
7458 
7459  alignas(CallExpr) char Buffer[sizeof(CallExpr) + sizeof(Stmt *)];
7460  CallExpr *TheTemporaryCall = CallExpr::CreateTemporary(
7461  Buffer, &ConversionFn, CallResultType, VK, From->getBeginLoc());
7462 
7463  ImplicitConversionSequence ICS =
7464  TryCopyInitialization(*this, TheTemporaryCall, ToType,
7465  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/true,
7466  /*InOverloadResolution=*/false,
7467  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/false);
7468 
7469  switch (ICS.getKind()) {
7470  case ImplicitConversionSequence::StandardConversion:
7471  Candidate.FinalConversion = ICS.Standard;
7472 
7473  // C++ [over.ics.user]p3:
7474  // If the user-defined conversion is specified by a specialization of a
7475  // conversion function template, the second standard conversion sequence
7476  // shall have exact match rank.
7477  if (Conversion->getPrimaryTemplate() &&
7478  GetConversionRank(ICS.Standard.Second) != ICR_Exact_Match) {
7479  Candidate.Viable = false;
7480  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_final_conversion_not_exact;
7481  return;
7482  }
7483 
7484  // C++0x [dcl.init.ref]p5:
7485  // In the second case, if the reference is an rvalue reference and
7486  // the second standard conversion sequence of the user-defined
7487  // conversion sequence includes an lvalue-to-rvalue conversion, the
7488  // program is ill-formed.
7489  if (ToType->isRValueReferenceType() &&
7490  ICS.Standard.First == ICK_Lvalue_To_Rvalue) {
7491  Candidate.Viable = false;
7492  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_final_conversion;
7493  return;
7494  }
7495  break;
7496 
7497  case ImplicitConversionSequence::BadConversion:
7498  Candidate.Viable = false;
7499  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_final_conversion;
7500  return;
7501 
7502  default:
7503  llvm_unreachable(
7504  "Can only end up with a standard conversion sequence or failure");
7505  }
7506 
7507  if (EnableIfAttr *FailedAttr =
7508  CheckEnableIf(Conversion, CandidateSet.getLocation(), None)) {
7509  Candidate.Viable = false;
7510  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_enable_if;
7511  Candidate.DeductionFailure.Data = FailedAttr;
7512  return;
7513  }
7514 
7515  if (Conversion->isMultiVersion() && Conversion->hasAttr<TargetAttr>() &&
7516  !Conversion->getAttr<TargetAttr>()->isDefaultVersion()) {
7517  Candidate.Viable = false;
7518  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_non_default_multiversion_function;
7519  }
7520 }
7521 
7522 /// Adds a conversion function template specialization
7523 /// candidate to the overload set, using template argument deduction
7524 /// to deduce the template arguments of the conversion function
7525 /// template from the type that we are converting to (C++
7526 /// [temp.deduct.conv]).
7527 void Sema::AddTemplateConversionCandidate(
7528  FunctionTemplateDecl *FunctionTemplate, DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
7529  CXXRecordDecl *ActingDC, Expr *From, QualType ToType,
7530  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet, bool AllowObjCConversionOnExplicit,
7531  bool AllowExplicit, bool AllowResultConversion) {
7532  assert(isa<CXXConversionDecl>(FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl()) &&
7533  "Only conversion function templates permitted here");
7534 
7535  if (!CandidateSet.isNewCandidate(FunctionTemplate))
7536  return;
7537 
7538  // If the function template has a non-dependent explicit specification,
7539  // exclude it now if appropriate; we are not permitted to perform deduction
7540  // and substitution in this case.
7541  if (!AllowExplicit && isNonDependentlyExplicit(FunctionTemplate)) {
7542  OverloadCandidate &Candidate = CandidateSet.addCandidate();
7543  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
7544  Candidate.Function = FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl();
7545  Candidate.Viable = false;
7546  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_explicit;
7547  return;
7548  }
7549 
7550  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(CandidateSet.getLocation());
7551  CXXConversionDecl *Specialization = nullptr;
7552  if (TemplateDeductionResult Result
7553  = DeduceTemplateArguments(FunctionTemplate, ToType,
7554  Specialization, Info)) {
7555  OverloadCandidate &Candidate = CandidateSet.addCandidate();
7556  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
7557  Candidate.Function = FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl();
7558  Candidate.Viable = false;
7559  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_deduction;
7560  Candidate.IsSurrogate = false;
7561  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument = false;
7562  Candidate.ExplicitCallArguments = 1;
7563  Candidate.DeductionFailure = MakeDeductionFailureInfo(Context, Result,
7564  Info);
7565  return;
7566  }
7567 
7568  // Add the conversion function template specialization produced by
7569  // template argument deduction as a candidate.
7570  assert(Specialization && "Missing function template specialization?");
7571  AddConversionCandidate(Specialization, FoundDecl, ActingDC, From, ToType,
7572  CandidateSet, AllowObjCConversionOnExplicit,
7573  AllowExplicit, AllowResultConversion);
7574 }
7575 
7576 /// AddSurrogateCandidate - Adds a "surrogate" candidate function that
7577 /// converts the given @c Object to a function pointer via the
7578 /// conversion function @c Conversion, and then attempts to call it
7579 /// with the given arguments (C++ [over.call.object]p2-4). Proto is
7580 /// the type of function that we'll eventually be calling.
7581 void Sema::AddSurrogateCandidate(CXXConversionDecl *Conversion,
7582  DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
7583  CXXRecordDecl *ActingContext,
7584  const FunctionProtoType *Proto,
7585  Expr *Object,
7586  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
7587  OverloadCandidateSet& CandidateSet) {
7588  if (!CandidateSet.isNewCandidate(Conversion))
7589  return;
7590 
7591  // Overload resolution is always an unevaluated context.
7592  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
7593  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
7594 
7595  OverloadCandidate &Candidate = CandidateSet.addCandidate(Args.size() + 1);
7596  Candidate.FoundDecl = FoundDecl;
7597  Candidate.Function = nullptr;
7598  Candidate.Surrogate = Conversion;
7599  Candidate.Viable = true;
7600  Candidate.IsSurrogate = true;
7601  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument = false;
7602  Candidate.ExplicitCallArguments = Args.size();
7603 
7604  // Determine the implicit conversion sequence for the implicit
7605  // object parameter.
7606  ImplicitConversionSequence ObjectInit = TryObjectArgumentInitialization(
7607  *this, CandidateSet.getLocation(), Object->getType(),
7608  Object->Classify(Context), Conversion, ActingContext);
7609  if (ObjectInit.isBad()) {
7610  Candidate.Viable = false;
7611  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
7612  Candidate.Conversions[0] = ObjectInit;
7613  return;
7614  }
7615 
7616  // The first conversion is actually a user-defined conversion whose
7617  // first conversion is ObjectInit's standard conversion (which is
7618  // effectively a reference binding). Record it as such.
7619  Candidate.Conversions[0].setUserDefined();
7620  Candidate.Conversions[0].UserDefined.Before = ObjectInit.Standard;
7621  Candidate.Conversions[0].UserDefined.EllipsisConversion = false;
7622  Candidate.Conversions[0].UserDefined.HadMultipleCandidates = false;
7623  Candidate.Conversions[0].UserDefined.ConversionFunction = Conversion;
7624  Candidate.Conversions[0].UserDefined.FoundConversionFunction = FoundDecl;
7625  Candidate.Conversions[0].UserDefined.After
7626  = Candidate.Conversions[0].UserDefined.Before;
7627  Candidate.Conversions[0].UserDefined.After.setAsIdentityConversion();
7628 
7629  // Find the
7630  unsigned NumParams = Proto->getNumParams();
7631 
7632  // (C++ 13.3.2p2): A candidate function having fewer than m
7633  // parameters is viable only if it has an ellipsis in its parameter
7634  // list (8.3.5).
7635  if (Args.size() > NumParams && !Proto->isVariadic()) {
7636  Candidate.Viable = false;
7637  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_too_many_arguments;
7638  return;
7639  }
7640 
7641  // Function types don't have any default arguments, so just check if
7642  // we have enough arguments.
7643  if (Args.size() < NumParams) {
7644  // Not enough arguments.
7645  Candidate.Viable = false;
7646  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_too_few_arguments;
7647  return;
7648  }
7649 
7650  // Determine the implicit conversion sequences for each of the
7651  // arguments.
7652  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0, N = Args.size(); ArgIdx != N; ++ArgIdx) {
7653  if (ArgIdx < NumParams) {
7654  // (C++ 13.3.2p3): for F to be a viable function, there shall
7655  // exist for each argument an implicit conversion sequence
7656  // (13.3.3.1) that converts that argument to the corresponding
7657  // parameter of F.
7658  QualType ParamType = Proto->getParamType(ArgIdx);
7659  Candidate.Conversions[ArgIdx + 1]
7660  = TryCopyInitialization(*this, Args[ArgIdx], ParamType,
7661  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false,
7662  /*InOverloadResolution=*/false,
7663  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/
7664  getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount);
7665  if (Candidate.Conversions[ArgIdx + 1].isBad()) {
7666  Candidate.Viable = false;
7667  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
7668  return;
7669  }
7670  } else {
7671  // (C++ 13.3.2p2): For the purposes of overload resolution, any
7672  // argument for which there is no corresponding parameter is
7673  // considered to ""match the ellipsis" (C+ 13.3.3.1.3).
7674  Candidate.Conversions[ArgIdx + 1].setEllipsis();
7675  }
7676  }
7677 
7678  if (EnableIfAttr *FailedAttr =
7679  CheckEnableIf(Conversion, CandidateSet.getLocation(), None)) {
7680  Candidate.Viable = false;
7681  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_enable_if;
7682  Candidate.DeductionFailure.Data = FailedAttr;
7683  return;
7684  }
7685 }
7686 
7687 /// Add all of the non-member operator function declarations in the given
7688 /// function set to the overload candidate set.
7689 void Sema::AddNonMemberOperatorCandidates(
7690  const UnresolvedSetImpl &Fns, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
7691  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
7692  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs) {
7693  for (UnresolvedSetIterator F = Fns.begin(), E = Fns.end(); F != E; ++F) {
7694  NamedDecl *D = F.getDecl()->getUnderlyingDecl();
7695  ArrayRef<Expr *> FunctionArgs = Args;
7696 
7697  FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D);
7698  FunctionDecl *FD =
7699  FunTmpl ? FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl() : cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
7700 
7701  // Don't consider rewritten functions if we're not rewriting.
7702  if (!CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().isAcceptableCandidate(FD))
7703  continue;
7704 
7705  assert(!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FD) &&
7706  "unqualified operator lookup found a member function");
7707 
7708  if (FunTmpl) {
7709  AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(FunTmpl, F.getPair(), ExplicitTemplateArgs,
7710  FunctionArgs, CandidateSet);
7711  if (CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().shouldAddReversed(Context, FD))
7712  AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(
7713  FunTmpl, F.getPair(), ExplicitTemplateArgs,
7714  {FunctionArgs[1], FunctionArgs[0]}, CandidateSet, false, false,
7715  true, ADLCallKind::NotADL, OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed);
7716  } else {
7717  if (ExplicitTemplateArgs)
7718  continue;
7719  AddOverloadCandidate(FD, F.getPair(), FunctionArgs, CandidateSet);
7720  if (CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().shouldAddReversed(Context, FD))
7721  AddOverloadCandidate(FD, F.getPair(),
7722  {FunctionArgs[1], FunctionArgs[0]}, CandidateSet,
7723  false, false, true, false, ADLCallKind::NotADL,
7724  None, OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed);
7725  }
7726  }
7727 }
7728 
7729 /// Add overload candidates for overloaded operators that are
7730 /// member functions.
7731 ///
7732 /// Add the overloaded operator candidates that are member functions
7733 /// for the operator Op that was used in an operator expression such
7734 /// as "x Op y". , Args/NumArgs provides the operator arguments, and
7735 /// CandidateSet will store the added overload candidates. (C++
7736 /// [over.match.oper]).
7737 void Sema::AddMemberOperatorCandidates(OverloadedOperatorKind Op,
7738  SourceLocation OpLoc,
7739  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
7740  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
7741  OverloadCandidateParamOrder PO) {
7742  DeclarationName OpName = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Op);
7743 
7744  // C++ [over.match.oper]p3:
7745  // For a unary operator @ with an operand of a type whose
7746  // cv-unqualified version is T1, and for a binary operator @ with
7747  // a left operand of a type whose cv-unqualified version is T1 and
7748  // a right operand of a type whose cv-unqualified version is T2,
7749  // three sets of candidate functions, designated member
7750  // candidates, non-member candidates and built-in candidates, are
7751  // constructed as follows:
7752  QualType T1 = Args[0]->getType();
7753 
7754  // -- If T1 is a complete class type or a class currently being
7755  // defined, the set of member candidates is the result of the
7756  // qualified lookup of T1::operator@ (13.3.1.1.1); otherwise,
7757  // the set of member candidates is empty.
7758  if (const RecordType *T1Rec = T1->getAs<RecordType>()) {
7759  // Complete the type if it can be completed.
7760  if (!isCompleteType(OpLoc, T1) && !T1Rec->isBeingDefined())
7761  return;
7762  // If the type is neither complete nor being defined, bail out now.
7763  if (!T1Rec->getDecl()->getDefinition())
7764  return;
7765 
7766  LookupResult Operators(*this, OpName, OpLoc, LookupOrdinaryName);
7767  LookupQualifiedName(Operators, T1Rec->getDecl());
7768  Operators.suppressDiagnostics();
7769 
7770  for (LookupResult::iterator Oper = Operators.begin(),
7771  OperEnd = Operators.end();
7772  Oper != OperEnd;
7773  ++Oper)
7774  AddMethodCandidate(Oper.getPair(), Args[0]->getType(),
7775  Args[0]->Classify(Context), Args.slice(1),
7776  CandidateSet, /*SuppressUserConversion=*/false, PO);
7777  }
7778 }
7779 
7780 /// AddBuiltinCandidate - Add a candidate for a built-in
7781 /// operator. ResultTy and ParamTys are the result and parameter types
7782 /// of the built-in candidate, respectively. Args and NumArgs are the
7783 /// arguments being passed to the candidate. IsAssignmentOperator
7784 /// should be true when this built-in candidate is an assignment
7785 /// operator. NumContextualBoolArguments is the number of arguments
7786 /// (at the beginning of the argument list) that will be contextually
7787 /// converted to bool.
7788 void Sema::AddBuiltinCandidate(QualType *ParamTys, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
7789  OverloadCandidateSet& CandidateSet,
7790  bool IsAssignmentOperator,
7791  unsigned NumContextualBoolArguments) {
7792  // Overload resolution is always an unevaluated context.
7793  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
7794  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
7795 
7796  // Add this candidate
7797  OverloadCandidate &Candidate = CandidateSet.addCandidate(Args.size());
7798  Candidate.FoundDecl = DeclAccessPair::make(nullptr, AS_none);
7799  Candidate.Function = nullptr;
7800  Candidate.IsSurrogate = false;
7801  Candidate.IgnoreObjectArgument = false;
7802  std::copy(ParamTys, ParamTys + Args.size(), Candidate.BuiltinParamTypes);
7803 
7804  // Determine the implicit conversion sequences for each of the
7805  // arguments.
7806  Candidate.Viable = true;
7807  Candidate.ExplicitCallArguments = Args.size();
7808  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0, N = Args.size(); ArgIdx != N; ++ArgIdx) {
7809  // C++ [over.match.oper]p4:
7810  // For the built-in assignment operators, conversions of the
7811  // left operand are restricted as follows:
7812  // -- no temporaries are introduced to hold the left operand, and
7813  // -- no user-defined conversions are applied to the left
7814  // operand to achieve a type match with the left-most
7815  // parameter of a built-in candidate.
7816  //
7817  // We block these conversions by turning off user-defined
7818  // conversions, since that is the only way that initialization of
7819  // a reference to a non-class type can occur from something that
7820  // is not of the same type.
7821  if (ArgIdx < NumContextualBoolArguments) {
7822  assert(ParamTys[ArgIdx] == Context.BoolTy &&
7823  "Contextual conversion to bool requires bool type");
7824  Candidate.Conversions[ArgIdx]
