7825  = TryContextuallyConvertToBool(*this, Args[ArgIdx]);
7826  } else {
7827  Candidate.Conversions[ArgIdx]
7828  = TryCopyInitialization(*this, Args[ArgIdx], ParamTys[ArgIdx],
7829  ArgIdx == 0 && IsAssignmentOperator,
7830  /*InOverloadResolution=*/false,
7831  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/
7832  getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount);
7833  }
7834  if (Candidate.Conversions[ArgIdx].isBad()) {
7835  Candidate.Viable = false;
7836  Candidate.FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
7837  break;
7838  }
7839  }
7840 }

7844 /// BuiltinCandidateTypeSet - A set of types that will be used for the
7845 /// candidate operator functions for built-in operators (C++
7846 /// [over.built]). The types are separated into pointer types and
7847 /// enumeration types.
7848 class BuiltinCandidateTypeSet {
7849  /// TypeSet - A set of types.
7850  typedef llvm::SetVector<QualType, SmallVector<QualType, 8>,
7851  llvm::SmallPtrSet<QualType, 8>> TypeSet;
7852 
7853  /// PointerTypes - The set of pointer types that will be used in the
7854  /// built-in candidates.
7855  TypeSet PointerTypes;
7856 
7857  /// MemberPointerTypes - The set of member pointer types that will be
7858  /// used in the built-in candidates.
7859  TypeSet MemberPointerTypes;
7860 
7861  /// EnumerationTypes - The set of enumeration types that will be
7862  /// used in the built-in candidates.
7863  TypeSet EnumerationTypes;
7864 
7865  /// The set of vector types that will be used in the built-in
7866  /// candidates.
7867  TypeSet VectorTypes;
7868 
7869  /// The set of matrix types that will be used in the built-in
7870  /// candidates.
7871  TypeSet MatrixTypes;
7872 
7873  /// A flag indicating non-record types are viable candidates
7874  bool HasNonRecordTypes;
7875 
7876  /// A flag indicating whether either arithmetic or enumeration types
7877  /// were present in the candidate set.
7878  bool HasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes;
7879 
7880  /// A flag indicating whether the nullptr type was present in the
7881  /// candidate set.
7882  bool HasNullPtrType;
7883 
7884  /// Sema - The semantic analysis instance where we are building the
7885  /// candidate type set.
7886  Sema &SemaRef;
7887 
7888  /// Context - The AST context in which we will build the type sets.
7889  ASTContext &Context;
7890 
7891  bool AddPointerWithMoreQualifiedTypeVariants(QualType Ty,
7892  const Qualifiers &VisibleQuals);
7893  bool AddMemberPointerWithMoreQualifiedTypeVariants(QualType Ty);
7894 
7895 public:
7896  /// iterator - Iterates through the types that are part of the set.
7897  typedef TypeSet::iterator iterator;
7898 
7899  BuiltinCandidateTypeSet(Sema &SemaRef)
7900  : HasNonRecordTypes(false),
7901  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes(false),
7902  HasNullPtrType(false),
7903  SemaRef(SemaRef),
7904  Context(SemaRef.Context) { }
7905 
7906  void AddTypesConvertedFrom(QualType Ty,
7907  SourceLocation Loc,
7908  bool AllowUserConversions,
7909  bool AllowExplicitConversions,
7910  const Qualifiers &VisibleTypeConversionsQuals);
7911 
7912  llvm::iterator_range<iterator> pointer_types() { return PointerTypes; }
7913  llvm::iterator_range<iterator> member_pointer_types() {
7914  return MemberPointerTypes;
7915  }
7916  llvm::iterator_range<iterator> enumeration_types() {
7917  return EnumerationTypes;
7918  }
7919  llvm::iterator_range<iterator> vector_types() { return VectorTypes; }
7920  llvm::iterator_range<iterator> matrix_types() { return MatrixTypes; }
7921 
7922  bool containsMatrixType(QualType Ty) const { return MatrixTypes.count(Ty); }
7923  bool hasNonRecordTypes() { return HasNonRecordTypes; }
7924  bool hasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes() { return HasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes; }
7925  bool hasNullPtrType() const { return HasNullPtrType; }
7926 };

7929 
7930 /// AddPointerWithMoreQualifiedTypeVariants - Add the pointer type @p Ty to
7931 /// the set of pointer types along with any more-qualified variants of
7932 /// that type. For example, if @p Ty is "int const *", this routine
7933 /// will add "int const *", "int const volatile *", "int const
7934 /// restrict *", and "int const volatile restrict *" to the set of
7935 /// pointer types. Returns true if the add of @p Ty itself succeeded,
7936 /// false otherwise.
7937 ///
7938 /// FIXME: what to do about extended qualifiers?
7939 bool
7940 BuiltinCandidateTypeSet::AddPointerWithMoreQualifiedTypeVariants(QualType Ty,
7941  const Qualifiers &VisibleQuals) {
7942 
7943  // Insert this type.
7944  if (!PointerTypes.insert(Ty))
7945  return false;
7946 
7947  QualType PointeeTy;
7948  const PointerType *PointerTy = Ty->getAs<PointerType>();
7949  bool buildObjCPtr = false;
7950  if (!PointerTy) {
7951  const ObjCObjectPointerType *PTy = Ty->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
7952  PointeeTy = PTy->getPointeeType();
7953  buildObjCPtr = true;
7954  } else {
7955  PointeeTy = PointerTy->getPointeeType();
7956  }
7957 
7958  // Don't add qualified variants of arrays. For one, they're not allowed
7959  // (the qualifier would sink to the element type), and for another, the
7960  // only overload situation where it matters is subscript or pointer +- int,
7961  // and those shouldn't have qualifier variants anyway.
7962  if (PointeeTy->isArrayType())
7963  return true;
7964 
7965  unsigned BaseCVR = PointeeTy.getCVRQualifiers();
7966  bool hasVolatile = VisibleQuals.hasVolatile();
7967  bool hasRestrict = VisibleQuals.hasRestrict();
7968 
7969  // Iterate through all strict supersets of BaseCVR.
7970  for (unsigned CVR = BaseCVR+1; CVR <= Qualifiers::CVRMask; ++CVR) {
7971  if ((CVR | BaseCVR) != CVR) continue;
7972  // Skip over volatile if no volatile found anywhere in the types.
7973  if ((CVR & Qualifiers::Volatile) && !hasVolatile) continue;
7974 
7975  // Skip over restrict if no restrict found anywhere in the types, or if
7976  // the type cannot be restrict-qualified.
7977  if ((CVR & Qualifiers::Restrict) &&
7978  (!hasRestrict ||
7979  (!(PointeeTy->isAnyPointerType() || PointeeTy->isReferenceType()))))
7980  continue;
7981 
7982  // Build qualified pointee type.
7983  QualType QPointeeTy = Context.getCVRQualifiedType(PointeeTy, CVR);
7984 
7985  // Build qualified pointer type.
7986  QualType QPointerTy;
7987  if (!buildObjCPtr)
7988  QPointerTy = Context.getPointerType(QPointeeTy);
7989  else
7990  QPointerTy = Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(QPointeeTy);
7991 
7992  // Insert qualified pointer type.
7993  PointerTypes.insert(QPointerTy);
7994  }
7995 
7996  return true;
7997 }
7998 
7999 /// AddMemberPointerWithMoreQualifiedTypeVariants - Add the pointer type @p Ty
8000 /// to the set of pointer types along with any more-qualified variants of
8001 /// that type. For example, if @p Ty is "int const *", this routine
8002 /// will add "int const *", "int const volatile *", "int const
8003 /// restrict *", and "int const volatile restrict *" to the set of
8004 /// pointer types. Returns true if the add of @p Ty itself succeeded,
8005 /// false otherwise.
8006 ///
8007 /// FIXME: what to do about extended qualifiers?
8008 bool
8009 BuiltinCandidateTypeSet::AddMemberPointerWithMoreQualifiedTypeVariants(
8010  QualType Ty) {
8011  // Insert this type.
8012  if (!MemberPointerTypes.insert(Ty))
8013  return false;
8014 
8015  const MemberPointerType *PointerTy = Ty->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
8016  assert(PointerTy && "type was not a member pointer type!");
8017 
8018  QualType PointeeTy = PointerTy->getPointeeType();
8019  // Don't add qualified variants of arrays. For one, they're not allowed
8020  // (the qualifier would sink to the element type), and for another, the
8021  // only overload situation where it matters is subscript or pointer +- int,
8022  // and those shouldn't have qualifier variants anyway.
8023  if (PointeeTy->isArrayType())
8024  return true;
8025  const Type *ClassTy = PointerTy->getClass();
8026 
8027  // Iterate through all strict supersets of the pointee type's CVR
8028  // qualifiers.
8029  unsigned BaseCVR = PointeeTy.getCVRQualifiers();
8030  for (unsigned CVR = BaseCVR+1; CVR <= Qualifiers::CVRMask; ++CVR) {
8031  if ((CVR | BaseCVR) != CVR) continue;
8032 
8033  QualType QPointeeTy = Context.getCVRQualifiedType(PointeeTy, CVR);
8034  MemberPointerTypes.insert(
8035  Context.getMemberPointerType(QPointeeTy, ClassTy));
8036  }
8037 
8038  return true;
8039 }
8040 
8041 /// AddTypesConvertedFrom - Add each of the types to which the type @p
8042 /// Ty can be implicit converted to the given set of @p Types. We're
8043 /// primarily interested in pointer types and enumeration types. We also
8044 /// take member pointer types, for the conditional operator.
8045 /// AllowUserConversions is true if we should look at the conversion
8046 /// functions of a class type, and AllowExplicitConversions if we
8047 /// should also include the explicit conversion functions of a class
8048 /// type.
8049 void
8050 BuiltinCandidateTypeSet::AddTypesConvertedFrom(QualType Ty,
8051  SourceLocation Loc,
8052  bool AllowUserConversions,
8053  bool AllowExplicitConversions,
8054  const Qualifiers &VisibleQuals) {
8055  // Only deal with canonical types.
8056  Ty = Context.getCanonicalType(Ty);
8057 
8058  // Look through reference types; they aren't part of the type of an
8059  // expression for the purposes of conversions.
8060  if (const ReferenceType *RefTy = Ty->getAs<ReferenceType>())
8061  Ty = RefTy->getPointeeType();
8062 
8063  // If we're dealing with an array type, decay to the pointer.
8064  if (Ty->isArrayType())
8065  Ty = SemaRef.Context.getArrayDecayedType(Ty);
8066 
8067  // Otherwise, we don't care about qualifiers on the type.
8068  Ty = Ty.getLocalUnqualifiedType();
8069 
8070  // Flag if we ever add a non-record type.
8071  const RecordType *TyRec = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
8072  HasNonRecordTypes = HasNonRecordTypes || !TyRec;
8073 
8074  // Flag if we encounter an arithmetic type.
8075  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes =
8076  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes || Ty->isArithmeticType();
8077 
8078  if (Ty->isObjCIdType() || Ty->isObjCClassType())
8079  PointerTypes.insert(Ty);
8080  else if (Ty->getAs<PointerType>() || Ty->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
8081  // Insert our type, and its more-qualified variants, into the set
8082  // of types.
8083  if (!AddPointerWithMoreQualifiedTypeVariants(Ty, VisibleQuals))
8084  return;
8085  } else if (Ty->isMemberPointerType()) {
8086  // Member pointers are far easier, since the pointee can't be converted.
8087  if (!AddMemberPointerWithMoreQualifiedTypeVariants(Ty))
8088  return;
8089  } else if (Ty->isEnumeralType()) {
8090  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes = true;
8091  EnumerationTypes.insert(Ty);
8092  } else if (Ty->isVectorType()) {
8093  // We treat vector types as arithmetic types in many contexts as an
8094  // extension.
8095  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes = true;
8096  VectorTypes.insert(Ty);
8097  } else if (Ty->isMatrixType()) {
8098  // Similar to vector types, we treat vector types as arithmetic types in
8099  // many contexts as an extension.
8100  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes = true;
8101  MatrixTypes.insert(Ty);
8102  } else if (Ty->isNullPtrType()) {
8103  HasNullPtrType = true;
8104  } else if (AllowUserConversions && TyRec) {
8105  // No conversion functions in incomplete types.
8106  if (!SemaRef.isCompleteType(Loc, Ty))
8107  return;
8108 
8109  CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(TyRec->getDecl());
8110  for (NamedDecl *D : ClassDecl->getVisibleConversionFunctions()) {
8111  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D))
8112  D = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(D)->getTargetDecl();
8113 
8114  // Skip conversion function templates; they don't tell us anything
8115  // about which builtin types we can convert to.
8116  if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D))
8117  continue;
8118 
8119  CXXConversionDecl *Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D);
8120  if (AllowExplicitConversions || !Conv->isExplicit()) {
8121  AddTypesConvertedFrom(Conv->getConversionType(), Loc, false, false,
8122  VisibleQuals);
8123  }
8124  }
8125  }
8126 }
8127 /// Helper function for adjusting address spaces for the pointer or reference
8128 /// operands of builtin operators depending on the argument.
8129 static QualType AdjustAddressSpaceForBuiltinOperandType(Sema &S, QualType T,
8130  Expr *Arg) {
8131  return S.Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(T, Arg->getType().getAddressSpace());
8132 }
8133 
8134 /// Helper function for AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates() that adds
8135 /// the volatile- and non-volatile-qualified assignment operators for the
8136 /// given type to the candidate set.
8137 static void AddBuiltinAssignmentOperatorCandidates(Sema &S,
8138  QualType T,
8139  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
8140  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet) {
8141  QualType ParamTypes[2];
8142 
8143  // T& operator=(T&, T)
8144  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(
8145  AdjustAddressSpaceForBuiltinOperandType(S, T, Args[0]));
8146  ParamTypes[1] = T;
8147  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8148  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/true);
8149 
8150  if (!S.Context.getCanonicalType(T).isVolatileQualified()) {
8151  // volatile T& operator=(volatile T&, T)
8152  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(
8153  AdjustAddressSpaceForBuiltinOperandType(S, S.Context.getVolatileType(T),
8154  Args[0]));
8155  ParamTypes[1] = T;
8156  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8157  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/true);
8158  }
8159 }
8160 
8161 /// CollectVRQualifiers - This routine returns Volatile/Restrict qualifiers,
8162 /// if any, found in visible type conversion functions found in ArgExpr's type.
8163 static Qualifiers CollectVRQualifiers(ASTContext &Context, Expr* ArgExpr) {
8164  Qualifiers VRQuals;
8165  const RecordType *TyRec;
8166  if (const MemberPointerType *RHSMPType =
8167  ArgExpr->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
8168  TyRec = RHSMPType->getClass()->getAs<RecordType>();
8169  else
8170  TyRec = ArgExpr->getType()->getAs<RecordType>();
8171  if (!TyRec) {
8172  // Just to be safe, assume the worst case.
8173  VRQuals.addVolatile();
8174  VRQuals.addRestrict();
8175  return VRQuals;
8176  }
8177 
8178  CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(TyRec->getDecl());
8179  if (!ClassDecl->hasDefinition())
8180  return VRQuals;
8181 
8182  for (NamedDecl *D : ClassDecl->getVisibleConversionFunctions()) {
8183  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D))
8184  D = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(D)->getTargetDecl();
8185  if (CXXConversionDecl *Conv = dyn_cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D)) {
8186  QualType CanTy = Context.getCanonicalType(Conv->getConversionType());
8187  if (const ReferenceType *ResTypeRef = CanTy->getAs<ReferenceType>())
8188  CanTy = ResTypeRef->getPointeeType();
8189  // Need to go down the pointer/mempointer chain and add qualifiers
8190  // as see them.
8191  bool done = false;
8192  while (!done) {
8193  if (CanTy.isRestrictQualified())
8194  VRQuals.addRestrict();
8195  if (const PointerType *ResTypePtr = CanTy->getAs<PointerType>())
8196  CanTy = ResTypePtr->getPointeeType();
8197  else if (const MemberPointerType *ResTypeMPtr =
8198  CanTy->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
8199  CanTy = ResTypeMPtr->getPointeeType();
8200  else
8201  done = true;
8202  if (CanTy.isVolatileQualified())
8203  VRQuals.addVolatile();
8204  if (VRQuals.hasRestrict() && VRQuals.hasVolatile())
8205  return VRQuals;
8206  }
8207  }
8208  }
8209  return VRQuals;
8210 }

8212 namespace {
8213 
8214 /// Helper class to manage the addition of builtin operator overload
8215 /// candidates. It provides shared state and utility methods used throughout
8216 /// the process, as well as a helper method to add each group of builtin
8217 /// operator overloads from the standard to a candidate set.
8218 class BuiltinOperatorOverloadBuilder {
8219  // Common instance state available to all overload candidate addition methods.
8220  Sema &S;
8221  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args;
8222  Qualifiers VisibleTypeConversionsQuals;
8223  bool HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType;
8224  SmallVectorImpl<BuiltinCandidateTypeSet> &CandidateTypes;
8225  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet;
8226 
8227  static constexpr int ArithmeticTypesCap = 24;
8228  SmallVector<CanQualType, ArithmeticTypesCap> ArithmeticTypes;
8229 
8230  // Define some indices used to iterate over the arithmetic types in
8231  // ArithmeticTypes. The "promoted arithmetic types" are the arithmetic
8232  // types are that preserved by promotion (C++ [over.built]p2).
8233  unsigned FirstIntegralType,
8234  LastIntegralType;
8235  unsigned FirstPromotedIntegralType,
8236  LastPromotedIntegralType;
8237  unsigned FirstPromotedArithmeticType,
8238  LastPromotedArithmeticType;
8239  unsigned NumArithmeticTypes;
8240 
8241  void InitArithmeticTypes() {
8242  // Start of promoted types.
8243  FirstPromotedArithmeticType = 0;
8244  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.FloatTy);
8245  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.DoubleTy);
8246  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.LongDoubleTy);
8247  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFloat128Type())
8248  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.Float128Ty);
8249  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasIbm128Type())
8250  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.Ibm128Ty);
8251 
8252  // Start of integral types.
8253  FirstIntegralType = ArithmeticTypes.size();
8254  FirstPromotedIntegralType = ArithmeticTypes.size();
8255  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.IntTy);
8256  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.LongTy);
8257  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.LongLongTy);
8258  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasInt128Type() ||
8259  (S.Context.getAuxTargetInfo() &&
8260  S.Context.getAuxTargetInfo()->hasInt128Type()))
8261  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.Int128Ty);
8262  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.UnsignedIntTy);
8263  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.UnsignedLongTy);
8264  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.UnsignedLongLongTy);
8265  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasInt128Type() ||
8266  (S.Context.getAuxTargetInfo() &&
8267  S.Context.getAuxTargetInfo()->hasInt128Type()))
8268  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.UnsignedInt128Ty);
8269  LastPromotedIntegralType = ArithmeticTypes.size();
8270  LastPromotedArithmeticType = ArithmeticTypes.size();
8271  // End of promoted types.
8272 
8273  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.BoolTy);
8274  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.CharTy);
8275  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.WCharTy);
8276  if (S.Context.getLangOpts().Char8)
8277  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.Char8Ty);
8278  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.Char16Ty);
8279  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.Char32Ty);
8280  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.SignedCharTy);
8281  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.ShortTy);
8282  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.UnsignedCharTy);
8283  ArithmeticTypes.push_back(S.Context.UnsignedShortTy);
8284  LastIntegralType = ArithmeticTypes.size();
8285  NumArithmeticTypes = ArithmeticTypes.size();
8286  // End of integral types.
8287  // FIXME: What about complex? What about half?
8288 
8289  assert(ArithmeticTypes.size() <= ArithmeticTypesCap &&
8290  "Enough inline storage for all arithmetic types.");
8291  }
8292 
8293  /// Helper method to factor out the common pattern of adding overloads
8294  /// for '++' and '--' builtin operators.
8295  void addPlusPlusMinusMinusStyleOverloads(QualType CandidateTy,
8296  bool HasVolatile,
8297  bool HasRestrict) {
8298  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {
8299  S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(CandidateTy),
8300  S.Context.IntTy
8301  };
8302 
8303  // Non-volatile version.
8304  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8305 
8306  // Use a heuristic to reduce number of builtin candidates in the set:
8307  // add volatile version only if there are conversions to a volatile type.
8308  if (HasVolatile) {
8309  ParamTypes[0] =
8310  S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(
8311  S.Context.getVolatileType(CandidateTy));
8312  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8313  }
8314 
8315  // Add restrict version only if there are conversions to a restrict type
8316  // and our candidate type is a non-restrict-qualified pointer.
8317  if (HasRestrict && CandidateTy->isAnyPointerType() &&
8318  !CandidateTy.isRestrictQualified()) {
8319  ParamTypes[0]
8320  = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(
8321  S.Context.getCVRQualifiedType(CandidateTy, Qualifiers::Restrict));
8322  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8323 
8324  if (HasVolatile) {
8325  ParamTypes[0]
8326  = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(
8327  S.Context.getCVRQualifiedType(CandidateTy,
8328  (Qualifiers::Volatile |
8329  Qualifiers::Restrict)));
8330  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8331  }
8332  }
8333 
8334  }
8335 
8336  /// Helper to add an overload candidate for a binary builtin with types \p L
8337  /// and \p R.
8338  void AddCandidate(QualType L, QualType R) {
8339  QualType LandR[2] = {L, R};
8340  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(LandR, Args, CandidateSet);
8341  }

8343 public:
8344  BuiltinOperatorOverloadBuilder(
8345  Sema &S, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
8346  Qualifiers VisibleTypeConversionsQuals,
8347  bool HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType,
8348  SmallVectorImpl<BuiltinCandidateTypeSet> &CandidateTypes,
8349  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet)
8350  : S(S), Args(Args),
8351  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals(VisibleTypeConversionsQuals),
8352  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType(
8353  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType),
8354  CandidateTypes(CandidateTypes),
8355  CandidateSet(CandidateSet) {
8356 
8357  InitArithmeticTypes();
8358  }
8359 
8360  // Increment is deprecated for bool since C++17.
8361  //
8362  // C++ [over.built]p3:
8363  //
8364  // For every pair (T, VQ), where T is an arithmetic type other
8365  // than bool, and VQ is either volatile or empty, there exist
8366  // candidate operator functions of the form
8367  //
8368  // VQ T& operator++(VQ T&);
8369  // T operator++(VQ T&, int);
8370  //
8371  // C++ [over.built]p4:
8372  //
8373  // For every pair (T, VQ), where T is an arithmetic type other
8374  // than bool, and VQ is either volatile or empty, there exist
8375  // candidate operator functions of the form
8376  //
8377  // VQ T& operator--(VQ T&);
8378  // T operator--(VQ T&, int);
8379  void addPlusPlusMinusMinusArithmeticOverloads(OverloadedOperatorKind Op) {
8380  if (!HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType)
8381  return;
8382 
8383  for (unsigned Arith = 0; Arith < NumArithmeticTypes; ++Arith) {
8384  const auto TypeOfT = ArithmeticTypes[Arith];
8385  if (TypeOfT == S.Context.BoolTy) {
8386  if (Op == OO_MinusMinus)
8387  continue;
8388  if (Op == OO_PlusPlus && S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17)
8389  continue;
8390  }
8391  addPlusPlusMinusMinusStyleOverloads(
8392  TypeOfT,
8393  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile(),
8394  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasRestrict());
8395  }
8396  }
8397 
8398  // C++ [over.built]p5:
8399  //
8400  // For every pair (T, VQ), where T is a cv-qualified or
8401  // cv-unqualified object type, and VQ is either volatile or
8402  // empty, there exist candidate operator functions of the form
8403  //
8404  // T*VQ& operator++(T*VQ&);
8405  // T*VQ& operator--(T*VQ&);
8406  // T* operator++(T*VQ&, int);
8407  // T* operator--(T*VQ&, int);
8408  void addPlusPlusMinusMinusPointerOverloads() {
8409  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[0].pointer_types()) {
8410  // Skip pointer types that aren't pointers to object types.
8411  if (!PtrTy->getPointeeType()->isObjectType())
8412  continue;
8413 
8414  addPlusPlusMinusMinusStyleOverloads(
8415  PtrTy,
8416  (!PtrTy.isVolatileQualified() &&
8417  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile()),
8418  (!PtrTy.isRestrictQualified() &&
8419  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasRestrict()));
8420  }
8421  }
8422 
8423  // C++ [over.built]p6:
8424  // For every cv-qualified or cv-unqualified object type T, there
8425  // exist candidate operator functions of the form
8426  //
8427  // T& operator*(T*);
8428  //
8429  // C++ [over.built]p7:
8430  // For every function type T that does not have cv-qualifiers or a
8431  // ref-qualifier, there exist candidate operator functions of the form
8432  // T& operator*(T*);
8433  void addUnaryStarPointerOverloads() {
8434  for (QualType ParamTy : CandidateTypes[0].pointer_types()) {
8435  QualType PointeeTy = ParamTy->getPointeeType();
8436  if (!PointeeTy->isObjectType() && !PointeeTy->isFunctionType())
8437  continue;
8438 
8439  if (const FunctionProtoType *Proto =PointeeTy->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
8440  if (Proto->getMethodQuals() || Proto->getRefQualifier())
8441  continue;
8442 
8443  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(&ParamTy, Args, CandidateSet);
8444  }
8445  }

8447  // C++ [over.built]p9:
8448  // For every promoted arithmetic type T, there exist candidate
8449  // operator functions of the form
8450  //
8451  // T operator+(T);
8452  // T operator-(T);
8453  void addUnaryPlusOrMinusArithmeticOverloads() {
8454  if (!HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType)
8455  return;
8456 
8457  for (unsigned Arith = FirstPromotedArithmeticType;
8458  Arith < LastPromotedArithmeticType; ++Arith) {
8459  QualType ArithTy = ArithmeticTypes[Arith];
8460  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(&ArithTy, Args, CandidateSet);
8461  }
8462 
8463  // Extension: We also add these operators for vector types.
8464  for (QualType VecTy : CandidateTypes[0].vector_types())
8465  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(&VecTy, Args, CandidateSet);
8466  }

8468  // C++ [over.built]p8:
8469  // For every type T, there exist candidate operator functions of
8470  // the form
8471  //
8472  // T* operator+(T*);
8473  void addUnaryPlusPointerOverloads() {
8474  for (QualType ParamTy : CandidateTypes[0].pointer_types())
8475  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(&ParamTy, Args, CandidateSet);
8476  }

8478  // C++ [over.built]p10:
8479  // For every promoted integral type T, there exist candidate
8480  // operator functions of the form
8481  //
8482  // T operator~(T);
8483  void addUnaryTildePromotedIntegralOverloads() {
8484  if (!HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType)
8485  return;
8486 
8487  for (unsigned Int = FirstPromotedIntegralType;
8488  Int < LastPromotedIntegralType; ++Int) {
8489  QualType IntTy = ArithmeticTypes[Int];
8490  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(&IntTy, Args, CandidateSet);
8491  }
8492 
8493  // Extension: We also add this operator for vector types.
8494  for (QualType VecTy : CandidateTypes[0].vector_types())
8495  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(&VecTy, Args, CandidateSet);
8496  }

8498  // C++ [over.match.oper]p16:
8499  // For every pointer to member type T or type std::nullptr_t, there
8500  // exist candidate operator functions of the form
8501  //
8502  // bool operator==(T,T);
8503  // bool operator!=(T,T);
8504  void addEqualEqualOrNotEqualMemberPointerOrNullptrOverloads() {
8505  /// Set of (canonical) types that we've already handled.
8506  llvm::SmallPtrSet<QualType, 8> AddedTypes;
8507 
8508  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0, N = Args.size(); ArgIdx != N; ++ArgIdx) {
8509  for (QualType MemPtrTy : CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].member_pointer_types()) {
8510  // Don't add the same builtin candidate twice.
8511  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(MemPtrTy)).second)
8512  continue;
8513 
8514  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {MemPtrTy, MemPtrTy};
8515  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8516  }
8517 
8518  if (CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].hasNullPtrType()) {
8519  CanQualType NullPtrTy = S.Context.getCanonicalType(S.Context.NullPtrTy);
8520  if (AddedTypes.insert(NullPtrTy).second) {
8521  QualType ParamTypes[2] = { NullPtrTy, NullPtrTy };
8522  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8523  }
8524  }
8525  }
8526  }
8527 
8528  // C++ [over.built]p15:
8529  //
8530  // For every T, where T is an enumeration type or a pointer type,
8531  // there exist candidate operator functions of the form
8532  //
8533  // bool operator<(T, T);
8534  // bool operator>(T, T);
8535  // bool operator<=(T, T);
8536  // bool operator>=(T, T);
8537  // bool operator==(T, T);
8538  // bool operator!=(T, T);
8539  // R operator<=>(T, T)
8540  void addGenericBinaryPointerOrEnumeralOverloads(bool IsSpaceship) {
8541  // C++ [over.match.oper]p3:
8542  // [...]the built-in candidates include all of the candidate operator
8543  // functions defined in 13.6 that, compared to the given operator, [...]
8544  // do not have the same parameter-type-list as any non-template non-member
8545  // candidate.
8546  //
8547  // Note that in practice, this only affects enumeration types because there
8548  // aren't any built-in candidates of record type, and a user-defined operator
8549  // must have an operand of record or enumeration type. Also, the only other
8550  // overloaded operator with enumeration arguments, operator=,
8551  // cannot be overloaded for enumeration types, so this is the only place
8552  // where we must suppress candidates like this.
8553  llvm::DenseSet<std::pair<CanQualType, CanQualType> >
8554  UserDefinedBinaryOperators;
8555 
8556  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0, N = Args.size(); ArgIdx != N; ++ArgIdx) {
8557  if (!CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].enumeration_types().empty()) {
8558  for (OverloadCandidateSet::iterator C = CandidateSet.begin(),
8559  CEnd = CandidateSet.end();
8560  C != CEnd; ++C) {
8561  if (!C->Viable || !C->Function || C->Function->getNumParams() != 2)
8562  continue;
8563 
8564  if (C->Function->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization())
8565  continue;
8566 
8567  // We interpret "same parameter-type-list" as applying to the
8568  // "synthesized candidate, with the order of the two parameters
8569  // reversed", not to the original function.
8570  bool Reversed = C->isReversed();
8571  QualType FirstParamType = C->Function->getParamDecl(Reversed ? 1 : 0)
8572  ->getType()
8573  .getUnqualifiedType();
8574  QualType SecondParamType = C->Function->getParamDecl(Reversed ? 0 : 1)
8575  ->getType()
8576  .getUnqualifiedType();
8577 
8578  // Skip if either parameter isn't of enumeral type.
8579  if (!FirstParamType->isEnumeralType() ||
8580  !SecondParamType->isEnumeralType())
8581  continue;
8582 
8583  // Add this operator to the set of known user-defined operators.
8584  UserDefinedBinaryOperators.insert(
8585  std::make_pair(S.Context.getCanonicalType(FirstParamType),
8586  S.Context.getCanonicalType(SecondParamType)));
8587  }
8588  }
8589  }
8590 
8591  /// Set of (canonical) types that we've already handled.
8592  llvm::SmallPtrSet<QualType, 8> AddedTypes;
8593 
8594  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0, N = Args.size(); ArgIdx != N; ++ArgIdx) {
8595  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].pointer_types()) {
8596  // Don't add the same builtin candidate twice.
8597  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(PtrTy)).second)
8598  continue;
8599  if (IsSpaceship && PtrTy->isFunctionPointerType())
8600  continue;
8601 
8602  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {PtrTy, PtrTy};
8603  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8604  }
8605  for (QualType EnumTy : CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].enumeration_types()) {
8606  CanQualType CanonType = S.Context.getCanonicalType(EnumTy);
8607 
8608  // Don't add the same builtin candidate twice, or if a user defined
8609  // candidate exists.
8610  if (!AddedTypes.insert(CanonType).second ||
8611  UserDefinedBinaryOperators.count(std::make_pair(CanonType,
8612  CanonType)))
8613  continue;
8614  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {EnumTy, EnumTy};
8615  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8616  }
8617  }
8618  }
8619 
8620  // C++ [over.built]p13:
8621  //
8622  // For every cv-qualified or cv-unqualified object type T
8623  // there exist candidate operator functions of the form
8624  //
8625  // T* operator+(T*, ptrdiff_t);
8626  // T& operator[](T*, ptrdiff_t); [BELOW]
8627  // T* operator-(T*, ptrdiff_t);
8628  // T* operator+(ptrdiff_t, T*);
8629  // T& operator[](ptrdiff_t, T*); [BELOW]
8630  //
8631  // C++ [over.built]p14:
8632  //
8633  // For every T, where T is a pointer to object type, there
8634  // exist candidate operator functions of the form
8635  //
8636  // ptrdiff_t operator-(T, T);
8637  void addBinaryPlusOrMinusPointerOverloads(OverloadedOperatorKind Op) {
8638  /// Set of (canonical) types that we've already handled.
8639  llvm::SmallPtrSet<QualType, 8> AddedTypes;
8640 
8641  for (int Arg = 0; Arg < 2; ++Arg) {
8642  QualType AsymmetricParamTypes[2] = {
8643  S.Context.getPointerDiffType(),
8644  S.Context.getPointerDiffType(),
8645  };
8646  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[Arg].pointer_types()) {
8647  QualType PointeeTy = PtrTy->getPointeeType();
8648  if (!PointeeTy->isObjectType())
8649  continue;
8650 
8651  AsymmetricParamTypes[Arg] = PtrTy;
8652  if (Arg == 0 || Op == OO_Plus) {
8653  // operator+(T*, ptrdiff_t) or operator-(T*, ptrdiff_t)
8654  // T* operator+(ptrdiff_t, T*);
8655  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(AsymmetricParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8656  }
8657  if (Op == OO_Minus) {
8658  // ptrdiff_t operator-(T, T);
8659  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(PtrTy)).second)
8660  continue;
8661 
8662  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {PtrTy, PtrTy};
8663  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
8664  }
8665  }
8666  }
8667  }
8668 
8669  // C++ [over.built]p12:
8670  //
8671  // For every pair of promoted arithmetic types L and R, there
8672  // exist candidate operator functions of the form
8673  //
8674  // LR operator*(L, R);
8675  // LR operator/(L, R);
8676  // LR operator+(L, R);
8677  // LR operator-(L, R);
8678  // bool operator<(L, R);
8679  // bool operator>(L, R);
8680  // bool operator<=(L, R);
8681  // bool operator>=(L, R);
8682  // bool operator==(L, R);
8683  // bool operator!=(L, R);
8684  //
8685  // where LR is the result of the usual arithmetic conversions
8686  // between types L and R.
8687  //
8688  // C++ [over.built]p24:
8689  //
8690  // For every pair of promoted arithmetic types L and R, there exist
8691  // candidate operator functions of the form
8692  //
8693  // LR operator?(bool, L, R);
8694  //
8695  // where LR is the result of the usual arithmetic conversions
8696  // between types L and R.
8697  // Our candidates ignore the first parameter.
8698  void addGenericBinaryArithmeticOverloads() {
8699  if (!HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType)
8700  return;
8701 
8702  for (unsigned Left = FirstPromotedArithmeticType;
8703  Left < LastPromotedArithmeticType; ++Left) {
8704  for (unsigned Right = FirstPromotedArithmeticType;
8705  Right < LastPromotedArithmeticType; ++Right) {
8706  QualType LandR[2] = { ArithmeticTypes[Left],
8707  ArithmeticTypes[Right] };
8708  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(LandR, Args, CandidateSet);
8709  }
8710  }
8711 
8712  // Extension: Add the binary operators ==, !=, <, <=, >=, >, *, /, and the
8713  // conditional operator for vector types.
8714  for (QualType Vec1Ty : CandidateTypes[0].vector_types())
8715  for (QualType Vec2Ty : CandidateTypes[1].vector_types()) {
8716  QualType LandR[2] = {Vec1Ty, Vec2Ty};
8717  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(LandR, Args, CandidateSet);
8718  }
8719  }
8720 
8721  /// Add binary operator overloads for each candidate matrix type M1, M2:
8722  /// * (M1, M1) -> M1
8723  /// * (M1, M1.getElementType()) -> M1
8724  /// * (M2.getElementType(), M2) -> M2
8725  /// * (M2, M2) -> M2 // Only if M2 is not part of CandidateTypes[0].
8726  void addMatrixBinaryArithmeticOverloads() {
8727  if (!HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType)
8728  return;
8729 
8730  for (QualType M1 : CandidateTypes[0].matrix_types()) {
8731  AddCandidate(M1, cast<MatrixType>(M1)->getElementType());
8732  AddCandidate(M1, M1);
8733  }
8734 
8735  for (QualType M2 : CandidateTypes[1].matrix_types()) {
8736  AddCandidate(cast<MatrixType>(M2)->getElementType(), M2);
8737  if (!CandidateTypes[0].containsMatrixType(M2))
8738  AddCandidate(M2, M2);
8739  }
8740  }
8741 
8742  // C++2a [over.built]p14:
8743  //
8744  // For every integral type T there exists a candidate operator function
8745  // of the form
8746  //
8747  // std::strong_ordering operator<=>(T, T)
8748  //
8749  // C++2a [over.built]p15:
8750  //
8751  // For every pair of floating-point types L and R, there exists a candidate
8752  // operator function of the form
8753  //
8754  // std::partial_ordering operator<=>(L, R);
8755  //
8756  // FIXME: The current specification for integral types doesn't play nice with
8757  // the direction of p0946r0, which allows mixed integral and unscoped-enum
8758  // comparisons. Under the current spec this can lead to ambiguity during
8759  // overload resolution. For example:
8760  //
8761  // enum A : int {a};
8762  // auto x = (a <=> (long)42);
8763  //
8764  // error: call is ambiguous for arguments 'A' and 'long'.
8765  // note: candidate operator<=>(int, int)
8766  // note: candidate operator<=>(long, long)
8767  //
8768  // To avoid this error, this function deviates from the specification and adds
8769  // the mixed overloads `operator<=>(L, R)` where L and R are promoted
8770  // arithmetic types (the same as the generic relational overloads).
8771  //
8772  // For now this function acts as a placeholder.
8773  void addThreeWayArithmeticOverloads() {
8774  addGenericBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
8775  }
8776 
8777  // C++ [over.built]p17:
8778  //
8779  // For every pair of promoted integral types L and R, there
8780  // exist candidate operator functions of the form
8781  //
8782  // LR operator%(L, R);
8783  // LR operator&(L, R);
8784  // LR operator^(L, R);
8785  // LR operator|(L, R);
8786  // L operator<<(L, R);
8787  // L operator>>(L, R);
8788  //
8789  // where LR is the result of the usual arithmetic conversions
8790  // between types L and R.
8791  void addBinaryBitwiseArithmeticOverloads() {
8792  if (!HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType)
8793  return;
8794 
8795  for (unsigned Left = FirstPromotedIntegralType;
8796  Left < LastPromotedIntegralType; ++Left) {
8797  for (unsigned Right = FirstPromotedIntegralType;
8798  Right < LastPromotedIntegralType; ++Right) {
8799  QualType LandR[2] = { ArithmeticTypes[Left],
8800  ArithmeticTypes[Right] };
8801  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(LandR, Args, CandidateSet);
8802  }
8803  }
8804  }
8805 
8806  // C++ [over.built]p20:
8807  //
8808  // For every pair (T, VQ), where T is an enumeration or
8809  // pointer to member type and VQ is either volatile or
8810  // empty, there exist candidate operator functions of the form
8811  //
8812  // VQ T& operator=(VQ T&, T);
8813  void addAssignmentMemberPointerOrEnumeralOverloads() {
8814  /// Set of (canonical) types that we've already handled.
8815  llvm::SmallPtrSet<QualType, 8> AddedTypes;
8816 
8817  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx < 2; ++ArgIdx) {
8818  for (QualType EnumTy : CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].enumeration_types()) {
8819  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(EnumTy)).second)
8820  continue;
8821 
8822  AddBuiltinAssignmentOperatorCandidates(S, EnumTy, Args, CandidateSet);
8823  }
8824 
8825  for (QualType MemPtrTy : CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].member_pointer_types()) {
8826  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(MemPtrTy)).second)
8827  continue;
8828 
8829  AddBuiltinAssignmentOperatorCandidates(S, MemPtrTy, Args, CandidateSet);
8830  }
8831  }
8832  }
8833 
8834  // C++ [over.built]p19:
8835  //
8836  // For every pair (T, VQ), where T is any type and VQ is either
8837  // volatile or empty, there exist candidate operator functions
8838  // of the form
8839  //
8840  // T*VQ& operator=(T*VQ&, T*);
8841  //
8842  // C++ [over.built]p21:
8843  //
8844  // For every pair (T, VQ), where T is a cv-qualified or
8845  // cv-unqualified object type and VQ is either volatile or
8846  // empty, there exist candidate operator functions of the form
8847  //
8848  // T*VQ& operator+=(T*VQ&, ptrdiff_t);
8849  // T*VQ& operator-=(T*VQ&, ptrdiff_t);
8850  void addAssignmentPointerOverloads(bool isEqualOp) {
8851  /// Set of (canonical) types that we've already handled.
8852  llvm::SmallPtrSet<QualType, 8> AddedTypes;
8853 
8854  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[0].pointer_types()) {
8855  // If this is operator=, keep track of the builtin candidates we added.
8856  if (isEqualOp)
8857  AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(PtrTy));
8858  else if (!PtrTy->getPointeeType()->isObjectType())
8859  continue;
8860 
8861  // non-volatile version
8862  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {
8863  S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(PtrTy),
8864  isEqualOp ? PtrTy : S.Context.getPointerDiffType(),
8865  };
8866  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8867  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/ isEqualOp);
8868 
8869  bool NeedVolatile = !PtrTy.isVolatileQualified() &&
8870  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile();
8871  if (NeedVolatile) {
8872  // volatile version
8873  ParamTypes[0] =
8874  S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(S.Context.getVolatileType(PtrTy));
8875  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8876  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/isEqualOp);
8877  }
8878 
8879  if (!PtrTy.isRestrictQualified() &&
8880  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasRestrict()) {
8881  // restrict version
8882  ParamTypes[0] =
8883  S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(S.Context.getRestrictType(PtrTy));
8884  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8885  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/isEqualOp);
8886 
8887  if (NeedVolatile) {
8888  // volatile restrict version
8889  ParamTypes[0] =
8890  S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(S.Context.getCVRQualifiedType(
8891  PtrTy, (Qualifiers::Volatile | Qualifiers::Restrict)));
8892  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8893  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/isEqualOp);
8894  }
8895  }
8896  }
8897 
8898  if (isEqualOp) {
8899  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[1].pointer_types()) {
8900  // Make sure we don't add the same candidate twice.
8901  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(PtrTy)).second)
8902  continue;
8903 
8904  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {
8905  S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(PtrTy),
8906  PtrTy,
8907  };
8908 
8909  // non-volatile version
8910  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8911  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/true);
8912 
8913  bool NeedVolatile = !PtrTy.isVolatileQualified() &&
8914  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile();
8915  if (NeedVolatile) {
8916  // volatile version
8917  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(
8918  S.Context.getVolatileType(PtrTy));
8919  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8920  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/true);
8921  }
8922 
8923  if (!PtrTy.isRestrictQualified() &&
8924  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasRestrict()) {
8925  // restrict version
8926  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(
8927  S.Context.getRestrictType(PtrTy));
8928  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8929  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/true);
8930 
8931  if (NeedVolatile) {
8932  // volatile restrict version
8933  ParamTypes[0] =
8934  S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(S.Context.getCVRQualifiedType(
8935  PtrTy, (Qualifiers::Volatile | Qualifiers::Restrict)));
8936  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8937  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/true);
8938  }
8939  }
8940  }
8941  }
8942  }
8943 
8944  // C++ [over.built]p18:
8945  //
8946  // For every triple (L, VQ, R), where L is an arithmetic type,
8947  // VQ is either volatile or empty, and R is a promoted
8948  // arithmetic type, there exist candidate operator functions of
8949  // the form
8950  //
8951  // VQ L& operator=(VQ L&, R);
8952  // VQ L& operator*=(VQ L&, R);
8953  // VQ L& operator/=(VQ L&, R);
8954  // VQ L& operator+=(VQ L&, R);
8955  // VQ L& operator-=(VQ L&, R);
8956  void addAssignmentArithmeticOverloads(bool isEqualOp) {
8957  if (!HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType)
8958  return;
8959 
8960  for (unsigned Left = 0; Left < NumArithmeticTypes; ++Left) {
8961  for (unsigned Right = FirstPromotedArithmeticType;
8962  Right < LastPromotedArithmeticType; ++Right) {
8963  QualType ParamTypes[2];
8964  ParamTypes[1] = ArithmeticTypes[Right];
8965  auto LeftBaseTy = AdjustAddressSpaceForBuiltinOperandType(
8966  S, ArithmeticTypes[Left], Args[0]);
8967  // Add this built-in operator as a candidate (VQ is empty).
8968  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(LeftBaseTy);
8969  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8970  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/isEqualOp);
8971 
8972  // Add this built-in operator as a candidate (VQ is 'volatile').
8973  if (VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile()) {
8974  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getVolatileType(LeftBaseTy);
8975  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(ParamTypes[0]);
8976  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8977  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/isEqualOp);
8978  }
8979  }
8980  }
8981 
8982  // Extension: Add the binary operators =, +=, -=, *=, /= for vector types.
8983  for (QualType Vec1Ty : CandidateTypes[0].vector_types())
8984  for (QualType Vec2Ty : CandidateTypes[0].vector_types()) {
8985  QualType ParamTypes[2];
8986  ParamTypes[1] = Vec2Ty;
8987  // Add this built-in operator as a candidate (VQ is empty).
8988  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(Vec1Ty);
8989  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8990  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/isEqualOp);
8991 
8992  // Add this built-in operator as a candidate (VQ is 'volatile').
8993  if (VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile()) {
8994  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getVolatileType(Vec1Ty);
8995  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(ParamTypes[0]);
8996  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
8997  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/isEqualOp);
8998  }
8999  }
9000  }
9001 
9002  // C++ [over.built]p22:
9003  //
9004  // For every triple (L, VQ, R), where L is an integral type, VQ
9005  // is either volatile or empty, and R is a promoted integral
9006  // type, there exist candidate operator functions of the form
9007  //
9008  // VQ L& operator%=(VQ L&, R);
9009  // VQ L& operator<<=(VQ L&, R);
9010  // VQ L& operator>>=(VQ L&, R);
9011  // VQ L& operator&=(VQ L&, R);
9012  // VQ L& operator^=(VQ L&, R);
9013  // VQ L& operator|=(VQ L&, R);
9014  void addAssignmentIntegralOverloads() {
9015  if (!HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType)
9016  return;
9017 
9018  for (unsigned Left = FirstIntegralType; Left < LastIntegralType; ++Left) {
9019  for (unsigned Right = FirstPromotedIntegralType;
9020  Right < LastPromotedIntegralType; ++Right) {
9021  QualType ParamTypes[2];
9022  ParamTypes[1] = ArithmeticTypes[Right];
9023  auto LeftBaseTy = AdjustAddressSpaceForBuiltinOperandType(
9024  S, ArithmeticTypes[Left], Args[0]);
9025  // Add this built-in operator as a candidate (VQ is empty).
9026  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(LeftBaseTy);
9027  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
9028  if (VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile()) {
9029  // Add this built-in operator as a candidate (VQ is 'volatile').
9030  ParamTypes[0] = LeftBaseTy;
9031  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getVolatileType(ParamTypes[0]);
9032  ParamTypes[0] = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(ParamTypes[0]);
9033  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
9034  }
9035  }
9036  }
9037  }
9038 
9039  // C++ [over.operator]p23:
9040  //
9041  // There also exist candidate operator functions of the form
9042  //
9043  // bool operator!(bool);
9044  // bool operator&&(bool, bool);
9045  // bool operator||(bool, bool);
9046  void addExclaimOverload() {
9047  QualType ParamTy = S.Context.BoolTy;
9048  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(&ParamTy, Args, CandidateSet,
9049  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/false,
9050  /*NumContextualBoolArguments=*/1);
9051  }
9052  void addAmpAmpOrPipePipeOverload() {
9053  QualType ParamTypes[2] = { S.Context.BoolTy, S.Context.BoolTy };
9054  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet,
9055  /*IsAssignmentOperator=*/false,
9056  /*NumContextualBoolArguments=*/2);
9057  }
9058 
9059  // C++ [over.built]p13:
9060  //
9061  // For every cv-qualified or cv-unqualified object type T there
9062  // exist candidate operator functions of the form
9063  //
9064  // T* operator+(T*, ptrdiff_t); [ABOVE]
9065  // T& operator[](T*, ptrdiff_t);
9066  // T* operator-(T*, ptrdiff_t); [ABOVE]
9067  // T* operator+(ptrdiff_t, T*); [ABOVE]
9068  // T& operator[](ptrdiff_t, T*);
9069  void addSubscriptOverloads() {
9070  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[0].pointer_types()) {
9071  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {PtrTy, S.Context.getPointerDiffType()};
9072  QualType PointeeType = PtrTy->getPointeeType();
9073  if (!PointeeType->isObjectType())
9074  continue;
9075 
9076  // T& operator[](T*, ptrdiff_t)
9077  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
9078  }
9079 
9080  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[1].pointer_types()) {
9081  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {S.Context.getPointerDiffType(), PtrTy};
9082  QualType PointeeType = PtrTy->getPointeeType();
9083  if (!PointeeType->isObjectType())
9084  continue;
9085 
9086  // T& operator[](ptrdiff_t, T*)
9087  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
9088  }
9089  }
9090 
9091  // C++ [over.built]p11:
9092  // For every quintuple (C1, C2, T, CV1, CV2), where C2 is a class type,
9093  // C1 is the same type as C2 or is a derived class of C2, T is an object
9094  // type or a function type, and CV1 and CV2 are cv-qualifier-seqs,
9095  // there exist candidate operator functions of the form
9096  //
9097  // CV12 T& operator->*(CV1 C1*, CV2 T C2::*);
9098  //
9099  // where CV12 is the union of CV1 and CV2.
9100  void addArrowStarOverloads() {
9101  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[0].pointer_types()) {
9102  QualType C1Ty = PtrTy;
9103  QualType C1;
9104  QualifierCollector Q1;
9105  C1 = QualType(Q1.strip(C1Ty->getPointeeType()), 0);
9106  if (!isa<RecordType>(C1))
9107  continue;
9108  // heuristic to reduce number of builtin candidates in the set.
9109  // Add volatile/restrict version only if there are conversions to a
9110  // volatile/restrict type.
9111  if (!VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile() && Q1.hasVolatile())
9112  continue;
9113  if (!VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasRestrict() && Q1.hasRestrict())
9114  continue;
9115  for (QualType MemPtrTy : CandidateTypes[1].member_pointer_types()) {
9116  const MemberPointerType *mptr = cast<MemberPointerType>(MemPtrTy);
9117  QualType C2 = QualType(mptr->getClass(), 0);
9118  C2 = C2.getUnqualifiedType();
9119  if (C1 != C2 && !S.IsDerivedFrom(CandidateSet.getLocation(), C1, C2))
9120  break;
9121  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {PtrTy, MemPtrTy};
9122  // build CV12 T&
9123  QualType T = mptr->getPointeeType();
9124  if (!VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasVolatile() &&
9125  T.isVolatileQualified())
9126  continue;
9127  if (!VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.hasRestrict() &&
9128  T.isRestrictQualified())
9129  continue;
9130  T = Q1.apply(S.Context, T);
9131  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
9132  }
9133  }
9134  }
9135 
9136  // Note that we don't consider the first argument, since it has been
9137  // contextually converted to bool long ago. The candidates below are
9138  // therefore added as binary.
9139  //
9140  // C++ [over.built]p25:
9141  // For every type T, where T is a pointer, pointer-to-member, or scoped
9142  // enumeration type, there exist candidate operator functions of the form
9143  //
9144  // T operator?(bool, T, T);
9145  //
9146  void addConditionalOperatorOverloads() {
9147  /// Set of (canonical) types that we've already handled.
9148  llvm::SmallPtrSet<QualType, 8> AddedTypes;
9149 
9150  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx < 2; ++ArgIdx) {
9151  for (QualType PtrTy : CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].pointer_types()) {
9152  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(PtrTy)).second)
9153  continue;
9154 
9155  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {PtrTy, PtrTy};
9156  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
9157  }
9158 
9159  for (QualType MemPtrTy : CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].member_pointer_types()) {
9160  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(MemPtrTy)).second)
9161  continue;
9162 
9163  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {MemPtrTy, MemPtrTy};
9164  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
9165  }
9166 
9167  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
9168  for (QualType EnumTy : CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].enumeration_types()) {
9169  if (!EnumTy->castAs<EnumType>()->getDecl()->isScoped())
9170  continue;
9171 
9172  if (!AddedTypes.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(EnumTy)).second)
9173  continue;
9174 
9175  QualType ParamTypes[2] = {EnumTy, EnumTy};
9176  S.AddBuiltinCandidate(ParamTypes, Args, CandidateSet);
9177  }
9178  }
9179  }
9180  }
9181 };
9182 
9183 } // end anonymous namespace
9184 
9185 /// AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates - Add the appropriate built-in
9186 /// operator overloads to the candidate set (C++ [over.built]), based
9187 /// on the operator @p Op and the arguments given. For example, if the
9188 /// operator is a binary '+', this routine might add "int
9189 /// operator+(int, int)" to cover integer addition.
9190 void Sema::AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates(OverloadedOperatorKind Op,
9191  SourceLocation OpLoc,
9192  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
9193  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet) {
9194  // Find all of the types that the arguments can convert to, but only
9195  // if the operator we're looking at has built-in operator candidates
9196  // that make use of these types. Also record whether we encounter non-record
9197  // candidate types or either arithmetic or enumeral candidate types.
9198  Qualifiers VisibleTypeConversionsQuals;
9199  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals.addConst();
9200  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0, N = Args.size(); ArgIdx != N; ++ArgIdx)
9201  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals += CollectVRQualifiers(Context, Args[ArgIdx]);
9202 
9203  bool HasNonRecordCandidateType = false;
9204  bool HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType = false;
9205  SmallVector<BuiltinCandidateTypeSet, 2> CandidateTypes;
9206  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0, N = Args.size(); ArgIdx != N; ++ArgIdx) {
9207  CandidateTypes.emplace_back(*this);
9208  CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].AddTypesConvertedFrom(Args[ArgIdx]->getType(),
9209  OpLoc,
9210  true,
9211  (Op == OO_Exclaim ||
9212  Op == OO_AmpAmp ||
9213  Op == OO_PipePipe),
9214  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals);
9215  HasNonRecordCandidateType = HasNonRecordCandidateType ||
9216  CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].hasNonRecordTypes();
9217  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType =
9218  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType ||
9219  CandidateTypes[ArgIdx].hasArithmeticOrEnumeralTypes();
9220  }
9221 
9222  // Exit early when no non-record types have been added to the candidate set
9223  // for any of the arguments to the operator.
9224  //
9225  // We can't exit early for !, ||, or &&, since there we have always have
9226  // 'bool' overloads.
9227  if (!HasNonRecordCandidateType &&
9228  !(Op == OO_Exclaim || Op == OO_AmpAmp || Op == OO_PipePipe))
9229  return;
9230 
9231  // Setup an object to manage the common state for building overloads.
9232  BuiltinOperatorOverloadBuilder OpBuilder(*this, Args,
9233  VisibleTypeConversionsQuals,
9234  HasArithmeticOrEnumeralCandidateType,
9235  CandidateTypes, CandidateSet);
9236 
9237  // Dispatch over the operation to add in only those overloads which apply.
9238  switch (Op) {
9239  case OO_None:
9240  case NUM_OVERLOADED_OPERATORS:
9241  llvm_unreachable("Expected an overloaded operator");
9242 
9243  case OO_New:
9244  case OO_Delete:
9245  case OO_Array_New:
9246  case OO_Array_Delete:
9247  case OO_Call:
9248  llvm_unreachable(
9249  "Special operators don't use AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates");
9250 
9251  case OO_Comma:
9252  case OO_Arrow:
9253  case OO_Coawait:
9254  // C++ [over.match.oper]p3:
9255  // -- For the operator ',', the unary operator '&', the
9256  // operator '->', or the operator 'co_await', the
9257  // built-in candidates set is empty.
9258  break;
9259 
9260  case OO_Plus: // '+' is either unary or binary
9261  if (Args.size() == 1)
9262  OpBuilder.addUnaryPlusPointerOverloads();
9263  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
9264 
9265  case OO_Minus: // '-' is either unary or binary
9266  if (Args.size() == 1) {
9267  OpBuilder.addUnaryPlusOrMinusArithmeticOverloads();
9268  } else {
9269  OpBuilder.addBinaryPlusOrMinusPointerOverloads(Op);
9270  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
9271  OpBuilder.addMatrixBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
9272  }
9273  break;
9274 
9275  case OO_Star: // '*' is either unary or binary
9276  if (Args.size() == 1)
9277  OpBuilder.addUnaryStarPointerOverloads();
9278  else {
9279  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
9280  OpBuilder.addMatrixBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
9281  }
9282  break;
9283 
9284  case OO_Slash:
9285  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
9286  break;
9287 
9288  case OO_PlusPlus:
9289  case OO_MinusMinus:
9290  OpBuilder.addPlusPlusMinusMinusArithmeticOverloads(Op);
9291  OpBuilder.addPlusPlusMinusMinusPointerOverloads();
9292  break;
9293 
9294  case OO_EqualEqual:
9295  case OO_ExclaimEqual:
9296  OpBuilder.addEqualEqualOrNotEqualMemberPointerOrNullptrOverloads();
9297  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryPointerOrEnumeralOverloads(/*IsSpaceship=*/false);
9298  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
9299  break;
9300 
9301  case OO_Less:
9302  case OO_Greater:
9303  case OO_LessEqual:
9304  case OO_GreaterEqual:
9305  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryPointerOrEnumeralOverloads(/*IsSpaceship=*/false);
9306  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
9307  break;
9308 
9309  case OO_Spaceship:
9310  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryPointerOrEnumeralOverloads(/*IsSpaceship=*/true);
9311  OpBuilder.addThreeWayArithmeticOverloads();
9312  break;
9313 
9314  case OO_Percent:
9315  case OO_Caret:
9316  case OO_Pipe:
9317  case OO_LessLess:
9318  case OO_GreaterGreater:
9319  OpBuilder.addBinaryBitwiseArithmeticOverloads();
9320  break;
9321 
9322  case OO_Amp: // '&' is either unary or binary
9323  if (Args.size() == 1)
9324  // C++ [over.match.oper]p3:
9325  // -- For the operator ',', the unary operator '&', or the
9326  // operator '->', the built-in candidates set is empty.
9327  break;
9328 
9329  OpBuilder.addBinaryBitwiseArithmeticOverloads();
9330  break;
9331 
9332  case OO_Tilde:
9333  OpBuilder.addUnaryTildePromotedIntegralOverloads();
9334  break;
9335 
9336  case OO_Equal:
9337  OpBuilder.addAssignmentMemberPointerOrEnumeralOverloads();
9338  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
9339 
9340  case OO_PlusEqual:
9341  case OO_MinusEqual:
9342  OpBuilder.addAssignmentPointerOverloads(Op == OO_Equal);
9343  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
9344 
9345  case OO_StarEqual:
9346  case OO_SlashEqual:
9347  OpBuilder.addAssignmentArithmeticOverloads(Op == OO_Equal);
9348  break;
9349 
9350  case OO_PercentEqual:
9351  case OO_LessLessEqual:
9352  case OO_GreaterGreaterEqual:
9353  case OO_AmpEqual:
9354  case OO_CaretEqual:
9355  case OO_PipeEqual:
9356  OpBuilder.addAssignmentIntegralOverloads();
9357  break;
9358 
9359  case OO_Exclaim:
9360  OpBuilder.addExclaimOverload();
9361  break;
9362 
9363  case OO_AmpAmp:
9364  case OO_PipePipe:
9365  OpBuilder.addAmpAmpOrPipePipeOverload();
9366  break;
9367 
9368  case OO_Subscript:
9369  if (Args.size() == 2)
9370  OpBuilder.addSubscriptOverloads();
9371  break;
9372 
9373  case OO_ArrowStar:
9374  OpBuilder.addArrowStarOverloads();
9375  break;
9376 
9377  case OO_Conditional:
9378  OpBuilder.addConditionalOperatorOverloads();
9379  OpBuilder.addGenericBinaryArithmeticOverloads();
9380  break;
9381  }
9382 }
9383 
9384 /// Add function candidates found via argument-dependent lookup
9385 /// to the set of overloading candidates.
9386 ///
9387 /// This routine performs argument-dependent name lookup based on the
9388 /// given function name (which may also be an operator name) and adds
9389 /// all of the overload candidates found by ADL to the overload
9390 /// candidate set (C++ [basic.lookup.argdep]).
9391 void
9392 Sema::AddArgumentDependentLookupCandidates(DeclarationName Name,
9393  SourceLocation Loc,
9394  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
9395  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs,
9396  OverloadCandidateSet& CandidateSet,
9397  bool PartialOverloading) {
9398  ADLResult Fns;
9399 
9400  // FIXME: This approach for uniquing ADL results (and removing
9401  // redundant candidates from the set) relies on pointer-equality,
9402  // which means we need to key off the canonical decl. However,
9403  // always going back to the canonical decl might not get us the
9404  // right set of default arguments. What default arguments are
9405  // we supposed to consider on ADL candidates, anyway?
9406 
9407  // FIXME: Pass in the explicit template arguments?
9408  ArgumentDependentLookup(Name, Loc, Args, Fns);
9409 
9410  // Erase all of the candidates we already knew about.
9411  for (OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Cand = CandidateSet.begin(),
9412  CandEnd = CandidateSet.end();
9413  Cand != CandEnd; ++Cand)
9414  if (Cand->Function) {
9415  Fns.erase(Cand->Function);
9416  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = Cand->Function->getPrimaryTemplate())
9417  Fns.erase(FunTmpl);
9418  }
9419 
9420  // For each of the ADL candidates we found, add it to the overload
9421  // set.
9422  for (ADLResult::iterator I = Fns.begin(), E = Fns.end(); I != E; ++I) {
9423  DeclAccessPair FoundDecl = DeclAccessPair::make(*I, AS_none);
9424 
9425  if (FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(*I)) {
9426  if (ExplicitTemplateArgs)
9427  continue;
9428 
9429  AddOverloadCandidate(
9430  FD, FoundDecl, Args, CandidateSet, /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false,
9431  PartialOverloading, /*AllowExplicit=*/true,
9432  /*AllowExplicitConversion=*/false, ADLCallKind::UsesADL);
9433  if (CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().shouldAddReversed(Context, FD)) {
9434  AddOverloadCandidate(
9435  FD, FoundDecl, {Args[1], Args[0]}, CandidateSet,
9436  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false, PartialOverloading,
9437  /*AllowExplicit=*/true, /*AllowExplicitConversion=*/false,
9438  ADLCallKind::UsesADL, None, OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed);
9439  }
9440  } else {
9441  auto *FTD = cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(*I);
9442  AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(
9443  FTD, FoundDecl, ExplicitTemplateArgs, Args, CandidateSet,
9444  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false, PartialOverloading,
9445  /*AllowExplicit=*/true, ADLCallKind::UsesADL);
9446  if (CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().shouldAddReversed(
9447  Context, FTD->getTemplatedDecl())) {
9448  AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(
9449  FTD, FoundDecl, ExplicitTemplateArgs, {Args[1], Args[0]},
9450  CandidateSet, /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false, PartialOverloading,
9451  /*AllowExplicit=*/true, ADLCallKind::UsesADL,
9452  OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed);
9453  }
9454  }
9455  }
9456 }
9457 
9458 namespace {
9459 enum class Comparison { Equal, Better, Worse };
9460 }
9461 
9462 /// Compares the enable_if attributes of two FunctionDecls, for the purposes of
9463 /// overload resolution.
9464 ///
9465 /// Cand1's set of enable_if attributes are said to be "better" than Cand2's iff
9466 /// Cand1's first N enable_if attributes have precisely the same conditions as
9467 /// Cand2's first N enable_if attributes (where N = the number of enable_if
9468 /// attributes on Cand2), and Cand1 has more than N enable_if attributes.
9469 ///
9470 /// Note that you can have a pair of candidates such that Cand1's enable_if
9471 /// attributes are worse than Cand2's, and Cand2's enable_if attributes are
9472 /// worse than Cand1's.
9473 static Comparison compareEnableIfAttrs(const Sema &S, const FunctionDecl *Cand1,
9474  const FunctionDecl *Cand2) {
9475  // Common case: One (or both) decls don't have enable_if attrs.
9476  bool Cand1Attr = Cand1->hasAttr<EnableIfAttr>();
9477  bool Cand2Attr = Cand2->hasAttr<EnableIfAttr>();
9478  if (!Cand1Attr || !Cand2Attr) {
9479  if (Cand1Attr == Cand2Attr)
9480  return Comparison::Equal;
9481  return Cand1Attr ? Comparison::Better : Comparison::Worse;
9482  }
9483 
9484  auto Cand1Attrs = Cand1->specific_attrs<EnableIfAttr>();
9485  auto Cand2Attrs = Cand2->specific_attrs<EnableIfAttr>();
9486 
9487  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID Cand1ID, Cand2ID;
9488  for (auto Pair : zip_longest(Cand1Attrs, Cand2Attrs)) {
9489  Optional<EnableIfAttr *> Cand1A = std::get<0>(Pair);
9490  Optional<EnableIfAttr *> Cand2A = std::get<1>(Pair);
9491 
9492  // It's impossible for Cand1 to be better than (or equal to) Cand2 if Cand1
9493  // has fewer enable_if attributes than Cand2, and vice versa.
9494  if (!Cand1A)
9495  return Comparison::Worse;
9496  if (!Cand2A)
9497  return Comparison::Better;
9498 
9499  Cand1ID.clear();
9500  Cand2ID.clear();
9501 
9502  (*Cand1A)->getCond()->Profile(Cand1ID, S.getASTContext(), true);
9503  (*Cand2A)->getCond()->Profile(Cand2ID, S.getASTContext(), true);
9504  if (Cand1ID != Cand2ID)
9505  return Comparison::Worse;
9506  }
9507 
9508  return Comparison::Equal;
9509 }
9510 
9511 static Comparison
9512 isBetterMultiversionCandidate(const OverloadCandidate &Cand1,
9513  const OverloadCandidate &Cand2) {
9514  if (!Cand1.Function || !Cand1.Function->isMultiVersion() || !Cand2.Function ||
9515  !Cand2.Function->isMultiVersion())
9516  return Comparison::Equal;
9517 
9518  // If both are invalid, they are equal. If one of them is invalid, the other
9519  // is better.
9520  if (Cand1.Function->isInvalidDecl()) {
9521  if (Cand2.Function->isInvalidDecl())
9522  return Comparison::Equal;
9523  return Comparison::Worse;
9524  }
9525  if (Cand2.Function->isInvalidDecl())
9526  return Comparison::Better;
9527 
9528  // If this is a cpu_dispatch/cpu_specific multiversion situation, prefer
9529  // cpu_dispatch, else arbitrarily based on the identifiers.
9530  bool Cand1CPUDisp = Cand1.Function->hasAttr<CPUDispatchAttr>();
9531  bool Cand2CPUDisp = Cand2.Function->hasAttr<CPUDispatchAttr>();
9532  const auto *Cand1CPUSpec = Cand1.Function->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>();
9533  const auto *Cand2CPUSpec = Cand2.Function->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>();
9534 
9535  if (!Cand1CPUDisp && !Cand2CPUDisp && !Cand1CPUSpec && !Cand2CPUSpec)
9536  return Comparison::Equal;
9537 
9538  if (Cand1CPUDisp && !Cand2CPUDisp)
9539  return Comparison::Better;
9540  if (Cand2CPUDisp && !Cand1CPUDisp)
9541  return Comparison::Worse;
9542 
9543  if (Cand1CPUSpec && Cand2CPUSpec) {
9544  if (Cand1CPUSpec->cpus_size() != Cand2CPUSpec->cpus_size())
9545  return Cand1CPUSpec->cpus_size() < Cand2CPUSpec->cpus_size()
9546  ? Comparison::Better
9547  : Comparison::Worse;
9548 
9549  std::pair<CPUSpecificAttr::cpus_iterator, CPUSpecificAttr::cpus_iterator>
9550  FirstDiff = std::mismatch(
9551  Cand1CPUSpec->cpus_begin(), Cand1CPUSpec->cpus_end(),
9552  Cand2CPUSpec->cpus_begin(),
9553  [](const IdentifierInfo *LHS, const IdentifierInfo *RHS) {
9554  return LHS->getName() == RHS->getName();
9555  });
9556 
9557  assert(FirstDiff.first != Cand1CPUSpec->cpus_end() &&
9558  "Two different cpu-specific versions should not have the same "
9559  "identifier list, otherwise they'd be the same decl!");
9560  return (*FirstDiff.first)->getName() < (*FirstDiff.second)->getName()
9561  ? Comparison::Better
9562  : Comparison::Worse;
9563  }
9564  llvm_unreachable("No way to get here unless both had cpu_dispatch");
9565 }
9566 
9567 /// Compute the type of the implicit object parameter for the given function,
9568 /// if any. Returns None if there is no implicit object parameter, and a null
9569 /// QualType if there is a 'matches anything' implicit object parameter.
9570 static Optional<QualType> getImplicitObjectParamType(ASTContext &Context,
9571  const FunctionDecl *F) {
9572  if (!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(F) || isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(F))
9573  return llvm::None;
9574 
9575  auto *M = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(F);
9576  // Static member functions' object parameters match all types.
9577  if (M->isStatic())
9578  return QualType();
9579 
9580  QualType T = M->getThisObjectType();
9581  if (M->getRefQualifier() == RQ_RValue)
9582  return Context.getRValueReferenceType(T);
9583  return Context.getLValueReferenceType(T);
9584 }
9585 
9586 static bool haveSameParameterTypes(ASTContext &Context, const FunctionDecl *F1,
9587  const FunctionDecl *F2, unsigned NumParams) {
9588  if (declaresSameEntity(F1, F2))
9589  return true;
9590 
9591  auto NextParam = [&](const FunctionDecl *F, unsigned &I, bool First) {
9592  if (First) {
9593  if (Optional<QualType> T = getImplicitObjectParamType(Context, F))
9594  return *T;
9595  }
9596  assert(I < F->getNumParams());
9597  return F->getParamDecl(I++)->getType();
9598  };
9599 
9600  unsigned I1 = 0, I2 = 0;
9601  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumParams; ++I) {
9602  QualType T1 = NextParam(F1, I1, I == 0);
9603  QualType T2 = NextParam(F2, I2, I == 0);
9604  assert(!T1.isNull() && !T2.isNull() && "Unexpected null param types");
9605  if (!Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(T1, T2))
9606  return false;
9607  }
9608  return true;
9609 }
9610 
9611 /// isBetterOverloadCandidate - Determines whether the first overload
9612 /// candidate is a better candidate than the second (C++ 13.3.3p1).
9613 bool clang::isBetterOverloadCandidate(
9614  Sema &S, const OverloadCandidate &Cand1, const OverloadCandidate &Cand2,
9615  SourceLocation Loc, OverloadCandidateSet::CandidateSetKind Kind) {
9616  // Define viable functions to be better candidates than non-viable
9617  // functions.
9618  if (!Cand2.Viable)
9619  return Cand1.Viable;
9620  else if (!Cand1.Viable)
9621  return false;
9622 
9623  // [CUDA] A function with 'never' preference is marked not viable, therefore
9624  // is never shown up here. The worst preference shown up here is 'wrong side',
9625  // e.g. an H function called by a HD function in device compilation. This is
9626  // valid AST as long as the HD function is not emitted, e.g. it is an inline
9627  // function which is called only by an H function. A deferred diagnostic will
9628  // be triggered if it is emitted. However a wrong-sided function is still
9629  // a viable candidate here.
9630  //
9631  // If Cand1 can be emitted and Cand2 cannot be emitted in the current
9632  // context, Cand1 is better than Cand2. If Cand1 can not be emitted and Cand2
9633  // can be emitted, Cand1 is not better than Cand2. This rule should have
9634  // precedence over other rules.
9635  //
9636  // If both Cand1 and Cand2 can be emitted, or neither can be emitted, then
9637  // other rules should be used to determine which is better. This is because
9638  // host/device based overloading resolution is mostly for determining
9639  // viability of a function. If two functions are both viable, other factors
9640  // should take precedence in preference, e.g. the standard-defined preferences
9641  // like argument conversion ranks or enable_if partial-ordering. The
9642  // preference for pass-object-size parameters is probably most similar to a
9643  // type-based-overloading decision and so should take priority.
9644  //
9645  // If other rules cannot determine which is better, CUDA preference will be
9646  // used again to determine which is better.
9647  //
9648  // TODO: Currently IdentifyCUDAPreference does not return correct values
9649  // for functions called in global variable initializers due to missing
9650  // correct context about device/host. Therefore we can only enforce this
9651  // rule when there is a caller. We should enforce this rule for functions
9652  // in global variable initializers once proper context is added.
9653  //
9654  // TODO: We can only enable the hostness based overloading resolution when
9655  // -fgpu-exclude-wrong-side-overloads is on since this requires deferring
9656  // overloading resolution diagnostics.
9657  if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA && Cand1.Function && Cand2.Function &&
9658  S.getLangOpts().GPUExcludeWrongSideOverloads) {
9659  if (FunctionDecl *Caller = S.getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true)) {
9660  bool IsCallerImplicitHD = Sema::isCUDAImplicitHostDeviceFunction(Caller);
9661  bool IsCand1ImplicitHD =
9662  Sema::isCUDAImplicitHostDeviceFunction(Cand1.Function);
9663  bool IsCand2ImplicitHD =
9664  Sema::isCUDAImplicitHostDeviceFunction(Cand2.Function);
9665  auto P1 = S.IdentifyCUDAPreference(Caller, Cand1.Function);
9666  auto P2 = S.IdentifyCUDAPreference(Caller, Cand2.Function);
9667  assert(P1 != Sema::CFP_Never && P2 != Sema::CFP_Never);
9668  // The implicit HD function may be a function in a system header which
9669  // is forced by pragma. In device compilation, if we prefer HD candidates
9670  // over wrong-sided candidates, overloading resolution may change, which
9671  // may result in non-deferrable diagnostics. As a workaround, we let
9672  // implicit HD candidates take equal preference as wrong-sided candidates.
9673  // This will preserve the overloading resolution.
9674  // TODO: We still need special handling of implicit HD functions since
9675  // they may incur other diagnostics to be deferred. We should make all
9676  // host/device related diagnostics deferrable and remove special handling
9677  // of implicit HD functions.
9678  auto EmitThreshold =
9679  (S.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && IsCallerImplicitHD &&
9680  (IsCand1ImplicitHD || IsCand2ImplicitHD))
9681  ? Sema::CFP_Never
9682  : Sema::CFP_WrongSide;
9683  auto Cand1Emittable = P1 > EmitThreshold;
9684  auto Cand2Emittable = P2 > EmitThreshold;
9685  if (Cand1Emittable && !Cand2Emittable)
9686  return true;
9687  if (!Cand1Emittable && Cand2Emittable)
9688  return false;
9689  }
9690  }
9691 
9692  // C++ [over.match.best]p1:
9693  //
9694  // -- if F is a static member function, ICS1(F) is defined such
9695  // that ICS1(F) is neither better nor worse than ICS1(G) for
9696  // any function G, and, symmetrically, ICS1(G) is neither
9697  // better nor worse than ICS1(F).
9698  unsigned StartArg = 0;
9699  if (Cand1.IgnoreObjectArgument || Cand2.IgnoreObjectArgument)
9700  StartArg = 1;
9701 
9702  auto IsIllFormedConversion = [&](const ImplicitConversionSequence &ICS) {
9703  // We don't allow incompatible pointer conversions in C++.
9704  if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
9705  return ICS.isStandard() &&
9706  ICS.Standard.Second == ICK_Incompatible_Pointer_Conversion;
9707 
9708  // The only ill-formed conversion we allow in C++ is the string literal to
9709  // char* conversion, which is only considered ill-formed after C++11.
9710  return S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && !S.getLangOpts().WritableStrings &&
9711  hasDeprecatedStringLiteralToCharPtrConversion(ICS);
9712  };
9713 
9714  // Define functions that don't require ill-formed conversions for a given
9715  // argument to be better candidates than functions that do.
9716  unsigned NumArgs = Cand1.Conversions.size();
9717  assert(Cand2.Conversions.size() == NumArgs && "Overload candidate mismatch");
9718  bool HasBetterConversion = false;
9719  for (unsigned ArgIdx = StartArg; ArgIdx < NumArgs; ++ArgIdx) {
9720  bool Cand1Bad = IsIllFormedConversion(Cand1.Conversions[ArgIdx]);
9721  bool Cand2Bad = IsIllFormedConversion(Cand2.Conversions[ArgIdx]);
9722  if (Cand1Bad != Cand2Bad) {
9723  if (Cand1Bad)
9724  return false;
9725  HasBetterConversion = true;
9726  }
9727  }
9728 
9729  if (HasBetterConversion)
9730  return true;
9731 
9732  // C++ [over.match.best]p1:
9733  // A viable function F1 is defined to be a better function than another
9734  // viable function F2 if for all arguments i, ICSi(F1) is not a worse
9735  // conversion sequence than ICSi(F2), and then...
9736  bool HasWorseConversion = false;
9737  for (unsigned ArgIdx = StartArg; ArgIdx < NumArgs; ++ArgIdx) {
9738  switch (CompareImplicitConversionSequences(S, Loc,
9739  Cand1.Conversions[ArgIdx],
9740  Cand2.Conversions[ArgIdx])) {
9741  case ImplicitConversionSequence::Better:
9742  // Cand1 has a better conversion sequence.
9743  HasBetterConversion = true;
9744  break;
9745 
9746  case ImplicitConversionSequence::Worse:
9747  if (Cand1.Function && Cand2.Function &&
9748  Cand1.isReversed() != Cand2.isReversed() &&
9749  haveSameParameterTypes(S.Context, Cand1.Function, Cand2.Function,
9750  NumArgs)) {
9751  // Work around large-scale breakage caused by considering reversed
9752  // forms of operator== in C++20:
9753  //
9754  // When comparing a function against a reversed function with the same
9755  // parameter types, if we have a better conversion for one argument and
9756  // a worse conversion for the other, the implicit conversion sequences
9757  // are treated as being equally good.
9758  //
9759  // This prevents a comparison function from being considered ambiguous
9760  // with a reversed form that is written in the same way.
9761  //
9762  // We diagnose this as an extension from CreateOverloadedBinOp.
9763  HasWorseConversion = true;
9764  break;
9765  }
9766 
9767  // Cand1 can't be better than Cand2.
9768  return false;
9769 
9770  case ImplicitConversionSequence::Indistinguishable:
9771  // Do nothing.
9772  break;
9773  }
9774  }
9775 
9776  // -- for some argument j, ICSj(F1) is a better conversion sequence than
9777  // ICSj(F2), or, if not that,
9778  if (HasBetterConversion && !HasWorseConversion)
9779  return true;
9780 
9781  // -- the context is an initialization by user-defined conversion
9782  // (see 8.5, 13.3.1.5) and the standard conversion sequence
9783  // from the return type of F1 to the destination type (i.e.,
9784  // the type of the entity being initialized) is a better
9785  // conversion sequence than the standard conversion sequence
9786  // from the return type of F2 to the destination type.
9787  if (Kind == OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_InitByUserDefinedConversion &&
9788  Cand1.Function && Cand2.Function &&
9789  isa<CXXConversionDecl>(Cand1.Function) &&
9790  isa<CXXConversionDecl>(Cand2.Function)) {
9791  // First check whether we prefer one of the conversion functions over the
9792  // other. This only distinguishes the results in non-standard, extension
9793  // cases such as the conversion from a lambda closure type to a function
9794  // pointer or block.
9795  ImplicitConversionSequence::CompareKind Result =
9796  compareConversionFunctions(S, Cand1.Function, Cand2.Function);
9797  if (Result == ImplicitConversionSequence::Indistinguishable)
9798  Result = CompareStandardConversionSequences(S, Loc,
9799  Cand1.FinalConversion,
9800  Cand2.FinalConversion);
9801 
9802  if (Result != ImplicitConversionSequence::Indistinguishable)
9803  return Result == ImplicitConversionSequence::Better;
9804 
9805  // FIXME: Compare kind of reference binding if conversion functions
9806  // convert to a reference type used in direct reference binding, per
9807  // C++14 [over.match.best]p1 section 2 bullet 3.
9808  }
9809 
9810  // FIXME: Work around a defect in the C++17 guaranteed copy elision wording,
9811  // as combined with the resolution to CWG issue 243.
9812  //
9813  // When the context is initialization by constructor ([over.match.ctor] or
9814  // either phase of [over.match.list]), a constructor is preferred over
9815  // a conversion function.
9816  if (Kind == OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_InitByConstructor && NumArgs == 1 &&
9817  Cand1.Function && Cand2.Function &&
9818  isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Cand1.Function) !=
9819  isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Cand2.Function))
9820  return isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Cand1.Function);
9821 
9822  // -- F1 is a non-template function and F2 is a function template
9823  // specialization, or, if not that,
9824  bool Cand1IsSpecialization = Cand1.Function &&
9825  Cand1.Function->getPrimaryTemplate();
9826  bool Cand2IsSpecialization = Cand2.Function &&
9827  Cand2.Function->getPrimaryTemplate();
9828  if (Cand1IsSpecialization != Cand2IsSpecialization)
9829  return Cand2IsSpecialization;
9830 
9831  // -- F1 and F2 are function template specializations, and the function
9832  // template for F1 is more specialized than the template for F2
9833  // according to the partial ordering rules described in 14.5.5.2, or,
9834  // if not that,
9835  if (Cand1IsSpecialization && Cand2IsSpecialization) {
9836  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *BetterTemplate = S.getMoreSpecializedTemplate(
9837  Cand1.Function->getPrimaryTemplate(),
9838  Cand2.Function->getPrimaryTemplate(), Loc,
