9839  isa<CXXConversionDecl>(Cand1.Function) ? TPOC_Conversion
9840  : TPOC_Call,
9841  Cand1.ExplicitCallArguments, Cand2.ExplicitCallArguments,
9842  Cand1.isReversed() ^ Cand2.isReversed()))
9843  return BetterTemplate == Cand1.Function->getPrimaryTemplate();
9844  }
9845 
9846  // - F1 and F2 are non-template functions with the same
9847  // parameter-type-lists, and F1 is more constrained than F2 [...],
9848  if (Cand1.Function && Cand2.Function && !Cand1IsSpecialization &&
9849  !Cand2IsSpecialization && Cand1.Function->hasPrototype() &&
9850  Cand2.Function->hasPrototype()) {
9851  auto *PT1 = cast<FunctionProtoType>(Cand1.Function->getFunctionType());
9852  auto *PT2 = cast<FunctionProtoType>(Cand2.Function->getFunctionType());
9853  if (PT1->getNumParams() == PT2->getNumParams() &&
9854  PT1->isVariadic() == PT2->isVariadic() &&
9855  S.FunctionParamTypesAreEqual(PT1, PT2)) {
9856  Expr *RC1 = Cand1.Function->getTrailingRequiresClause();
9857  Expr *RC2 = Cand2.Function->getTrailingRequiresClause();
9858  if (RC1 && RC2) {
9859  bool AtLeastAsConstrained1, AtLeastAsConstrained2;
9860  if (S.IsAtLeastAsConstrained(Cand1.Function, {RC1}, Cand2.Function,
9861  {RC2}, AtLeastAsConstrained1) ||
9862  S.IsAtLeastAsConstrained(Cand2.Function, {RC2}, Cand1.Function,
9863  {RC1}, AtLeastAsConstrained2))
9864  return false;
9865  if (AtLeastAsConstrained1 != AtLeastAsConstrained2)
9866  return AtLeastAsConstrained1;
9867  } else if (RC1 || RC2) {
9868  return RC1 != nullptr;
9869  }
9870  }
9871  }
9872 
9873  // -- F1 is a constructor for a class D, F2 is a constructor for a base
9874  // class B of D, and for all arguments the corresponding parameters of
9875  // F1 and F2 have the same type.
9876  // FIXME: Implement the "all parameters have the same type" check.
9877  bool Cand1IsInherited =
9878  isa_and_nonnull<ConstructorUsingShadowDecl>(Cand1.FoundDecl.getDecl());
9879  bool Cand2IsInherited =
9880  isa_and_nonnull<ConstructorUsingShadowDecl>(Cand2.FoundDecl.getDecl());
9881  if (Cand1IsInherited != Cand2IsInherited)
9882  return Cand2IsInherited;
9883  else if (Cand1IsInherited) {
9884  assert(Cand2IsInherited);
9885  auto *Cand1Class = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Cand1.Function->getDeclContext());
9886  auto *Cand2Class = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Cand2.Function->getDeclContext());
9887  if (Cand1Class->isDerivedFrom(Cand2Class))
9888  return true;
9889  if (Cand2Class->isDerivedFrom(Cand1Class))
9890  return false;
9891  // Inherited from sibling base classes: still ambiguous.
9892  }
9893 
9894  // -- F2 is a rewritten candidate (12.4.1.2) and F1 is not
9895  // -- F1 and F2 are rewritten candidates, and F2 is a synthesized candidate
9896  // with reversed order of parameters and F1 is not
9897  //
9898  // We rank reversed + different operator as worse than just reversed, but
9899  // that comparison can never happen, because we only consider reversing for
9900  // the maximally-rewritten operator (== or <=>).
9901  if (Cand1.RewriteKind != Cand2.RewriteKind)
9902  return Cand1.RewriteKind < Cand2.RewriteKind;
9903 
9904  // Check C++17 tie-breakers for deduction guides.
9905  {
9906  auto *Guide1 = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(Cand1.Function);
9907  auto *Guide2 = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(Cand2.Function);
9908  if (Guide1 && Guide2) {
9909  // -- F1 is generated from a deduction-guide and F2 is not
9910  if (Guide1->isImplicit() != Guide2->isImplicit())
9911  return Guide2->isImplicit();
9912 
9913  // -- F1 is the copy deduction candidate(16.3.1.8) and F2 is not
9914  if (Guide1->isCopyDeductionCandidate())
9915  return true;
9916  }
9917  }
9918 
9919  // Check for enable_if value-based overload resolution.
9920  if (Cand1.Function && Cand2.Function) {
9921  Comparison Cmp = compareEnableIfAttrs(S, Cand1.Function, Cand2.Function);
9922  if (Cmp != Comparison::Equal)
9923  return Cmp == Comparison::Better;
9924  }
9925 
9926  bool HasPS1 = Cand1.Function != nullptr &&
9927  functionHasPassObjectSizeParams(Cand1.Function);
9928  bool HasPS2 = Cand2.Function != nullptr &&
9929  functionHasPassObjectSizeParams(Cand2.Function);
9930  if (HasPS1 != HasPS2 && HasPS1)
9931  return true;
9932 
9933  auto MV = isBetterMultiversionCandidate(Cand1, Cand2);
9934  if (MV == Comparison::Better)
9935  return true;
9936  if (MV == Comparison::Worse)
9937  return false;
9938 
9939  // If other rules cannot determine which is better, CUDA preference is used
9940  // to determine which is better.
9941  if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA && Cand1.Function && Cand2.Function) {
9942  FunctionDecl *Caller = S.getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true);
9943  return S.IdentifyCUDAPreference(Caller, Cand1.Function) >
9944  S.IdentifyCUDAPreference(Caller, Cand2.Function);
9945  }
9946 
9947  // General member function overloading is handled above, so this only handles
9948  // constructors with address spaces.
9949  // This only handles address spaces since C++ has no other
9950  // qualifier that can be used with constructors.
9951  const auto *CD1 = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXConstructorDecl>(Cand1.Function);
9952  const auto *CD2 = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXConstructorDecl>(Cand2.Function);
9953  if (CD1 && CD2) {
9954  LangAS AS1 = CD1->getMethodQualifiers().getAddressSpace();
9955  LangAS AS2 = CD2->getMethodQualifiers().getAddressSpace();
9956  if (AS1 != AS2) {
9957  if (Qualifiers::isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(AS2, AS1))
9958  return true;
9959  if (Qualifiers::isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(AS2, AS1))
9960  return false;
9961  }
9962  }
9963 
9964  return false;
9965 }
9966 
9967 /// Determine whether two declarations are "equivalent" for the purposes of
9968 /// name lookup and overload resolution. This applies when the same internal/no
9969 /// linkage entity is defined by two modules (probably by textually including
9970 /// the same header). In such a case, we don't consider the declarations to
9971 /// declare the same entity, but we also don't want lookups with both
9972 /// declarations visible to be ambiguous in some cases (this happens when using
9973 /// a modularized libstdc++).
9974 bool Sema::isEquivalentInternalLinkageDeclaration(const NamedDecl *A,
9975  const NamedDecl *B) {
9976  auto *VA = dyn_cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(A);
9977  auto *VB = dyn_cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(B);
9978  if (!VA || !VB)
9979  return false;
9980 
9981  // The declarations must be declaring the same name as an internal linkage
9982  // entity in different modules.
9983  if (!VA->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()->Equals(
9984  VB->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()) ||
9985  getOwningModule(VA) == getOwningModule(VB) ||
9986  VA->isExternallyVisible() || VB->isExternallyVisible())
9987  return false;
9988 
9989  // Check that the declarations appear to be equivalent.
9990  //
9991  // FIXME: Checking the type isn't really enough to resolve the ambiguity.
9992  // For constants and functions, we should check the initializer or body is
9993  // the same. For non-constant variables, we shouldn't allow it at all.
9994  if (Context.hasSameType(VA->getType(), VB->getType()))
9995  return true;
9996 
9997  // Enum constants within unnamed enumerations will have different types, but
9998  // may still be similar enough to be interchangeable for our purposes.
9999  if (auto *EA = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(VA)) {
10000  if (auto *EB = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(VB)) {
10001  // Only handle anonymous enums. If the enumerations were named and
10002  // equivalent, they would have been merged to the same type.
10003  auto *EnumA = cast<EnumDecl>(EA->getDeclContext());
10004  auto *EnumB = cast<EnumDecl>(EB->getDeclContext());
10005  if (EnumA->hasNameForLinkage() || EnumB->hasNameForLinkage() ||
10006  !Context.hasSameType(EnumA->getIntegerType(),
10007  EnumB->getIntegerType()))
10008  return false;
10009  // Allow this only if the value is the same for both enumerators.
10010  return llvm::APSInt::isSameValue(EA->getInitVal(), EB->getInitVal());
10011  }
10012  }
10013 
10014  // Nothing else is sufficiently similar.
10015  return false;
10016 }
10017 
10018 void Sema::diagnoseEquivalentInternalLinkageDeclarations(
10019  SourceLocation Loc, const NamedDecl *D, ArrayRef<const NamedDecl *> Equiv) {
10020  assert(D && "Unknown declaration");
10021  Diag(Loc, diag::ext_equivalent_internal_linkage_decl_in_modules) << D;
10022 
10023  Module *M = getOwningModule(D);
10024  Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::note_equivalent_internal_linkage_decl)
10025  << !M << (M ? M->getFullModuleName() : "");
10026 
10027  for (auto *E : Equiv) {
10028  Module *M = getOwningModule(E);
10029  Diag(E->getLocation(), diag::note_equivalent_internal_linkage_decl)
10030  << !M << (M ? M->getFullModuleName() : "");
10031  }
10032 }
10033 
10034 /// Computes the best viable function (C++ 13.3.3)
10035 /// within an overload candidate set.
10036 ///
10037 /// \param Loc The location of the function name (or operator symbol) for
10038 /// which overload resolution occurs.
10039 ///
10040 /// \param Best If overload resolution was successful or found a deleted
10041 /// function, \p Best points to the candidate function found.
10042 ///
10043 /// \returns The result of overload resolution.
10044 OverloadingResult
10045 OverloadCandidateSet::BestViableFunction(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
10046  iterator &Best) {
10047  llvm::SmallVector<OverloadCandidate *, 16> Candidates;
10048  std::transform(begin(), end(), std::back_inserter(Candidates),
10049  [](OverloadCandidate &Cand) { return &Cand; });
10050 
10051  // [CUDA] HD->H or HD->D calls are technically not allowed by CUDA but
10052  // are accepted by both clang and NVCC. However, during a particular
10053  // compilation mode only one call variant is viable. We need to
10054  // exclude non-viable overload candidates from consideration based
10055  // only on their host/device attributes. Specifically, if one
10056  // candidate call is WrongSide and the other is SameSide, we ignore
10057  // the WrongSide candidate.
10058  // We only need to remove wrong-sided candidates here if
10059  // -fgpu-exclude-wrong-side-overloads is off. When
10060  // -fgpu-exclude-wrong-side-overloads is on, all candidates are compared
10061  // uniformly in isBetterOverloadCandidate.
10062  if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA && !S.getLangOpts().GPUExcludeWrongSideOverloads) {
10063  const FunctionDecl *Caller = S.getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true);
10064  bool ContainsSameSideCandidate =
10065  llvm::any_of(Candidates, [&](OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
10066  // Check viable function only.
10067  return Cand->Viable && Cand->Function &&
10068  S.IdentifyCUDAPreference(Caller, Cand->Function) ==
10069  Sema::CFP_SameSide;
10070  });
10071  if (ContainsSameSideCandidate) {
10072  auto IsWrongSideCandidate = [&](OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
10073  // Check viable function only to avoid unnecessary data copying/moving.
10074  return Cand->Viable && Cand->Function &&
10075  S.IdentifyCUDAPreference(Caller, Cand->Function) ==
10076  Sema::CFP_WrongSide;
10077  };
10078  llvm::erase_if(Candidates, IsWrongSideCandidate);
10079  }
10080  }
10081 
10082  // Find the best viable function.
10083  Best = end();
10084  for (auto *Cand : Candidates) {
10085  Cand->Best = false;
10086  if (Cand->Viable)
10087  if (Best == end() ||
10088  isBetterOverloadCandidate(S, *Cand, *Best, Loc, Kind))
10089  Best = Cand;
10090  }
10091 
10092  // If we didn't find any viable functions, abort.
10093  if (Best == end())
10094  return OR_No_Viable_Function;
10095 
10096  llvm::SmallVector<const NamedDecl *, 4> EquivalentCands;
10097 
10098  llvm::SmallVector<OverloadCandidate*, 4> PendingBest;
10099  PendingBest.push_back(&*Best);
10100  Best->Best = true;
10101 
10102  // Make sure that this function is better than every other viable
10103  // function. If not, we have an ambiguity.
10104  while (!PendingBest.empty()) {
10105  auto *Curr = PendingBest.pop_back_val();
10106  for (auto *Cand : Candidates) {
10107  if (Cand->Viable && !Cand->Best &&
10108  !isBetterOverloadCandidate(S, *Curr, *Cand, Loc, Kind)) {
10109  PendingBest.push_back(Cand);
10110  Cand->Best = true;
10111 
10112  if (S.isEquivalentInternalLinkageDeclaration(Cand->Function,
10113  Curr->Function))
10114  EquivalentCands.push_back(Cand->Function);
10115  else
10116  Best = end();
10117  }
10118  }
10119  }
10120 
10121  // If we found more than one best candidate, this is ambiguous.
10122  if (Best == end())
10123  return OR_Ambiguous;
10124 
10125  // Best is the best viable function.
10126  if (Best->Function && Best->Function->isDeleted())
10127  return OR_Deleted;
10128 
10129  if (!EquivalentCands.empty())
10130  S.diagnoseEquivalentInternalLinkageDeclarations(Loc, Best->Function,
10131  EquivalentCands);
10132 
10133  return OR_Success;
10134 }
10135 
10136 namespace {
10137 
10138 enum OverloadCandidateKind {
10139  oc_function,
10140  oc_method,
10141  oc_reversed_binary_operator,
10142  oc_constructor,
10143  oc_implicit_default_constructor,
10144  oc_implicit_copy_constructor,
10145  oc_implicit_move_constructor,
10146  oc_implicit_copy_assignment,
10147  oc_implicit_move_assignment,
10148  oc_implicit_equality_comparison,
10149  oc_inherited_constructor
10150 };
10151 
10152 enum OverloadCandidateSelect {
10153  ocs_non_template,
10154  ocs_template,
10155  ocs_described_template,
10156 };
10157 
10158 static std::pair<OverloadCandidateKind, OverloadCandidateSelect>
10159 ClassifyOverloadCandidate(Sema &S, NamedDecl *Found, FunctionDecl *Fn,
10160  OverloadCandidateRewriteKind CRK,
10161  std::string &Description) {
10162 
10163  bool isTemplate = Fn->isTemplateDecl() || Found->isTemplateDecl();
10164  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = Fn->getPrimaryTemplate()) {
10165  isTemplate = true;
10166  Description = S.getTemplateArgumentBindingsText(
10167  FunTmpl->getTemplateParameters(), *Fn->getTemplateSpecializationArgs());
10168  }
10169 
10170  OverloadCandidateSelect Select = [&]() {
10171  if (!Description.empty())
10172  return ocs_described_template;
10173  return isTemplate ? ocs_template : ocs_non_template;
10174  }();
10175 
10176  OverloadCandidateKind Kind = [&]() {
10177  if (Fn->isImplicit() && Fn->getOverloadedOperator() == OO_EqualEqual)
10178  return oc_implicit_equality_comparison;
10179 
10180  if (CRK & CRK_Reversed)
10181  return oc_reversed_binary_operator;
10182 
10183  if (CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Fn)) {
10184  if (!Ctor->isImplicit()) {
10185  if (isa<ConstructorUsingShadowDecl>(Found))
10186  return oc_inherited_constructor;
10187  else
10188  return oc_constructor;
10189  }
10190 
10191  if (Ctor->isDefaultConstructor())
10192  return oc_implicit_default_constructor;
10193 
10194  if (Ctor->isMoveConstructor())
10195  return oc_implicit_move_constructor;
10196 
10197  assert(Ctor->isCopyConstructor() &&
10198  "unexpected sort of implicit constructor");
10199  return oc_implicit_copy_constructor;
10200  }
10201 
10202  if (CXXMethodDecl *Meth = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn)) {
10203  // This actually gets spelled 'candidate function' for now, but
10204  // it doesn't hurt to split it out.
10205  if (!Meth->isImplicit())
10206  return oc_method;
10207 
10208  if (Meth->isMoveAssignmentOperator())
10209  return oc_implicit_move_assignment;
10210 
10211  if (Meth->isCopyAssignmentOperator())
10212  return oc_implicit_copy_assignment;
10213 
10214  assert(isa<CXXConversionDecl>(Meth) && "expected conversion");
10215  return oc_method;
10216  }
10217 
10218  return oc_function;
10219  }();
10220 
10221  return std::make_pair(Kind, Select);
10222 }
10223 
10224 void MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(Sema &S, Decl *FoundDecl) {
10225  // FIXME: It'd be nice to only emit a note once per using-decl per overload
10226  // set.
10227  if (auto *Shadow = dyn_cast<ConstructorUsingShadowDecl>(FoundDecl))
10228  S.Diag(FoundDecl->getLocation(),
10229  diag::note_ovl_candidate_inherited_constructor)
10230  << Shadow->getNominatedBaseClass();
10231 }
10232 
10233 } // end anonymous namespace
10234 
10235 static bool isFunctionAlwaysEnabled(const ASTContext &Ctx,
10236  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
10237  for (auto *EnableIf : FD->specific_attrs<EnableIfAttr>()) {
10238  bool AlwaysTrue;
10239  if (EnableIf->getCond()->isValueDependent() ||
10240  !EnableIf->getCond()->EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(AlwaysTrue, Ctx))
10241  return false;
10242  if (!AlwaysTrue)
10243  return false;
10244  }
10245  return true;
10246 }
10247 
10248 /// Returns true if we can take the address of the function.
10249 ///
10250 /// \param Complain - If true, we'll emit a diagnostic
10251 /// \param InOverloadResolution - For the purposes of emitting a diagnostic, are
10252 /// we in overload resolution?
10253 /// \param Loc - The location of the statement we're complaining about. Ignored
10254 /// if we're not complaining, or if we're in overload resolution.
10255 static bool checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(Sema &S, const FunctionDecl *FD,
10256  bool Complain,
10257  bool InOverloadResolution,
10258  SourceLocation Loc) {
10259  if (Complain && S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
10260  S.getLangOpts().SYCLAllowFuncPtr) {
10261  if (!FD->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceIndirectlyCallableAttr>()) {
10262  S.SYCLDiagIfDeviceCode(Loc,
10263  diag::err_sycl_taking_address_of_wrong_function,
10264  Sema::DeviceDiagnosticReason::Sycl);
10265  }
10266  }
10267 
10268  if (!isFunctionAlwaysEnabled(S.Context, FD)) {
10269  if (Complain) {
10270  if (InOverloadResolution)
10271  S.Diag(FD->getBeginLoc(),
10272  diag::note_addrof_ovl_candidate_disabled_by_enable_if_attr);
10273  else
10274  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_addrof_function_disabled_by_enable_if_attr) << FD;
10275  }
10276  return false;
10277  }
10278 
10279  if (FD->getTrailingRequiresClause()) {
10280  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
10281  if (S.CheckFunctionConstraints(FD, Satisfaction, Loc))
10282  return false;
10283  if (!Satisfaction.IsSatisfied) {
10284  if (Complain) {
10285  if (InOverloadResolution) {
10286  SmallString<128> TemplateArgString;
10287  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = FD->getPrimaryTemplate()) {
10288  TemplateArgString += " ";
10289  TemplateArgString += S.getTemplateArgumentBindingsText(
10290  FunTmpl->getTemplateParameters(),
10291  *FD->getTemplateSpecializationArgs());
10292  }
10293 
10294  S.Diag(FD->getBeginLoc(),
10295  diag::note_ovl_candidate_unsatisfied_constraints)
10296  << TemplateArgString;
10297  } else
10298  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_addrof_function_constraints_not_satisfied)
10299  << FD;
10300  S.DiagnoseUnsatisfiedConstraint(Satisfaction);
10301  }
10302  return false;
10303  }
10304  }
10305 
10306  auto I = llvm::find_if(FD->parameters(), [](const ParmVarDecl *P) {
10307  return P->hasAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>();
10308  });
10309  if (I == FD->param_end())
10310  return true;
10311 
10312  if (Complain) {
10313  // Add one to ParamNo because it's user-facing
10314  unsigned ParamNo = std::distance(FD->param_begin(), I) + 1;
10315  if (InOverloadResolution)
10316  S.Diag(FD->getLocation(),
10317  diag::note_ovl_candidate_has_pass_object_size_params)
10318  << ParamNo;
10319  else
10320  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_address_of_function_with_pass_object_size_params)
10321  << FD << ParamNo;
10322  }
10323  return false;
10324 }
10325 
10326 static bool checkAddressOfCandidateIsAvailable(Sema &S,
10327  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
10328  return checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(S, FD, /*Complain=*/true,
10329  /*InOverloadResolution=*/true,
10330  /*Loc=*/SourceLocation());
10331 }
10332 
10333 bool Sema::checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(const FunctionDecl *Function,
10334  bool Complain,
10335  SourceLocation Loc) {
10336  return ::checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(*this, Function, Complain,
10337  /*InOverloadResolution=*/false,
10338  Loc);
10339 }
10340 
10341 // Don't print candidates other than the one that matches the calling
10342 // convention of the call operator, since that is guaranteed to exist.
10343 static bool shouldSkipNotingLambdaConversionDecl(FunctionDecl *Fn) {
10344  const auto *ConvD = dyn_cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Fn);
10345 
10346  if (!ConvD)
10347  return false;
10348  const auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Fn->getParent());
10349  if (!RD->isLambda())
10350  return false;
10351 
10352  CXXMethodDecl *CallOp = RD->getLambdaCallOperator();
10353  CallingConv CallOpCC =
10354  CallOp->getType()->castAs<FunctionType>()->getCallConv();
10355  QualType ConvRTy = ConvD->getType()->castAs<FunctionType>()->getReturnType();
10356  CallingConv ConvToCC =
10357  ConvRTy->getPointeeType()->castAs<FunctionType>()->getCallConv();
10358 
10359  return ConvToCC != CallOpCC;
10360 }
10361 
10362 // Notes the location of an overload candidate.
10363 void Sema::NoteOverloadCandidate(NamedDecl *Found, FunctionDecl *Fn,
10364  OverloadCandidateRewriteKind RewriteKind,
10365  QualType DestType, bool TakingAddress) {
10366  if (TakingAddress && !checkAddressOfCandidateIsAvailable(*this, Fn))
10367  return;
10368  if (Fn->isMultiVersion() && Fn->hasAttr<TargetAttr>() &&
10369  !Fn->getAttr<TargetAttr>()->isDefaultVersion())
10370  return;
10371  if (shouldSkipNotingLambdaConversionDecl(Fn))
10372  return;
10373 
10374  std::string FnDesc;
10375  std::pair<OverloadCandidateKind, OverloadCandidateSelect> KSPair =
10376  ClassifyOverloadCandidate(*this, Found, Fn, RewriteKind, FnDesc);
10377  PartialDiagnostic PD = PDiag(diag::note_ovl_candidate)
10378  << (unsigned)KSPair.first << (unsigned)KSPair.second
10379  << Fn << FnDesc;
10380 
10381  HandleFunctionTypeMismatch(PD, Fn->getType(), DestType);
10382  Diag(Fn->getLocation(), PD);
10383  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(*this, Found);
10384 }
10385 
10386 static void
10387 MaybeDiagnoseAmbiguousConstraints(Sema &S, ArrayRef<OverloadCandidate> Cands) {
10388  // Perhaps the ambiguity was caused by two atomic constraints that are
10389  // 'identical' but not equivalent:
10390  //
10391  // void foo() requires (sizeof(T) > 4) { } // #1
10392  // void foo() requires (sizeof(T) > 4) && T::value { } // #2
10393  //
10394  // The 'sizeof(T) > 4' constraints are seemingly equivalent and should cause
10395  // #2 to subsume #1, but these constraint are not considered equivalent
10396  // according to the subsumption rules because they are not the same
10397  // source-level construct. This behavior is quite confusing and we should try
10398  // to help the user figure out what happened.
10399 
10400  SmallVector<const Expr *, 3> FirstAC, SecondAC;
10401  FunctionDecl *FirstCand = nullptr, *SecondCand = nullptr;
10402  for (auto I = Cands.begin(), E = Cands.end(); I != E; ++I) {
10403  if (!I->Function)
10404  continue;
10405  SmallVector<const Expr *, 3> AC;
10406  if (auto *Template = I->Function->getPrimaryTemplate())
10407  Template->getAssociatedConstraints(AC);
10408  else
10409  I->Function->getAssociatedConstraints(AC);
10410  if (AC.empty())
10411  continue;
10412  if (FirstCand == nullptr) {
10413  FirstCand = I->Function;
10414  FirstAC = AC;
10415  } else if (SecondCand == nullptr) {
10416  SecondCand = I->Function;
10417  SecondAC = AC;
10418  } else {
10419  // We have more than one pair of constrained functions - this check is
10420  // expensive and we'd rather not try to diagnose it.
10421  return;
10422  }
10423  }
10424  if (!SecondCand)
10425  return;
10426  // The diagnostic can only happen if there are associated constraints on
10427  // both sides (there needs to be some identical atomic constraint).
10428  if (S.MaybeEmitAmbiguousAtomicConstraintsDiagnostic(FirstCand, FirstAC,
10429  SecondCand, SecondAC))
10430  // Just show the user one diagnostic, they'll probably figure it out
10431  // from here.
10432  return;
10433 }
10434 
10435 // Notes the location of all overload candidates designated through
10436 // OverloadedExpr
10437 void Sema::NoteAllOverloadCandidates(Expr *OverloadedExpr, QualType DestType,
10438  bool TakingAddress) {
10439  assert(OverloadedExpr->getType() == Context.OverloadTy);
10440 
10441  OverloadExpr::FindResult Ovl = OverloadExpr::find(OverloadedExpr);
10442  OverloadExpr *OvlExpr = Ovl.Expression;
10443 
10444  for (UnresolvedSetIterator I = OvlExpr->decls_begin(),
10445  IEnd = OvlExpr->decls_end();
10446  I != IEnd; ++I) {
10447  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl =
10448  dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>((*I)->getUnderlyingDecl()) ) {
10449  NoteOverloadCandidate(*I, FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl(), CRK_None, DestType,
10450  TakingAddress);
10451  } else if (FunctionDecl *Fun
10452  = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>((*I)->getUnderlyingDecl()) ) {
10453  NoteOverloadCandidate(*I, Fun, CRK_None, DestType, TakingAddress);
10454  }
10455  }
10456 }
10457 
10458 /// Diagnoses an ambiguous conversion. The partial diagnostic is the
10459 /// "lead" diagnostic; it will be given two arguments, the source and
10460 /// target types of the conversion.
10461 void ImplicitConversionSequence::DiagnoseAmbiguousConversion(
10462  Sema &S,
10463  SourceLocation CaretLoc,
10464  const PartialDiagnostic &PDiag) const {
10465  S.Diag(CaretLoc, PDiag)
10466  << Ambiguous.getFromType() << Ambiguous.getToType();
10467  unsigned CandsShown = 0;
10468  AmbiguousConversionSequence::const_iterator I, E;
10469  for (I = Ambiguous.begin(), E = Ambiguous.end(); I != E; ++I) {
10470  if (CandsShown >= S.Diags.getNumOverloadCandidatesToShow())
10471  break;
10472  ++CandsShown;
10473  S.NoteOverloadCandidate(I->first, I->second);
10474  }
10475  S.Diags.overloadCandidatesShown(CandsShown);
10476  if (I != E)
10477  S.Diag(SourceLocation(), diag::note_ovl_too_many_candidates) << int(E - I);
10478 }
10479 
10480 static void DiagnoseBadConversion(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand,
10481  unsigned I, bool TakingCandidateAddress) {
10482  const ImplicitConversionSequence &Conv = Cand->Conversions[I];
10483  assert(Conv.isBad());
10484  assert(Cand->Function && "for now, candidate must be a function");
10485  FunctionDecl *Fn = Cand->Function;
10486 
10487  // There's a conversion slot for the object argument if this is a
10488  // non-constructor method. Note that 'I' corresponds the
10489  // conversion-slot index.
10490  bool isObjectArgument = false;
10491  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn) && !isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Fn)) {
10492  if (I == 0)
10493  isObjectArgument = true;
10494  else
10495  I--;
10496  }
10497 
10498  std::string FnDesc;
10499  std::pair<OverloadCandidateKind, OverloadCandidateSelect> FnKindPair =
10500  ClassifyOverloadCandidate(S, Cand->FoundDecl, Fn, Cand->getRewriteKind(),
10501  FnDesc);
10502 
10503  Expr *FromExpr = Conv.Bad.FromExpr;
10504  QualType FromTy = Conv.Bad.getFromType();
10505  QualType ToTy = Conv.Bad.getToType();
10506 
10507  if (FromTy == S.Context.OverloadTy) {
10508  assert(FromExpr && "overload set argument came from implicit argument?");
10509  Expr *E = FromExpr->IgnoreParens();
10510  if (isa<UnaryOperator>(E))
10511  E = cast<UnaryOperator>(E)->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParens();
10512  DeclarationName Name = cast<OverloadExpr>(E)->getName();
10513 
10514  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_overload)
10515  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10516  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << ToTy
10517  << Name << I + 1;
10518  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10519  return;
10520  }
10521 
10522  // Do some hand-waving analysis to see if the non-viability is due
10523  // to a qualifier mismatch.
10524  CanQualType CFromTy = S.Context.getCanonicalType(FromTy);
10525  CanQualType CToTy = S.Context.getCanonicalType(ToTy);
10526  if (CanQual<ReferenceType> RT = CToTy->getAs<ReferenceType>())
10527  CToTy = RT->getPointeeType();
10528  else {
10529  // TODO: detect and diagnose the full richness of const mismatches.
10530  if (CanQual<PointerType> FromPT = CFromTy->getAs<PointerType>())
10531  if (CanQual<PointerType> ToPT = CToTy->getAs<PointerType>()) {
10532  CFromTy = FromPT->getPointeeType();
10533  CToTy = ToPT->getPointeeType();
10534  }
10535  }
10536 
10537  if (CToTy.getUnqualifiedType() == CFromTy.getUnqualifiedType() &&
10538  !CToTy.isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(CFromTy)) {
10539  Qualifiers FromQs = CFromTy.getQualifiers();
10540  Qualifiers ToQs = CToTy.getQualifiers();
10541 
10542  if (FromQs.getAddressSpace() != ToQs.getAddressSpace()) {
10543  if (isObjectArgument)
10544  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_addrspace_this)
10545  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second
10546  << FnDesc << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange())
10547  << FromQs.getAddressSpace() << ToQs.getAddressSpace();
10548  else
10549  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_addrspace)
10550  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second
10551  << FnDesc << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange())
10552  << FromQs.getAddressSpace() << ToQs.getAddressSpace()
10553  << ToTy->isReferenceType() << I + 1;
10554  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10555  return;
10556  }
10557 
10558  if (FromQs.getObjCLifetime() != ToQs.getObjCLifetime()) {
10559  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_ownership)
10560  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10561  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << FromTy
10562  << FromQs.getObjCLifetime() << ToQs.getObjCLifetime()
10563  << (unsigned)isObjectArgument << I + 1;
10564  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10565  return;
10566  }
10567 
10568  if (FromQs.getObjCGCAttr() != ToQs.getObjCGCAttr()) {
10569  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_gc)
10570  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10571  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << FromTy
10572  << FromQs.getObjCGCAttr() << ToQs.getObjCGCAttr()
10573  << (unsigned)isObjectArgument << I + 1;
10574  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10575  return;
10576  }
10577 
10578  if (FromQs.hasUnaligned() != ToQs.hasUnaligned()) {
10579  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_unaligned)
10580  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10581  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << FromTy
10582  << FromQs.hasUnaligned() << I + 1;
10583  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10584  return;
10585  }
10586 
10587  unsigned CVR = FromQs.getCVRQualifiers() & ~ToQs.getCVRQualifiers();
10588  assert(CVR && "expected qualifiers mismatch");
10589 
10590  if (isObjectArgument) {
10591  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_cvr_this)
10592  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10593  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << FromTy
10594  << (CVR - 1);
10595  } else {
10596  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_cvr)
10597  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10598  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << FromTy
10599  << (CVR - 1) << I + 1;
10600  }
10601  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10602  return;
10603  }
10604 
10605  if (Conv.Bad.Kind == BadConversionSequence::lvalue_ref_to_rvalue ||
10606  Conv.Bad.Kind == BadConversionSequence::rvalue_ref_to_lvalue) {
10607  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_value_category)
10608  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10609  << (unsigned)isObjectArgument << I + 1
10610  << (Conv.Bad.Kind == BadConversionSequence::rvalue_ref_to_lvalue)
10611  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange());
10612  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10613  return;
10614  }
10615 
10616  // Special diagnostic for failure to convert an initializer list, since
10617  // telling the user that it has type void is not useful.
10618  if (FromExpr && isa<InitListExpr>(FromExpr)) {
10619  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_list_argument)
10620  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10621  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << FromTy
10622  << ToTy << (unsigned)isObjectArgument << I + 1
10623  << (Conv.Bad.Kind == BadConversionSequence::too_few_initializers ? 1
10624  : Conv.Bad.Kind == BadConversionSequence::too_many_initializers
10625  ? 2
10626  : 0);
10627  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10628  return;
10629  }
10630 
10631  // Diagnose references or pointers to incomplete types differently,
10632  // since it's far from impossible that the incompleteness triggered
10633  // the failure.
10634  QualType TempFromTy = FromTy.getNonReferenceType();
10635  if (const PointerType *PTy = TempFromTy->getAs<PointerType>())
10636  TempFromTy = PTy->getPointeeType();
10637  if (TempFromTy->isIncompleteType()) {
10638  // Emit the generic diagnostic and, optionally, add the hints to it.
10639  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_conv_incomplete)
10640  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10641  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << FromTy
10642  << ToTy << (unsigned)isObjectArgument << I + 1
10643  << (unsigned)(Cand->Fix.Kind);
10644 
10645  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10646  return;
10647  }
10648 
10649  // Diagnose base -> derived pointer conversions.
10650  unsigned BaseToDerivedConversion = 0;
10651  if (const PointerType *FromPtrTy = FromTy->getAs<PointerType>()) {
10652  if (const PointerType *ToPtrTy = ToTy->getAs<PointerType>()) {
10653  if (ToPtrTy->getPointeeType().isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(
10654  FromPtrTy->getPointeeType()) &&
10655  !FromPtrTy->getPointeeType()->isIncompleteType() &&
10656  !ToPtrTy->getPointeeType()->isIncompleteType() &&
10657  S.IsDerivedFrom(SourceLocation(), ToPtrTy->getPointeeType(),
10658  FromPtrTy->getPointeeType()))
10659  BaseToDerivedConversion = 1;
10660  }
10661  } else if (const ObjCObjectPointerType *FromPtrTy
10662  = FromTy->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
10663  if (const ObjCObjectPointerType *ToPtrTy
10664  = ToTy->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>())
10665  if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *FromIface = FromPtrTy->getInterfaceDecl())
10666  if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ToIface = ToPtrTy->getInterfaceDecl())
10667  if (ToPtrTy->getPointeeType().isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(
10668  FromPtrTy->getPointeeType()) &&
10669  FromIface->isSuperClassOf(ToIface))
10670  BaseToDerivedConversion = 2;
10671  } else if (const ReferenceType *ToRefTy = ToTy->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
10672  if (ToRefTy->getPointeeType().isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(FromTy) &&
10673  !FromTy->isIncompleteType() &&
10674  !ToRefTy->getPointeeType()->isIncompleteType() &&
10675  S.IsDerivedFrom(SourceLocation(), ToRefTy->getPointeeType(), FromTy)) {
10676  BaseToDerivedConversion = 3;
10677  }
10678  }
10679 
10680  if (BaseToDerivedConversion) {
10681  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_base_to_derived_conv)
10682  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10683  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange())
10684  << (BaseToDerivedConversion - 1) << FromTy << ToTy << I + 1;
10685  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10686  return;
10687  }
10688 
10689  if (isa<ObjCObjectPointerType>(CFromTy) &&
10690  isa<PointerType>(CToTy)) {
10691  Qualifiers FromQs = CFromTy.getQualifiers();
10692  Qualifiers ToQs = CToTy.getQualifiers();
10693  if (FromQs.getObjCLifetime() != ToQs.getObjCLifetime()) {
10694  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_arc_conv)
10695  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second
10696  << FnDesc << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange())
10697  << FromTy << ToTy << (unsigned)isObjectArgument << I + 1;
10698  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10699  return;
10700  }
10701  }
10702 
10703  if (TakingCandidateAddress &&
10704  !checkAddressOfCandidateIsAvailable(S, Cand->Function))
10705  return;
10706 
10707  // Emit the generic diagnostic and, optionally, add the hints to it.
10708  PartialDiagnostic FDiag = S.PDiag(diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_conv);
10709  FDiag << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
10710  << (FromExpr ? FromExpr->getSourceRange() : SourceRange()) << FromTy
10711  << ToTy << (unsigned)isObjectArgument << I + 1
10712  << (unsigned)(Cand->Fix.Kind);
10713 
10714  // If we can fix the conversion, suggest the FixIts.
10715  for (std::vector<FixItHint>::iterator HI = Cand->Fix.Hints.begin(),
10716  HE = Cand->Fix.Hints.end(); HI != HE; ++HI)
10717  FDiag << *HI;
10718  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), FDiag);
10719 
10720  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
10721 }
10722 
10723 /// Additional arity mismatch diagnosis specific to a function overload
10724 /// candidates. This is not covered by the more general DiagnoseArityMismatch()
10725 /// over a candidate in any candidate set.
10726 static bool CheckArityMismatch(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand,
10727  unsigned NumArgs) {
10728  FunctionDecl *Fn = Cand->Function;
10729  unsigned MinParams = Fn->getMinRequiredArguments();
10730 
10731  // With invalid overloaded operators, it's possible that we think we
10732  // have an arity mismatch when in fact it looks like we have the
10733  // right number of arguments, because only overloaded operators have
10734  // the weird behavior of overloading member and non-member functions.
10735  // Just don't report anything.
10736  if (Fn->isInvalidDecl() &&
10737  Fn->getDeclName().getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName)
10738  return true;
10739 
10740  if (NumArgs < MinParams) {
10741  assert((Cand->FailureKind == ovl_fail_too_few_arguments) ||
10742  (Cand->FailureKind == ovl_fail_bad_deduction &&
10743  Cand->DeductionFailure.Result == Sema::TDK_TooFewArguments));
10744  } else {
10745  assert((Cand->FailureKind == ovl_fail_too_many_arguments) ||
10746  (Cand->FailureKind == ovl_fail_bad_deduction &&
10747  Cand->DeductionFailure.Result == Sema::TDK_TooManyArguments));
10748  }
10749 
10750  return false;
10751 }
10752 
10753 /// General arity mismatch diagnosis over a candidate in a candidate set.
10754 static void DiagnoseArityMismatch(Sema &S, NamedDecl *Found, Decl *D,
10755  unsigned NumFormalArgs) {
10756  assert(isa<FunctionDecl>(D) &&
10757  "The templated declaration should at least be a function"
10758  " when diagnosing bad template argument deduction due to too many"
10759  " or too few arguments");
10760 
10761  FunctionDecl *Fn = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
10762 
10763  // TODO: treat calls to a missing default constructor as a special case
10764  const auto *FnTy = Fn->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
10765  unsigned MinParams = Fn->getMinRequiredArguments();
10766 
10767  // at least / at most / exactly
10768  unsigned mode, modeCount;
10769  if (NumFormalArgs < MinParams) {
10770  if (MinParams != FnTy->getNumParams() || FnTy->isVariadic() ||
10771  FnTy->isTemplateVariadic())
10772  mode = 0; // "at least"
10773  else
10774  mode = 2; // "exactly"
10775  modeCount = MinParams;
10776  } else {
10777  if (MinParams != FnTy->getNumParams())
10778  mode = 1; // "at most"
10779  else
10780  mode = 2; // "exactly"
10781  modeCount = FnTy->getNumParams();
10782  }
10783 
10784  std::string Description;
10785  std::pair<OverloadCandidateKind, OverloadCandidateSelect> FnKindPair =
10786  ClassifyOverloadCandidate(S, Found, Fn, CRK_None, Description);
10787 
10788  if (modeCount == 1 && Fn->getParamDecl(0)->getDeclName())
10789  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_arity_one)
10790  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second
10791  << Description << mode << Fn->getParamDecl(0) << NumFormalArgs;
10792  else
10793  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_arity)
10794  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second
10795  << Description << mode << modeCount << NumFormalArgs;
10796 
10797  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
10798 }
10799 
10800 /// Arity mismatch diagnosis specific to a function overload candidate.
10801 static void DiagnoseArityMismatch(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand,
10802  unsigned NumFormalArgs) {
10803  if (!CheckArityMismatch(S, Cand, NumFormalArgs))
10804  DiagnoseArityMismatch(S, Cand->FoundDecl, Cand->Function, NumFormalArgs);
10805 }
10806 
10807 static TemplateDecl *getDescribedTemplate(Decl *Templated) {
10808  if (TemplateDecl *TD = Templated->getDescribedTemplate())
10809  return TD;
10810  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported: Getting the described template declaration"
10811  " for bad deduction diagnosis");
10812 }
10813 
10814 /// Diagnose a failed template-argument deduction.
10815 static void DiagnoseBadDeduction(Sema &S, NamedDecl *Found, Decl *Templated,
10816  DeductionFailureInfo &DeductionFailure,
10817  unsigned NumArgs,
10818  bool TakingCandidateAddress) {
10819  TemplateParameter Param = DeductionFailure.getTemplateParameter();
10820  NamedDecl *ParamD;
10821  (ParamD = Param.dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl*>()) ||
10822  (ParamD = Param.dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl*>()) ||
10823  (ParamD = Param.dyn_cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl*>());
10824  switch (DeductionFailure.Result) {
10825  case Sema::TDK_Success:
10826  llvm_unreachable("TDK_success while diagnosing bad deduction");
10827 
10828  case Sema::TDK_Incomplete: {
10829  assert(ParamD && "no parameter found for incomplete deduction result");
10830  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10831  diag::note_ovl_candidate_incomplete_deduction)
10832  << ParamD->getDeclName();
10833  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
10834  return;
10835  }
10836 
10837  case Sema::TDK_IncompletePack: {
10838  assert(ParamD && "no parameter found for incomplete deduction result");
10839  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10840  diag::note_ovl_candidate_incomplete_deduction_pack)
10841  << ParamD->getDeclName()
10842  << (DeductionFailure.getFirstArg()->pack_size() + 1)
10843  << *DeductionFailure.getFirstArg();
10844  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
10845  return;
10846  }
10847 
10848  case Sema::TDK_Underqualified: {
10849  assert(ParamD && "no parameter found for bad qualifiers deduction result");
10850  TemplateTypeParmDecl *TParam = cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(ParamD);
10851 
10852  QualType Param = DeductionFailure.getFirstArg()->getAsType();
10853 
10854  // Param will have been canonicalized, but it should just be a
10855  // qualified version of ParamD, so move the qualifiers to that.
10856  QualifierCollector Qs;
10857  Qs.strip(Param);
10858  QualType NonCanonParam = Qs.apply(S.Context, TParam->getTypeForDecl());
10859  assert(S.Context.hasSameType(Param, NonCanonParam));
10860 
10861  // Arg has also been canonicalized, but there's nothing we can do
10862  // about that. It also doesn't matter as much, because it won't
10863  // have any template parameters in it (because deduction isn't
10864  // done on dependent types).
10865  QualType Arg = DeductionFailure.getSecondArg()->getAsType();
10866 
10867  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_underqualified)
10868  << ParamD->getDeclName() << Arg << NonCanonParam;
10869  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
10870  return;
10871  }
10872 
10873  case Sema::TDK_Inconsistent: {
10874  assert(ParamD && "no parameter found for inconsistent deduction result");
10875  int which = 0;
10876  if (isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(ParamD))
10877  which = 0;
10878  else if (isa<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(ParamD)) {
10879  // Deduction might have failed because we deduced arguments of two
10880  // different types for a non-type template parameter.
10881  // FIXME: Use a different TDK value for this.
10882  QualType T1 =
10883  DeductionFailure.getFirstArg()->getNonTypeTemplateArgumentType();
10884  QualType T2 =
10885  DeductionFailure.getSecondArg()->getNonTypeTemplateArgumentType();
10886  if (!T1.isNull() && !T2.isNull() && !S.Context.hasSameType(T1, T2)) {
10887  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10888  diag::note_ovl_candidate_inconsistent_deduction_types)
10889  << ParamD->getDeclName() << *DeductionFailure.getFirstArg() << T1
10890  << *DeductionFailure.getSecondArg() << T2;
10891  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
10892  return;
10893  }
10894 
10895  which = 1;
10896  } else {
10897  which = 2;
10898  }
10899 
10900  // Tweak the diagnostic if the problem is that we deduced packs of
10901  // different arities. We'll print the actual packs anyway in case that
10902  // includes additional useful information.
10903  if (DeductionFailure.getFirstArg()->getKind() == TemplateArgument::Pack &&
10904  DeductionFailure.getSecondArg()->getKind() == TemplateArgument::Pack &&
10905  DeductionFailure.getFirstArg()->pack_size() !=
10906  DeductionFailure.getSecondArg()->pack_size()) {
10907  which = 3;
10908  }
10909 
10910  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10911  diag::note_ovl_candidate_inconsistent_deduction)
10912  << which << ParamD->getDeclName() << *DeductionFailure.getFirstArg()
10913  << *DeductionFailure.getSecondArg();
10914  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
10915  return;
10916  }
10917 
10918  case Sema::TDK_InvalidExplicitArguments:
10919  assert(ParamD && "no parameter found for invalid explicit arguments");
10920  if (ParamD->getDeclName())
10921  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10922  diag::note_ovl_candidate_explicit_arg_mismatch_named)
10923  << ParamD->getDeclName();
10924  else {
10925  int index = 0;
10926  if (TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(ParamD))
10927  index = TTP->getIndex();
10928  else if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *NTTP
10929  = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(ParamD))
10930  index = NTTP->getIndex();
10931  else
10932  index = cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(ParamD)->getIndex();
10933  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10934  diag::note_ovl_candidate_explicit_arg_mismatch_unnamed)
10935  << (index + 1);
10936  }
10937  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
10938  return;
10939 
10940  case Sema::TDK_ConstraintsNotSatisfied: {
10941  // Format the template argument list into the argument string.
10942  SmallString<128> TemplateArgString;
10943  TemplateArgumentList *Args = DeductionFailure.getTemplateArgumentList();
10944  TemplateArgString = " ";
10945  TemplateArgString += S.getTemplateArgumentBindingsText(
10946  getDescribedTemplate(Templated)->getTemplateParameters(), *Args);
10947  if (TemplateArgString.size() == 1)
10948  TemplateArgString.clear();
10949  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10950  diag::note_ovl_candidate_unsatisfied_constraints)
10951  << TemplateArgString;
10952 
10953  S.DiagnoseUnsatisfiedConstraint(
10954  static_cast<CNSInfo*>(DeductionFailure.Data)->Satisfaction);
10955  return;
10956  }
10957  case Sema::TDK_TooManyArguments:
10958  case Sema::TDK_TooFewArguments:
10959  DiagnoseArityMismatch(S, Found, Templated, NumArgs);
10960  return;
10961 
10962  case Sema::TDK_InstantiationDepth:
10963  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10964  diag::note_ovl_candidate_instantiation_depth);
10965  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
10966  return;
10967 
10968  case Sema::TDK_SubstitutionFailure: {
10969  // Format the template argument list into the argument string.
10970  SmallString<128> TemplateArgString;
10971  if (TemplateArgumentList *Args =
10972  DeductionFailure.getTemplateArgumentList()) {
10973  TemplateArgString = " ";
10974  TemplateArgString += S.getTemplateArgumentBindingsText(
10975  getDescribedTemplate(Templated)->getTemplateParameters(), *Args);
10976  if (TemplateArgString.size() == 1)
10977  TemplateArgString.clear();
10978  }
10979 
10980  // If this candidate was disabled by enable_if, say so.
10981  PartialDiagnosticAt *PDiag = DeductionFailure.getSFINAEDiagnostic();
10982  if (PDiag && PDiag->second.getDiagID() ==
10983  diag::err_typename_nested_not_found_enable_if) {
10984  // FIXME: Use the source range of the condition, and the fully-qualified
10985  // name of the enable_if template. These are both present in PDiag.
10986  S.Diag(PDiag->first, diag::note_ovl_candidate_disabled_by_enable_if)
10987  << "'enable_if'" << TemplateArgString;
10988  return;
10989  }
10990 
10991  // We found a specific requirement that disabled the enable_if.
10992  if (PDiag && PDiag->second.getDiagID() ==
10993  diag::err_typename_nested_not_found_requirement) {
10994  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
10995  diag::note_ovl_candidate_disabled_by_requirement)
10996  << PDiag->second.getStringArg(0) << TemplateArgString;
10997  return;
10998  }
10999 
11000  // Format the SFINAE diagnostic into the argument string.
11001  // FIXME: Add a general mechanism to include a PartialDiagnostic *'s
11002  // formatted message in another diagnostic.
11003  SmallString<128> SFINAEArgString;
11004  SourceRange R;
11005  if (PDiag) {
11006  SFINAEArgString = ": ";
11007  R = SourceRange(PDiag->first, PDiag->first);
11008  PDiag->second.EmitToString(S.getDiagnostics(), SFINAEArgString);
11009  }
11010 
11011  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
11012  diag::note_ovl_candidate_substitution_failure)
11013  << TemplateArgString << SFINAEArgString << R;
11014  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
11015  return;
11016  }
11017 
11018  case Sema::TDK_DeducedMismatch:
11019  case Sema::TDK_DeducedMismatchNested: {
11020  // Format the template argument list into the argument string.
11021  SmallString<128> TemplateArgString;
11022  if (TemplateArgumentList *Args =
11023  DeductionFailure.getTemplateArgumentList()) {
11024  TemplateArgString = " ";
11025  TemplateArgString += S.getTemplateArgumentBindingsText(
11026  getDescribedTemplate(Templated)->getTemplateParameters(), *Args);
11027  if (TemplateArgString.size() == 1)
11028  TemplateArgString.clear();
11029  }
11030 
11031  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_deduced_mismatch)
11032  << (*DeductionFailure.getCallArgIndex() + 1)
11033  << *DeductionFailure.getFirstArg() << *DeductionFailure.getSecondArg()
11034  << TemplateArgString
11035  << (DeductionFailure.Result == Sema::TDK_DeducedMismatchNested);
11036  break;
11037  }
11038 
11039  case Sema::TDK_NonDeducedMismatch: {
11040  // FIXME: Provide a source location to indicate what we couldn't match.
11041  TemplateArgument FirstTA = *DeductionFailure.getFirstArg();
11042  TemplateArgument SecondTA = *DeductionFailure.getSecondArg();
11043  if (FirstTA.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Template &&
11044  SecondTA.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Template) {
11045  TemplateName FirstTN = FirstTA.getAsTemplate();
11046  TemplateName SecondTN = SecondTA.getAsTemplate();
11047  if (FirstTN.getKind() == TemplateName::Template &&
11048  SecondTN.getKind() == TemplateName::Template) {
11049  if (FirstTN.getAsTemplateDecl()->getName() ==
11050  SecondTN.getAsTemplateDecl()->getName()) {
11051  // FIXME: This fixes a bad diagnostic where both templates are named
11052  // the same. This particular case is a bit difficult since:
11053  // 1) It is passed as a string to the diagnostic printer.
11054  // 2) The diagnostic printer only attempts to find a better
11055  // name for types, not decls.
11056  // Ideally, this should folded into the diagnostic printer.
11057  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
11058  diag::note_ovl_candidate_non_deduced_mismatch_qualified)
11059  << FirstTN.getAsTemplateDecl() << SecondTN.getAsTemplateDecl();
11060  return;
11061  }
11062  }
11063  }
11064 
11065  if (TakingCandidateAddress && isa<FunctionDecl>(Templated) &&
11066  !checkAddressOfCandidateIsAvailable(S, cast<FunctionDecl>(Templated)))
11067  return;
11068 
11069  // FIXME: For generic lambda parameters, check if the function is a lambda
11070  // call operator, and if so, emit a prettier and more informative
11071  // diagnostic that mentions 'auto' and lambda in addition to
11072  // (or instead of?) the canonical template type parameters.
11073  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
11074  diag::note_ovl_candidate_non_deduced_mismatch)
11075  << FirstTA << SecondTA;
11076  return;
11077  }
11078  // TODO: diagnose these individually, then kill off
11079  // note_ovl_candidate_bad_deduction, which is uselessly vague.
11080  case Sema::TDK_MiscellaneousDeductionFailure:
11081  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_deduction);
11082  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Found);
11083  return;
11084  case Sema::TDK_CUDATargetMismatch:
11085  S.Diag(Templated->getLocation(),
11086  diag::note_cuda_ovl_candidate_target_mismatch);
11087  return;
11088  }
11089 }
11090 
11091 /// Diagnose a failed template-argument deduction, for function calls.
11092 static void DiagnoseBadDeduction(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand,
11093  unsigned NumArgs,
11094  bool TakingCandidateAddress) {
11095  unsigned TDK = Cand->DeductionFailure.Result;
11096  if (TDK == Sema::TDK_TooFewArguments || TDK == Sema::TDK_TooManyArguments) {
11097  if (CheckArityMismatch(S, Cand, NumArgs))
11098  return;
11099  }
11100  DiagnoseBadDeduction(S, Cand->FoundDecl, Cand->Function, // pattern
11101  Cand->DeductionFailure, NumArgs, TakingCandidateAddress);
11102 }
11103 
11104 /// CUDA: diagnose an invalid call across targets.
11105 static void DiagnoseBadTarget(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
11106  FunctionDecl *Caller = S.getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true);
11107  FunctionDecl *Callee = Cand->Function;
11108 
11109  Sema::CUDAFunctionTarget CallerTarget = S.IdentifyCUDATarget(Caller),
11110  CalleeTarget = S.IdentifyCUDATarget(Callee);
11111 
11112  std::string FnDesc;
11113  std::pair<OverloadCandidateKind, OverloadCandidateSelect> FnKindPair =
11114  ClassifyOverloadCandidate(S, Cand->FoundDecl, Callee,
11115  Cand->getRewriteKind(), FnDesc);
11116 
11117  S.Diag(Callee->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_bad_target)
11118  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)ocs_non_template
11119  << FnDesc /* Ignored */
11120  << CalleeTarget << CallerTarget;
11121 
11122  // This could be an implicit constructor for which we could not infer the
11123  // target due to a collsion. Diagnose that case.
11124  CXXMethodDecl *Meth = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Callee);
11125  if (Meth != nullptr && Meth->isImplicit()) {
11126  CXXRecordDecl *ParentClass = Meth->getParent();
11127  Sema::CXXSpecialMember CSM;
11128 
11129  switch (FnKindPair.first) {
11130  default:
11131  return;
11132  case oc_implicit_default_constructor:
11133  CSM = Sema::CXXDefaultConstructor;
11134  break;
11135  case oc_implicit_copy_constructor:
11136  CSM = Sema::CXXCopyConstructor;
11137  break;
11138  case oc_implicit_move_constructor:
11139  CSM = Sema::CXXMoveConstructor;
11140  break;
11141  case oc_implicit_copy_assignment:
11142  CSM = Sema::CXXCopyAssignment;
11143  break;
11144  case oc_implicit_move_assignment:
11145  CSM = Sema::CXXMoveAssignment;
11146  break;
11147  };
11148 
11149  bool ConstRHS = false;
11150  if (Meth->getNumParams()) {
11151  if (const ReferenceType *RT =
11152  Meth->getParamDecl(0)->getType()->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
11153  ConstRHS = RT->getPointeeType().isConstQualified();
11154  }
11155  }
11156 
11157  S.inferCUDATargetForImplicitSpecialMember(ParentClass, CSM, Meth,
11158  /* ConstRHS */ ConstRHS,
11159  /* Diagnose */ true);
11160  }
11161 }
11162 
11163 static void DiagnoseFailedEnableIfAttr(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
11164  FunctionDecl *Callee = Cand->Function;
11165  EnableIfAttr *Attr = static_cast<EnableIfAttr*>(Cand->DeductionFailure.Data);
11166 
11167  S.Diag(Callee->getLocation(),
11168  diag::note_ovl_candidate_disabled_by_function_cond_attr)
11169  << Attr->getCond()->getSourceRange() << Attr->getMessage();
11170 }
11171 
11172 static void DiagnoseFailedExplicitSpec(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
11173  ExplicitSpecifier ES = ExplicitSpecifier::getFromDecl(Cand->Function);
11174  assert(ES.isExplicit() && "not an explicit candidate");
11175 
11176  unsigned Kind;
11177  switch (Cand->Function->getDeclKind()) {
11178  case Decl::Kind::CXXConstructor:
11179  Kind = 0;
11180  break;
11181  case Decl::Kind::CXXConversion:
11182  Kind = 1;
11183  break;
11184  case Decl::Kind::CXXDeductionGuide:
11185  Kind = Cand->Function->isImplicit() ? 0 : 2;
11186  break;
11187  default:
11188  llvm_unreachable("invalid Decl");
11189  }
11190 
11191  // Note the location of the first (in-class) declaration; a redeclaration
11192  // (particularly an out-of-class definition) will typically lack the
11193  // 'explicit' specifier.
11194  // FIXME: This is probably a good thing to do for all 'candidate' notes.
11195  FunctionDecl *First = Cand->Function->getFirstDecl();
11196  if (FunctionDecl *Pattern = First->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
11197  First = Pattern->getFirstDecl();
11198 
11199  S.Diag(First->getLocation(),
11200  diag::note_ovl_candidate_explicit)
11201  << Kind << (ES.getExpr() ? 1 : 0)
11202  << (ES.getExpr() ? ES.getExpr()->getSourceRange() : SourceRange());
11203 }
11204 
11205 /// Generates a 'note' diagnostic for an overload candidate. We've
11206 /// already generated a primary error at the call site.
11207 ///
11208 /// It really does need to be a single diagnostic with its caret
11209 /// pointed at the candidate declaration. Yes, this creates some
11210 /// major challenges of technical writing. Yes, this makes pointing
11211 /// out problems with specific arguments quite awkward. It's still
11212 /// better than generating twenty screens of text for every failed
11213 /// overload.
11214 ///
11215 /// It would be great to be able to express per-candidate problems
11216 /// more richly for those diagnostic clients that cared, but we'd
11217 /// still have to be just as careful with the default diagnostics.
11218 /// \param CtorDestAS Addr space of object being constructed (for ctor
11219 /// candidates only).
11220 static void NoteFunctionCandidate(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand,
11221  unsigned NumArgs,
11222  bool TakingCandidateAddress,
11223  LangAS CtorDestAS = LangAS::Default) {
11224  FunctionDecl *Fn = Cand->Function;
11225  if (shouldSkipNotingLambdaConversionDecl(Fn))
11226  return;
11227 
11228  // Note deleted candidates, but only if they're viable.
11229  if (Cand->Viable) {
11230  if (Fn->isDeleted()) {
11231  std::string FnDesc;
11232  std::pair<OverloadCandidateKind, OverloadCandidateSelect> FnKindPair =
11233  ClassifyOverloadCandidate(S, Cand->FoundDecl, Fn,
11234  Cand->getRewriteKind(), FnDesc);
11235 
11236  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_deleted)
11237  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)FnKindPair.second << FnDesc
11238  << (Fn->isDeleted() ? (Fn->isDeletedAsWritten() ? 1 : 2) : 0);
11239  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
11240  return;
11241  }
11242 
11243  // We don't really have anything else to say about viable candidates.
11244  S.NoteOverloadCandidate(Cand->FoundDecl, Fn, Cand->getRewriteKind());
11245  return;
11246  }
11247 
11248  switch (Cand->FailureKind) {
11249  case ovl_fail_too_many_arguments:
11250  case ovl_fail_too_few_arguments:
11251  return DiagnoseArityMismatch(S, Cand, NumArgs);
11252 
11253  case ovl_fail_bad_deduction:
11254  return DiagnoseBadDeduction(S, Cand, NumArgs,
11255  TakingCandidateAddress);
11256 
11257  case ovl_fail_illegal_constructor: {
11258  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_candidate_illegal_constructor)
11259  << (Fn->getPrimaryTemplate() ? 1 : 0);
11260  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
11261  return;
11262  }
11263 
11264  case ovl_fail_object_addrspace_mismatch: {
11265  Qualifiers QualsForPrinting;
11266  QualsForPrinting.setAddressSpace(CtorDestAS);
11267  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(),
11268  diag::note_ovl_candidate_illegal_constructor_adrspace_mismatch)
11269  << QualsForPrinting;
11270  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
11271  return;
11272  }
11273 
11274  case ovl_fail_trivial_conversion:
11275  case ovl_fail_bad_final_conversion:
11276  case ovl_fail_final_conversion_not_exact:
11277  return S.NoteOverloadCandidate(Cand->FoundDecl, Fn, Cand->getRewriteKind());
11278 
11279  case ovl_fail_bad_conversion: {
11280  unsigned I = (Cand->IgnoreObjectArgument ? 1 : 0);
11281  for (unsigned N = Cand->Conversions.size(); I != N; ++I)
11282  if (Cand->Conversions[I].isBad())
11283  return DiagnoseBadConversion(S, Cand, I, TakingCandidateAddress);
11284 
11285  // FIXME: this currently happens when we're called from SemaInit
11286  // when user-conversion overload fails. Figure out how to handle
11287  // those conditions and diagnose them well.
11288  return S.NoteOverloadCandidate(Cand->FoundDecl, Fn, Cand->getRewriteKind());
11289  }
11290 
11291  case ovl_fail_bad_target:
11292  return DiagnoseBadTarget(S, Cand);
11293 
11294  case ovl_fail_enable_if:
11295  return DiagnoseFailedEnableIfAttr(S, Cand);
11296 
11297  case ovl_fail_explicit:
11298  return DiagnoseFailedExplicitSpec(S, Cand);
11299 
11300  case ovl_fail_inhctor_slice:
11301  // It's generally not interesting to note copy/move constructors here.
11302  if (cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Fn)->isCopyOrMoveConstructor())
11303  return;
11304  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(),
11305  diag::note_ovl_candidate_inherited_constructor_slice)
11306  << (Fn->getPrimaryTemplate() ? 1 : 0)
11307  << Fn->getParamDecl(0)->getType()->isRValueReferenceType();
11308  MaybeEmitInheritedConstructorNote(S, Cand->FoundDecl);
11309  return;
11310 
11311  case ovl_fail_addr_not_available: {
11312  bool Available = checkAddressOfCandidateIsAvailable(S, Cand->Function);
11313  (void)Available;
11314  assert(!Available);
11315  break;
11316  }
11317  case ovl_non_default_multiversion_function:
11318  // Do nothing, these should simply be ignored.
11319  break;
11320 
11321  case ovl_fail_constraints_not_satisfied: {
11322  std::string FnDesc;
11323  std::pair<OverloadCandidateKind, OverloadCandidateSelect> FnKindPair =
11324  ClassifyOverloadCandidate(S, Cand->FoundDecl, Fn,
11325  Cand->getRewriteKind(), FnDesc);
11326 
11327  S.Diag(Fn->getLocation(),
11328  diag::note_ovl_candidate_constraints_not_satisfied)
11329  << (unsigned)FnKindPair.first << (unsigned)ocs_non_template
11330  << FnDesc /* Ignored */;
11331  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
11332  if (S.CheckFunctionConstraints(Fn, Satisfaction))
11333  break;
11334  S.DiagnoseUnsatisfiedConstraint(Satisfaction);
11335  }
11336  }
11337 }
11338 
11339 static void NoteSurrogateCandidate(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
11340  if (shouldSkipNotingLambdaConversionDecl(Cand->Surrogate))
11341  return;
11342 
11343  // Desugar the type of the surrogate down to a function type,
11344  // retaining as many typedefs as possible while still showing
11345  // the function type (and, therefore, its parameter types).
11346  QualType FnType = Cand->Surrogate->getConversionType();
11347  bool isLValueReference = false;
11348  bool isRValueReference = false;
11349  bool isPointer = false;
11350  if (const LValueReferenceType *FnTypeRef =
11351  FnType->getAs<LValueReferenceType>()) {
11352  FnType = FnTypeRef->getPointeeType();
11353  isLValueReference = true;
11354  } else if (const RValueReferenceType *FnTypeRef =
11355  FnType->getAs<RValueReferenceType>()) {
11356  FnType = FnTypeRef->getPointeeType();
11357  isRValueReference = true;
11358  }
11359  if (const PointerType *FnTypePtr = FnType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
11360  FnType = FnTypePtr->getPointeeType();
11361  isPointer = true;
11362  }
11363  // Desugar down to a function type.
11364  FnType = QualType(FnType->getAs<FunctionType>(), 0);
11365  // Reconstruct the pointer/reference as appropriate.
11366  if (isPointer) FnType = S.Context.getPointerType(FnType);
11367  if (isRValueReference) FnType = S.Context.getRValueReferenceType(FnType);
11368  if (isLValueReference) FnType = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(FnType);
11369 
11370  S.Diag(Cand->Surrogate->getLocation(), diag::note_ovl_surrogate_cand)
11371  << FnType;
11372 }
11373 
11374 static void NoteBuiltinOperatorCandidate(Sema &S, StringRef Opc,
11375  SourceLocation OpLoc,
11376  OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
11377  assert(Cand->Conversions.size() <= 2 && "builtin operator is not binary");
11378  std::string TypeStr("operator");
11379  TypeStr += Opc;
11380  TypeStr += "(";
11381  TypeStr += Cand->BuiltinParamTypes[0].getAsString();
11382  if (Cand->Conversions.size() == 1) {
11383  TypeStr += ")";
11384  S.Diag(OpLoc, diag::note_ovl_builtin_candidate) << TypeStr;
11385  } else {
11386  TypeStr += ", ";
11387  TypeStr += Cand->BuiltinParamTypes[1].getAsString();
11388  TypeStr += ")";
11389  S.Diag(OpLoc, diag::note_ovl_builtin_candidate) << TypeStr;
11390  }
11391 }
11392 
11393 static void NoteAmbiguousUserConversions(Sema &S, SourceLocation OpLoc,
11394  OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
11395  for (const ImplicitConversionSequence &ICS : Cand->Conversions) {
11396  if (ICS.isBad()) break; // all meaningless after first invalid
11397  if (!ICS.isAmbiguous()) continue;
11398 
11399  ICS.DiagnoseAmbiguousConversion(
11400  S, OpLoc, S.PDiag(diag::note_ambiguous_type_conversion));
11401  }
11402 }
11403 
11404 static SourceLocation GetLocationForCandidate(const OverloadCandidate *Cand) {
11405  if (Cand->Function)
11406  return Cand->Function->getLocation();
11407  if (Cand->IsSurrogate)
11408  return Cand->Surrogate->getLocation();
11409  return SourceLocation();
11410 }
11411 
11412 static unsigned RankDeductionFailure(const DeductionFailureInfo &DFI) {
11413  switch ((Sema::TemplateDeductionResult)DFI.Result) {
11414  case Sema::TDK_Success:
11415  case Sema::TDK_NonDependentConversionFailure:
11416  llvm_unreachable("non-deduction failure while diagnosing bad deduction");
11417 
11418  case Sema::TDK_Invalid:
11419  case Sema::TDK_Incomplete:
11420  case Sema::TDK_IncompletePack:
11421  return 1;
11422 
11423  case Sema::TDK_Underqualified:
11424  case Sema::TDK_Inconsistent:
11425  return 2;
11426 
11427  case Sema::TDK_SubstitutionFailure:
11428  case Sema::TDK_DeducedMismatch:
11429  case Sema::TDK_ConstraintsNotSatisfied:
11430  case Sema::TDK_DeducedMismatchNested:
11431  case Sema::TDK_NonDeducedMismatch:
11432  case Sema::TDK_MiscellaneousDeductionFailure:
11433  case Sema::TDK_CUDATargetMismatch:
11434  return 3;
11435 
11436  case Sema::TDK_InstantiationDepth:
11437  return 4;
11438 
11439  case Sema::TDK_InvalidExplicitArguments:
11440  return 5;
11441 
11442  case Sema::TDK_TooManyArguments:
11443  case Sema::TDK_TooFewArguments:
11444  return 6;
11445  }
11446  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled deduction result");
11447 }
11448 
11449 namespace {
11450 struct CompareOverloadCandidatesForDisplay {
11451  Sema &S;
11452  SourceLocation Loc;
11453  size_t NumArgs;
11454  OverloadCandidateSet::CandidateSetKind CSK;
11455 
11456  CompareOverloadCandidatesForDisplay(
11457  Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc, size_t NArgs,
11458  OverloadCandidateSet::CandidateSetKind CSK)
11459  : S(S), NumArgs(NArgs), CSK(CSK) {}
11460 
11461  OverloadFailureKind EffectiveFailureKind(const OverloadCandidate *C) const {
11462  // If there are too many or too few arguments, that's the high-order bit we
11463  // want to sort by, even if the immediate failure kind was something else.
11464  if (C->FailureKind == ovl_fail_too_many_arguments ||
11465  C->FailureKind == ovl_fail_too_few_arguments)
11466  return static_cast<OverloadFailureKind>(C->FailureKind);
11467 
11468  if (C->Function) {
11469  if (NumArgs > C->Function->getNumParams() && !C->Function->isVariadic())
11470  return ovl_fail_too_many_arguments;
11471  if (NumArgs < C->Function->getMinRequiredArguments())
11472  return ovl_fail_too_few_arguments;
11473  }
11474 
11475  return static_cast<OverloadFailureKind>(C->FailureKind);
11476  }
11477 
11478  bool operator()(const OverloadCandidate *L,
11479  const OverloadCandidate *R) {
11480  // Fast-path this check.
11481  if (L == R) return false;
11482 
11483  // Order first by viability.
11484  if (L->Viable) {
11485  if (!R->Viable) return true;
11486 
11487  // TODO: introduce a tri-valued comparison for overload
11488  // candidates. Would be more worthwhile if we had a sort
11489  // that could exploit it.
11490  if (isBetterOverloadCandidate(S, *L, *R, SourceLocation(), CSK))
11491  return true;
11492  if (isBetterOverloadCandidate(S, *R, *L, SourceLocation(), CSK))
11493  return false;
11494  } else if (R->Viable)
11495  return false;
11496 
11497  assert(L->Viable == R->Viable);
11498 
11499  // Criteria by which we can sort non-viable candidates:
11500  if (!L->Viable) {
11501  OverloadFailureKind LFailureKind = EffectiveFailureKind(L);
11502  OverloadFailureKind RFailureKind = EffectiveFailureKind(R);
11503 
11504  // 1. Arity mismatches come after other candidates.
11505  if (LFailureKind == ovl_fail_too_many_arguments ||
11506  LFailureKind == ovl_fail_too_few_arguments) {
11507  if (RFailureKind == ovl_fail_too_many_arguments ||
11508  RFailureKind == ovl_fail_too_few_arguments) {
11509  int LDist = std::abs((int)L->getNumParams() - (int)NumArgs);
11510  int RDist = std::abs((int)R->getNumParams() - (int)NumArgs);
11511  if (LDist == RDist) {
11512  if (LFailureKind == RFailureKind)
11513  // Sort non-surrogates before surrogates.
11514  return !L->IsSurrogate && R->IsSurrogate;
11515  // Sort candidates requiring fewer parameters than there were
11516  // arguments given after candidates requiring more parameters
11517  // than there were arguments given.
11518  return LFailureKind == ovl_fail_too_many_arguments;
11519  }
11520  return LDist < RDist;
11521  }
11522  return false;
11523  }
11524  if (RFailureKind == ovl_fail_too_many_arguments ||
11525  RFailureKind == ovl_fail_too_few_arguments)
11526  return true;
11527 
11528  // 2. Bad conversions come first and are ordered by the number
11529  // of bad conversions and quality of good conversions.
11530  if (LFailureKind == ovl_fail_bad_conversion) {
11531  if (RFailureKind != ovl_fail_bad_conversion)
11532  return true;
11533 
11534  // The conversion that can be fixed with a smaller number of changes,
11535  // comes first.
11536  unsigned numLFixes = L->Fix.NumConversionsFixed;
11537  unsigned numRFixes = R->Fix.NumConversionsFixed;
11538  numLFixes = (numLFixes == 0) ? UINT_MAX : numLFixes;
11539  numRFixes = (numRFixes == 0) ? UINT_MAX : numRFixes;
11540  if (numLFixes != numRFixes) {
11541  return numLFixes < numRFixes;
11542  }
11543 
11544  // If there's any ordering between the defined conversions...
11545  // FIXME: this might not be transitive.
11546  assert(L->Conversions.size() == R->Conversions.size());
11547 
11548  int leftBetter = 0;
11549  unsigned I = (L->IgnoreObjectArgument || R->IgnoreObjectArgument);
11550  for (unsigned E = L->Conversions.size(); I != E; ++I) {
11551  switch (CompareImplicitConversionSequences(S, Loc,
11552  L->Conversions[I],
11553  R->Conversions[I])) {
11554  case ImplicitConversionSequence::Better:
11555  leftBetter++;
11556  break;
11557 
11558  case ImplicitConversionSequence::Worse:
11559  leftBetter--;
11560  break;
11561 
11562  case ImplicitConversionSequence::Indistinguishable:
11563  break;
11564  }
11565  }
11566  if (leftBetter > 0) return true;
11567  if (leftBetter < 0) return false;
11568 
11569  } else if (RFailureKind == ovl_fail_bad_conversion)
11570  return false;
11571 
11572  if (LFailureKind == ovl_fail_bad_deduction) {
11573  if (RFailureKind != ovl_fail_bad_deduction)
11574  return true;
11575 
11576  if (L->DeductionFailure.Result != R->DeductionFailure.Result)
11577  return RankDeductionFailure(L->DeductionFailure)
11578  < RankDeductionFailure(R->DeductionFailure);
11579  } else if (RFailureKind == ovl_fail_bad_deduction)
11580  return false;
11581 
11582  // TODO: others?
11583  }
11584 
11585  // Sort everything else by location.
11586  SourceLocation LLoc = GetLocationForCandidate(L);
11587  SourceLocation RLoc = GetLocationForCandidate(R);
11588 
11589  // Put candidates without locations (e.g. builtins) at the end.
11590  if (LLoc.isInvalid()) return false;
11591  if (RLoc.isInvalid()) return true;
11592 
11593  return S.SourceMgr.isBeforeInTranslationUnit(LLoc, RLoc);
11594  }
11595 };
11596 }
11597 
11598 /// CompleteNonViableCandidate - Normally, overload resolution only
11599 /// computes up to the first bad conversion. Produces the FixIt set if
11600 /// possible.
11601 static void
11602 CompleteNonViableCandidate(Sema &S, OverloadCandidate *Cand,
11603  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
11604  OverloadCandidateSet::CandidateSetKind CSK) {
11605  assert(!Cand->Viable);
11606 
11607  // Don't do anything on failures other than bad conversion.
11608  if (Cand->FailureKind != ovl_fail_bad_conversion)
11609  return;
11610 
11611  // We only want the FixIts if all the arguments can be corrected.
11612  bool Unfixable = false;
11613  // Use a implicit copy initialization to check conversion fixes.
11614  Cand->Fix.setConversionChecker(TryCopyInitialization);
11615 
11616  // Attempt to fix the bad conversion.
11617  unsigned ConvCount = Cand->Conversions.size();
11618  for (unsigned ConvIdx = (Cand->IgnoreObjectArgument ? 1 : 0); /**/;
11619  ++ConvIdx) {
11620  assert(ConvIdx != ConvCount && "no bad conversion in candidate");
11621  if (Cand->Conversions[ConvIdx].isInitialized() &&
11622  Cand->Conversions[ConvIdx].isBad()) {
11623  Unfixable = !Cand->TryToFixBadConversion(ConvIdx, S);
11624  break;
11625  }
11626  }
11627 
11628  // FIXME: this should probably be preserved from the overload
11629  // operation somehow.
11630  bool SuppressUserConversions = false;
11631 
11632  unsigned ConvIdx = 0;
11633  unsigned ArgIdx = 0;
11634  ArrayRef<QualType> ParamTypes;
11635  bool Reversed = Cand->isReversed();
11636 
11637  if (Cand->IsSurrogate) {
11638  QualType ConvType
11639  = Cand->Surrogate->getConversionType().getNonReferenceType();
11640  if (const PointerType *ConvPtrType = ConvType->getAs<PointerType>())
11641  ConvType = ConvPtrType->getPointeeType();
11642  ParamTypes = ConvType->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getParamTypes();
11643  // Conversion 0 is 'this', which doesn't have a corresponding parameter.
11644  ConvIdx = 1;
11645  } else if (Cand->Function) {
11646  ParamTypes =
11647  Cand->Function->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getParamTypes();
11648  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(Cand->Function) &&
11649  !isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Cand->Function) && !Reversed) {
11650  // Conversion 0 is 'this', which doesn't have a corresponding parameter.
11651  ConvIdx = 1;
11652  if (CSK == OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator &&
11653  Cand->Function->getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_Call &&
11654  Cand->Function->getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() !=
11655  OO_Subscript)
11656  // Argument 0 is 'this', which doesn't have a corresponding parameter.
11657  ArgIdx = 1;
11658  }
11659  } else {
11660  // Builtin operator.
11661  assert(ConvCount <= 3);
11662  ParamTypes = Cand->BuiltinParamTypes;
11663  }
11664 
11665  // Fill in the rest of the conversions.
11666  for (unsigned ParamIdx = Reversed ? ParamTypes.size() - 1 : 0;
11667  ConvIdx != ConvCount;
11668  ++ConvIdx, ++ArgIdx, ParamIdx += (Reversed ? -1 : 1)) {
11669  assert(ArgIdx < Args.size() && "no argument for this arg conversion");
11670  if (Cand->Conversions[ConvIdx].isInitialized()) {
11671  // We've already checked this conversion.
11672  } else if (ParamIdx < ParamTypes.size()) {
11673  if (ParamTypes[ParamIdx]->isDependentType())
11674  Cand->Conversions[ConvIdx].setAsIdentityConversion(
11675  Args[ArgIdx]->getType());
11676  else {
11677  Cand->Conversions[ConvIdx] =
11678  TryCopyInitialization(S, Args[ArgIdx], ParamTypes[ParamIdx],
11679  SuppressUserConversions,
11680  /*InOverloadResolution=*/true,
11681  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/
11682  S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount);
11683  // Store the FixIt in the candidate if it exists.
11684  if (!Unfixable && Cand->Conversions[ConvIdx].isBad())
11685  Unfixable = !Cand->TryToFixBadConversion(ConvIdx, S);
11686  }
11687  } else
11688  Cand->Conversions[ConvIdx].setEllipsis();
11689  }
11690 }
11691 
11692 SmallVector<OverloadCandidate *, 32> OverloadCandidateSet::CompleteCandidates(
11693  Sema &S, OverloadCandidateDisplayKind OCD, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
11694  SourceLocation OpLoc,
11695  llvm::function_ref<bool(OverloadCandidate &)> Filter) {
11696  // Sort the candidates by viability and position. Sorting directly would
11697  // be prohibitive, so we make a set of pointers and sort those.
11698  SmallVector<OverloadCandidate*, 32> Cands;
11699  if (OCD == OCD_AllCandidates) Cands.reserve(size());
11700  for (iterator Cand = begin(), LastCand = end(); Cand != LastCand; ++Cand) {
11701  if (!Filter(*Cand))
11702  continue;
11703  switch (OCD) {
11704  case OCD_AllCandidates:
11705  if (!Cand->Viable) {
11706  if (!Cand->Function && !Cand->IsSurrogate) {
11707  // This a non-viable builtin candidate. We do not, in general,
11708  // want to list every possible builtin candidate.
11709  continue;
11710  }
11711  CompleteNonViableCandidate(S, Cand, Args, Kind);
11712  }
11713  break;
11714 
11715  case OCD_ViableCandidates:
11716  if (!Cand->Viable)
11717  continue;
11718  break;
11719 
11720  case OCD_AmbiguousCandidates:
11721  if (!Cand->Best)
11722  continue;
11723  break;
11724  }
11725 
11726  Cands.push_back(Cand);
11727  }
11728 
11729  llvm::stable_sort(
11730  Cands, CompareOverloadCandidatesForDisplay(S, OpLoc, Args.size(), Kind));
11731 
11732  return Cands;
11733 }
11734 
11735 bool OverloadCandidateSet::shouldDeferDiags(Sema &S, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
11736  SourceLocation OpLoc) {
11737  bool DeferHint = false;
11738  if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA && S.getLangOpts().GPUDeferDiag) {
11739  // Defer diagnostic for CUDA/HIP if there are wrong-sided candidates or
11740  // host device candidates.
11741  auto WrongSidedCands =
11742  CompleteCandidates(S, OCD_AllCandidates, Args, OpLoc, [](auto &Cand) {
11743  return (Cand.Viable == false &&
11744  Cand.FailureKind == ovl_fail_bad_target) ||
11745  (Cand.Function &&
11746  Cand.Function->template hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>() &&
11747  Cand.Function->template hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>());
11748  });
11749  DeferHint = !WrongSidedCands.empty();
11750  }
11751  return DeferHint;
11752 }
11753 
11754 /// When overload resolution fails, prints diagnostic messages containing the
11755 /// candidates in the candidate set.
11756 void OverloadCandidateSet::NoteCandidates(
11757  PartialDiagnosticAt PD, Sema &S, OverloadCandidateDisplayKind OCD,
11758  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args, StringRef Opc, SourceLocation OpLoc,
11759  llvm::function_ref<bool(OverloadCandidate &)> Filter) {
11760 
11761  auto Cands = CompleteCandidates(S, OCD, Args, OpLoc, Filter);
11762 
11763  S.Diag(PD.first, PD.second, shouldDeferDiags(S, Args, OpLoc));
11764 
11765  NoteCandidates(S, Args, Cands, Opc, OpLoc);
11766 
11767  if (OCD == OCD_AmbiguousCandidates)
11768  MaybeDiagnoseAmbiguousConstraints(S, {begin(), end()});
11769 }
11770 
11771 void OverloadCandidateSet::NoteCandidates(Sema &S, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
11772  ArrayRef<OverloadCandidate *> Cands,
11773  StringRef Opc, SourceLocation OpLoc) {
11774  bool ReportedAmbiguousConversions = false;
11775 
11776  const OverloadsShown ShowOverloads = S.Diags.getShowOverloads();
11777  unsigned CandsShown = 0;
11778  auto I = Cands.begin(), E = Cands.end();
11779  for (; I != E; ++I) {
11780  OverloadCandidate *Cand = *I;
11781 
11782  if (CandsShown >= S.Diags.getNumOverloadCandidatesToShow() &&
11783  ShowOverloads == Ovl_Best) {
11784  break;
11785  }
11786  ++CandsShown;
11787 
11788  if (Cand->Function)
11789  NoteFunctionCandidate(S, Cand, Args.size(),
11790  /*TakingCandidateAddress=*/false, DestAS);
11791  else if (Cand->IsSurrogate)
