11792  NoteSurrogateCandidate(S, Cand);
11793  else {
11794  assert(Cand->Viable &&
11795  "Non-viable built-in candidates are not added to Cands.");
11796  // Generally we only see ambiguities including viable builtin
11797  // operators if overload resolution got screwed up by an
11798  // ambiguous user-defined conversion.
11799  //
11800  // FIXME: It's quite possible for different conversions to see
11801  // different ambiguities, though.
11802  if (!ReportedAmbiguousConversions) {
11803  NoteAmbiguousUserConversions(S, OpLoc, Cand);
11804  ReportedAmbiguousConversions = true;
11805  }
11806 
11807  // If this is a viable builtin, print it.
11808  NoteBuiltinOperatorCandidate(S, Opc, OpLoc, Cand);
11809  }
11810  }
11811 
11812  // Inform S.Diags that we've shown an overload set with N elements. This may
11813  // inform the future value of S.Diags.getNumOverloadCandidatesToShow().
11814  S.Diags.overloadCandidatesShown(CandsShown);
11815 
11816  if (I != E)
11817  S.Diag(OpLoc, diag::note_ovl_too_many_candidates,
11818  shouldDeferDiags(S, Args, OpLoc))
11819  << int(E - I);
11820 }
11821 
11822 static SourceLocation
11823 GetLocationForCandidate(const TemplateSpecCandidate *Cand) {
11824  return Cand->Specialization ? Cand->Specialization->getLocation()
11825  : SourceLocation();
11826 }
11827 
11828 namespace {
11829 struct CompareTemplateSpecCandidatesForDisplay {
11830  Sema &S;
11831  CompareTemplateSpecCandidatesForDisplay(Sema &S) : S(S) {}
11832 
11833  bool operator()(const TemplateSpecCandidate *L,
11834  const TemplateSpecCandidate *R) {
11835  // Fast-path this check.
11836  if (L == R)
11837  return false;
11838 
11839  // Assuming that both candidates are not matches...
11840 
11841  // Sort by the ranking of deduction failures.
11842  if (L->DeductionFailure.Result != R->DeductionFailure.Result)
11843  return RankDeductionFailure(L->DeductionFailure) <
11844  RankDeductionFailure(R->DeductionFailure);
11845 
11846  // Sort everything else by location.
11847  SourceLocation LLoc = GetLocationForCandidate(L);
11848  SourceLocation RLoc = GetLocationForCandidate(R);
11849 
11850  // Put candidates without locations (e.g. builtins) at the end.
11851  if (LLoc.isInvalid())
11852  return false;
11853  if (RLoc.isInvalid())
11854  return true;
11855 
11856  return S.SourceMgr.isBeforeInTranslationUnit(LLoc, RLoc);
11857  }
11858 };
11859 }
11860 
11861 /// Diagnose a template argument deduction failure.
11862 /// We are treating these failures as overload failures due to bad
11863 /// deductions.
11864 void TemplateSpecCandidate::NoteDeductionFailure(Sema &S,
11865  bool ForTakingAddress) {
11866  DiagnoseBadDeduction(S, FoundDecl, Specialization, // pattern
11867  DeductionFailure, /*NumArgs=*/0, ForTakingAddress);
11868 }
11869 
11870 void TemplateSpecCandidateSet::destroyCandidates() {
11871  for (iterator i = begin(), e = end(); i != e; ++i) {
11872  i->DeductionFailure.Destroy();
11873  }
11874 }
11875 
11876 void TemplateSpecCandidateSet::clear() {
11877  destroyCandidates();
11878  Candidates.clear();
11879 }
11880 
11881 /// NoteCandidates - When no template specialization match is found, prints
11882 /// diagnostic messages containing the non-matching specializations that form
11883 /// the candidate set.
11884 /// This is analoguous to OverloadCandidateSet::NoteCandidates() with
11885 /// OCD == OCD_AllCandidates and Cand->Viable == false.
11886 void TemplateSpecCandidateSet::NoteCandidates(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc) {
11887  // Sort the candidates by position (assuming no candidate is a match).
11888  // Sorting directly would be prohibitive, so we make a set of pointers
11889  // and sort those.
11890  SmallVector<TemplateSpecCandidate *, 32> Cands;
11891  Cands.reserve(size());
11892  for (iterator Cand = begin(), LastCand = end(); Cand != LastCand; ++Cand) {
11893  if (Cand->Specialization)
11894  Cands.push_back(Cand);
11895  // Otherwise, this is a non-matching builtin candidate. We do not,
11896  // in general, want to list every possible builtin candidate.
11897  }
11898 
11899  llvm::sort(Cands, CompareTemplateSpecCandidatesForDisplay(S));
11900 
11901  // FIXME: Perhaps rename OverloadsShown and getShowOverloads()
11902  // for generalization purposes (?).
11903  const OverloadsShown ShowOverloads = S.Diags.getShowOverloads();
11904 
11905  SmallVectorImpl<TemplateSpecCandidate *>::iterator I, E;
11906  unsigned CandsShown = 0;
11907  for (I = Cands.begin(), E = Cands.end(); I != E; ++I) {
11908  TemplateSpecCandidate *Cand = *I;
11909 
11910  // Set an arbitrary limit on the number of candidates we'll spam
11911  // the user with. FIXME: This limit should depend on details of the
11912  // candidate list.
11913  if (CandsShown >= 4 && ShowOverloads == Ovl_Best)
11914  break;
11915  ++CandsShown;
11916 
11917  assert(Cand->Specialization &&
11918  "Non-matching built-in candidates are not added to Cands.");
11919  Cand->NoteDeductionFailure(S, ForTakingAddress);
11920  }
11921 
11922  if (I != E)
11923  S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_ovl_too_many_candidates) << int(E - I);
11924 }
11925 
11926 // [PossiblyAFunctionType] --> [Return]
11927 // NonFunctionType --> NonFunctionType
11928 // R (A) --> R(A)
11929 // R (*)(A) --> R (A)
11930 // R (&)(A) --> R (A)
11931 // R (S::*)(A) --> R (A)
11932 QualType Sema::ExtractUnqualifiedFunctionType(QualType PossiblyAFunctionType) {
11933  QualType Ret = PossiblyAFunctionType;
11934  if (const PointerType *ToTypePtr =
11935  PossiblyAFunctionType->getAs<PointerType>())
11936  Ret = ToTypePtr->getPointeeType();
11937  else if (const ReferenceType *ToTypeRef =
11938  PossiblyAFunctionType->getAs<ReferenceType>())
11939  Ret = ToTypeRef->getPointeeType();
11940  else if (const MemberPointerType *MemTypePtr =
11941  PossiblyAFunctionType->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
11942  Ret = MemTypePtr->getPointeeType();
11943  Ret =
11944  Context.getCanonicalType(Ret).getUnqualifiedType();
11945  return Ret;
11946 }
11947 
11948 static bool completeFunctionType(Sema &S, FunctionDecl *FD, SourceLocation Loc,
11949  bool Complain = true) {
11950  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 && FD->getReturnType()->isUndeducedType() &&
11951  S.DeduceReturnType(FD, Loc, Complain))
11952  return true;
11953 
11954  auto *FPT = FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
11955  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 &&
11956  isUnresolvedExceptionSpec(FPT->getExceptionSpecType()) &&
11957  !S.ResolveExceptionSpec(Loc, FPT))
11958  return true;
11959 
11960  return false;
11961 }
11962 
11963 namespace {
11964 // A helper class to help with address of function resolution
11965 // - allows us to avoid passing around all those ugly parameters
11966 class AddressOfFunctionResolver {
11967  Sema& S;
11968  Expr* SourceExpr;
11969  const QualType& TargetType;
11970  QualType TargetFunctionType; // Extracted function type from target type
11971 
11972  bool Complain;
11973  //DeclAccessPair& ResultFunctionAccessPair;
11974  ASTContext& Context;
11975 
11976  bool TargetTypeIsNonStaticMemberFunction;
11977  bool FoundNonTemplateFunction;
11978  bool StaticMemberFunctionFromBoundPointer;
11979  bool HasComplained;
11980 
11981  OverloadExpr::FindResult OvlExprInfo;
11982  OverloadExpr *OvlExpr;
11983  TemplateArgumentListInfo OvlExplicitTemplateArgs;
11984  SmallVector<std::pair<DeclAccessPair, FunctionDecl*>, 4> Matches;
11985  TemplateSpecCandidateSet FailedCandidates;
11986 
11987 public:
11988  AddressOfFunctionResolver(Sema &S, Expr *SourceExpr,
11989  const QualType &TargetType, bool Complain)
11990  : S(S), SourceExpr(SourceExpr), TargetType(TargetType),
11991  Complain(Complain), Context(S.getASTContext()),
11992  TargetTypeIsNonStaticMemberFunction(
11993  !!TargetType->getAs<MemberPointerType>()),
11994  FoundNonTemplateFunction(false),
11995  StaticMemberFunctionFromBoundPointer(false),
11996  HasComplained(false),
11997  OvlExprInfo(OverloadExpr::find(SourceExpr)),
11998  OvlExpr(OvlExprInfo.Expression),
11999  FailedCandidates(OvlExpr->getNameLoc(), /*ForTakingAddress=*/true) {
12000  ExtractUnqualifiedFunctionTypeFromTargetType();
12001 
12002  if (TargetFunctionType->isFunctionType()) {
12003  if (UnresolvedMemberExpr *UME = dyn_cast<UnresolvedMemberExpr>(OvlExpr))
12004  if (!UME->isImplicitAccess() &&
12005  !S.ResolveSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(UME))
12006  StaticMemberFunctionFromBoundPointer = true;
12007  } else if (OvlExpr->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
12008  DeclAccessPair dap;
12009  if (FunctionDecl *Fn = S.ResolveSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(
12010  OvlExpr, false, &dap)) {
12011  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn))
12012  if (!Method->isStatic()) {
12013  // If the target type is a non-function type and the function found
12014  // is a non-static member function, pretend as if that was the
12015  // target, it's the only possible type to end up with.
12016  TargetTypeIsNonStaticMemberFunction = true;
12017 
12018  // And skip adding the function if its not in the proper form.
12019  // We'll diagnose this due to an empty set of functions.
12020  if (!OvlExprInfo.HasFormOfMemberPointer)
12021  return;
12022  }
12023 
12024  Matches.push_back(std::make_pair(dap, Fn));
12025  }
12026  return;
12027  }
12028 
12029  if (OvlExpr->hasExplicitTemplateArgs())
12030  OvlExpr->copyTemplateArgumentsInto(OvlExplicitTemplateArgs);
12031 
12032  if (FindAllFunctionsThatMatchTargetTypeExactly()) {
12033  // C++ [over.over]p4:
12034  // If more than one function is selected, [...]
12035  if (Matches.size() > 1 && !eliminiateSuboptimalOverloadCandidates()) {
12036  if (FoundNonTemplateFunction)
12037  EliminateAllTemplateMatches();
12038  else
12039  EliminateAllExceptMostSpecializedTemplate();
12040  }
12041  }
12042 
12043  if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA && Matches.size() > 1)
12044  EliminateSuboptimalCudaMatches();
12045  }
12046 
12047  bool hasComplained() const { return HasComplained; }
12048 
12049 private:
12050  bool candidateHasExactlyCorrectType(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
12051  QualType Discard;
12052  return Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(TargetFunctionType, FD->getType()) ||
12053  S.IsFunctionConversion(FD->getType(), TargetFunctionType, Discard);
12054  }
12055 
12056  /// \return true if A is considered a better overload candidate for the
12057  /// desired type than B.
12058  bool isBetterCandidate(const FunctionDecl *A, const FunctionDecl *B) {
12059  // If A doesn't have exactly the correct type, we don't want to classify it
12060  // as "better" than anything else. This way, the user is required to
12061  // disambiguate for us if there are multiple candidates and no exact match.
12062  return candidateHasExactlyCorrectType(A) &&
12063  (!candidateHasExactlyCorrectType(B) ||
12064  compareEnableIfAttrs(S, A, B) == Comparison::Better);
12065  }
12066 
12067  /// \return true if we were able to eliminate all but one overload candidate,
12068  /// false otherwise.
12069  bool eliminiateSuboptimalOverloadCandidates() {
12070  // Same algorithm as overload resolution -- one pass to pick the "best",
12071  // another pass to be sure that nothing is better than the best.
12072  auto Best = Matches.begin();
12073  for (auto I = Matches.begin()+1, E = Matches.end(); I != E; ++I)
12074  if (isBetterCandidate(I->second, Best->second))
12075  Best = I;
12076 
12077  const FunctionDecl *BestFn = Best->second;
12078  auto IsBestOrInferiorToBest = [this, BestFn](
12079  const std::pair<DeclAccessPair, FunctionDecl *> &Pair) {
12080  return BestFn == Pair.second || isBetterCandidate(BestFn, Pair.second);
12081  };
12082 
12083  // Note: We explicitly leave Matches unmodified if there isn't a clear best
12084  // option, so we can potentially give the user a better error
12085  if (!llvm::all_of(Matches, IsBestOrInferiorToBest))
12086  return false;
12087  Matches[0] = *Best;
12088  Matches.resize(1);
12089  return true;
12090  }
12091 
12092  bool isTargetTypeAFunction() const {
12093  return TargetFunctionType->isFunctionType();
12094  }
12095 
12096  // [ToType] [Return]
12097 
12098  // R (*)(A) --> R (A), IsNonStaticMemberFunction = false
12099  // R (&)(A) --> R (A), IsNonStaticMemberFunction = false
12100  // R (S::*)(A) --> R (A), IsNonStaticMemberFunction = true
12101  void inline ExtractUnqualifiedFunctionTypeFromTargetType() {
12102  TargetFunctionType = S.ExtractUnqualifiedFunctionType(TargetType);
12103  }
12104 
12105  // return true if any matching specializations were found
12106  bool AddMatchingTemplateFunction(FunctionTemplateDecl* FunctionTemplate,
12107  const DeclAccessPair& CurAccessFunPair) {
12108  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method
12109  = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl())) {
12110  // Skip non-static function templates when converting to pointer, and
12111  // static when converting to member pointer.
12112  if (Method->isStatic() == TargetTypeIsNonStaticMemberFunction)
12113  return false;
12114  }
12115  else if (TargetTypeIsNonStaticMemberFunction)
12116  return false;
12117 
12118  // C++ [over.over]p2:
12119  // If the name is a function template, template argument deduction is
12120  // done (14.8.2.2), and if the argument deduction succeeds, the
12121  // resulting template argument list is used to generate a single
12122  // function template specialization, which is added to the set of
12123  // overloaded functions considered.
12124  FunctionDecl *Specialization = nullptr;
12125  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(FailedCandidates.getLocation());
12126  if (Sema::TemplateDeductionResult Result
12127  = S.DeduceTemplateArguments(FunctionTemplate,
12128  &OvlExplicitTemplateArgs,
12129  TargetFunctionType, Specialization,
12130  Info, /*IsAddressOfFunction*/true)) {
12131  // Make a note of the failed deduction for diagnostics.
12132  FailedCandidates.addCandidate()
12133  .set(CurAccessFunPair, FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl(),
12134  MakeDeductionFailureInfo(Context, Result, Info));
12135  return false;
12136  }
12137 
12138  // Template argument deduction ensures that we have an exact match or
12139  // compatible pointer-to-function arguments that would be adjusted by ICS.
12140  // This function template specicalization works.
12141  assert(S.isSameOrCompatibleFunctionType(
12142  Context.getCanonicalType(Specialization->getType()),
12143  Context.getCanonicalType(TargetFunctionType)));
12144 
12145  if (!S.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(Specialization))
12146  return false;
12147 
12148  Matches.push_back(std::make_pair(CurAccessFunPair, Specialization));
12149  return true;
12150  }
12151 
12152  bool AddMatchingNonTemplateFunction(NamedDecl* Fn,
12153  const DeclAccessPair& CurAccessFunPair) {
12154  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn)) {
12155  // Skip non-static functions when converting to pointer, and static
12156  // when converting to member pointer.
12157  if (Method->isStatic() == TargetTypeIsNonStaticMemberFunction)
12158  return false;
12159  }
12160  else if (TargetTypeIsNonStaticMemberFunction)
12161  return false;
12162 
12163  if (FunctionDecl *FunDecl = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Fn)) {
12164  if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA)
12165  if (FunctionDecl *Caller = S.getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true))
12166  if (!Caller->isImplicit() && !S.IsAllowedCUDACall(Caller, FunDecl))
12167  return false;
12168  if (FunDecl->isMultiVersion()) {
12169  const auto *TA = FunDecl->getAttr<TargetAttr>();
12170  if (TA && !TA->isDefaultVersion())
12171  return false;
12172  }
12173 
12174  // If any candidate has a placeholder return type, trigger its deduction
12175  // now.
12176  if (completeFunctionType(S, FunDecl, SourceExpr->getBeginLoc(),
12177  Complain)) {
12178  HasComplained |= Complain;
12179  return false;
12180  }
12181 
12182  if (!S.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(FunDecl))
12183  return false;
12184 
12185  // If we're in C, we need to support types that aren't exactly identical.
12186  if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ||
12187  candidateHasExactlyCorrectType(FunDecl)) {
12188  Matches.push_back(std::make_pair(
12189  CurAccessFunPair, cast<FunctionDecl>(FunDecl->getCanonicalDecl())));
12190  FoundNonTemplateFunction = true;
12191  return true;
12192  }
12193  }
12194 
12195  return false;
12196  }
12197 
12198  bool FindAllFunctionsThatMatchTargetTypeExactly() {
12199  bool Ret = false;
12200 
12201  // If the overload expression doesn't have the form of a pointer to
12202  // member, don't try to convert it to a pointer-to-member type.
12203  if (IsInvalidFormOfPointerToMemberFunction())
12204  return false;
12205 
12206  for (UnresolvedSetIterator I = OvlExpr->decls_begin(),
12207  E = OvlExpr->decls_end();
12208  I != E; ++I) {
12209  // Look through any using declarations to find the underlying function.
12210  NamedDecl *Fn = (*I)->getUnderlyingDecl();
12211 
12212  // C++ [over.over]p3:
12213  // Non-member functions and static member functions match
12214  // targets of type "pointer-to-function" or "reference-to-function."
12215  // Nonstatic member functions match targets of
12216  // type "pointer-to-member-function."
12217  // Note that according to DR 247, the containing class does not matter.
12218  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunctionTemplate
12219  = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Fn)) {
12220  if (AddMatchingTemplateFunction(FunctionTemplate, I.getPair()))
12221  Ret = true;
12222  }
12223  // If we have explicit template arguments supplied, skip non-templates.
12224  else if (!OvlExpr->hasExplicitTemplateArgs() &&
12225  AddMatchingNonTemplateFunction(Fn, I.getPair()))
12226  Ret = true;
12227  }
12228  assert(Ret || Matches.empty());
12229  return Ret;
12230  }
12231 
12232  void EliminateAllExceptMostSpecializedTemplate() {
12233  // [...] and any given function template specialization F1 is
12234  // eliminated if the set contains a second function template
12235  // specialization whose function template is more specialized
12236  // than the function template of F1 according to the partial
12237  // ordering rules of 14.5.5.2.
12238 
12239  // The algorithm specified above is quadratic. We instead use a
12240  // two-pass algorithm (similar to the one used to identify the
12241  // best viable function in an overload set) that identifies the
12242  // best function template (if it exists).
12243 
12244  UnresolvedSet<4> MatchesCopy; // TODO: avoid!
12245  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Matches.size(); I != E; ++I)
12246  MatchesCopy.addDecl(Matches[I].second, Matches[I].first.getAccess());
12247 
12248  // TODO: It looks like FailedCandidates does not serve much purpose
12249  // here, since the no_viable diagnostic has index 0.
12250  UnresolvedSetIterator Result = S.getMostSpecialized(
12251  MatchesCopy.begin(), MatchesCopy.end(), FailedCandidates,
12252  SourceExpr->getBeginLoc(), S.PDiag(),
12253  S.PDiag(diag::err_addr_ovl_ambiguous)
12254  << Matches[0].second->getDeclName(),
12255  S.PDiag(diag::note_ovl_candidate)
12256  << (unsigned)oc_function << (unsigned)ocs_described_template,
12257  Complain, TargetFunctionType);
12258 
12259  if (Result != MatchesCopy.end()) {
12260  // Make it the first and only element
12261  Matches[0].first = Matches[Result - MatchesCopy.begin()].first;
12262  Matches[0].second = cast<FunctionDecl>(*Result);
12263  Matches.resize(1);
12264  } else
12265  HasComplained |= Complain;
12266  }
12267 
12268  void EliminateAllTemplateMatches() {
12269  // [...] any function template specializations in the set are
12270  // eliminated if the set also contains a non-template function, [...]
12271  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Matches.size(); I != N; ) {
12272  if (Matches[I].second->getPrimaryTemplate() == nullptr)
12273  ++I;
12274  else {
12275  Matches[I] = Matches[--N];
12276  Matches.resize(N);
12277  }
12278  }
12279  }
12280 
12281  void EliminateSuboptimalCudaMatches() {
12282  S.EraseUnwantedCUDAMatches(S.getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true),
12283  Matches);
12284  }
12285 
12286 public:
12287  void ComplainNoMatchesFound() const {
12288  assert(Matches.empty());
12289  S.Diag(OvlExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_addr_ovl_no_viable)
12290  << OvlExpr->getName() << TargetFunctionType
12291  << OvlExpr->getSourceRange();
12292  if (FailedCandidates.empty())
12293  S.NoteAllOverloadCandidates(OvlExpr, TargetFunctionType,
12294  /*TakingAddress=*/true);
12295  else {
12296  // We have some deduction failure messages. Use them to diagnose
12297  // the function templates, and diagnose the non-template candidates
12298  // normally.
12299  for (UnresolvedSetIterator I = OvlExpr->decls_begin(),
12300  IEnd = OvlExpr->decls_end();
12301  I != IEnd; ++I)
12302  if (FunctionDecl *Fun =
12303  dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>((*I)->getUnderlyingDecl()))
12304  if (!functionHasPassObjectSizeParams(Fun))
12305  S.NoteOverloadCandidate(*I, Fun, CRK_None, TargetFunctionType,
12306  /*TakingAddress=*/true);
12307  FailedCandidates.NoteCandidates(S, OvlExpr->getBeginLoc());
12308  }
12309  }
12310 
12311  bool IsInvalidFormOfPointerToMemberFunction() const {
12312  return TargetTypeIsNonStaticMemberFunction &&
12313  !OvlExprInfo.HasFormOfMemberPointer;
12314  }

12316  void ComplainIsInvalidFormOfPointerToMemberFunction() const {
12317  // TODO: Should we condition this on whether any functions might
12318  // have matched, or is it more appropriate to do that in callers?
12319  // TODO: a fixit wouldn't hurt.
12320  S.Diag(OvlExpr->getNameLoc(), diag::err_addr_ovl_no_qualifier)
12321  << TargetType << OvlExpr->getSourceRange();
12322  }
12323 
12324  bool IsStaticMemberFunctionFromBoundPointer() const {
12325  return StaticMemberFunctionFromBoundPointer;
12326  }
12327 
12328  void ComplainIsStaticMemberFunctionFromBoundPointer() const {
12329  S.Diag(OvlExpr->getBeginLoc(),
12330  diag::err_invalid_form_pointer_member_function)
12331  << OvlExpr->getSourceRange();
12332  }
12333 
12334  void ComplainOfInvalidConversion() const {
12335  S.Diag(OvlExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_addr_ovl_not_func_ptrref)
12336  << OvlExpr->getName() << TargetType;
12337  }
12338 
12339  void ComplainMultipleMatchesFound() const {
12340  assert(Matches.size() > 1);
12341  S.Diag(OvlExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_addr_ovl_ambiguous)
12342  << OvlExpr->getName() << OvlExpr->getSourceRange();
12343  S.NoteAllOverloadCandidates(OvlExpr, TargetFunctionType,
12344  /*TakingAddress=*/true);
12345  }
12346 
12347  bool hadMultipleCandidates() const { return (OvlExpr->getNumDecls() > 1); }
12348 
12349  int getNumMatches() const { return Matches.size(); }
12350 
12351  FunctionDecl* getMatchingFunctionDecl() const {
12352  if (Matches.size() != 1) return nullptr;
12353  return Matches[0].second;
12354  }
12355 
12356  const DeclAccessPair* getMatchingFunctionAccessPair() const {
12357  if (Matches.size() != 1) return nullptr;
12358  return &Matches[0].first;
12359  }
12360 };
12361 }
12362 
12363 /// ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction - Try to resolve the address of
12364 /// an overloaded function (C++ [over.over]), where @p From is an
12365 /// expression with overloaded function type and @p ToType is the type
12366 /// we're trying to resolve to. For example:
12367 ///
12368 /// @code
12369 /// int f(double);
12370 /// int f(int);
12371 ///
12372 /// int (*pfd)(double) = f; // selects f(double)
12373 /// @endcode
12374 ///
12375 /// This routine returns the resulting FunctionDecl if it could be
12376 /// resolved, and NULL otherwise. When @p Complain is true, this
12377 /// routine will emit diagnostics if there is an error.
12378 FunctionDecl *
12379 Sema::ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(Expr *AddressOfExpr,
12380  QualType TargetType,
12381  bool Complain,
12382  DeclAccessPair &FoundResult,
12383  bool *pHadMultipleCandidates) {
12384  assert(AddressOfExpr->getType() == Context.OverloadTy);
12385 
12386  AddressOfFunctionResolver Resolver(*this, AddressOfExpr, TargetType,
12387  Complain);
12388  int NumMatches = Resolver.getNumMatches();
12389  FunctionDecl *Fn = nullptr;
12390  bool ShouldComplain = Complain && !Resolver.hasComplained();
12391  if (NumMatches == 0 && ShouldComplain) {
12392  if (Resolver.IsInvalidFormOfPointerToMemberFunction())
12393  Resolver.ComplainIsInvalidFormOfPointerToMemberFunction();
12394  else
12395  Resolver.ComplainNoMatchesFound();
12396  }
12397  else if (NumMatches > 1 && ShouldComplain)
12398  Resolver.ComplainMultipleMatchesFound();
12399  else if (NumMatches == 1) {
12400  Fn = Resolver.getMatchingFunctionDecl();
12401  assert(Fn);
12402  if (auto *FPT = Fn->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
12403  ResolveExceptionSpec(AddressOfExpr->getExprLoc(), FPT);
12404  FoundResult = *Resolver.getMatchingFunctionAccessPair();
12405  if (Complain) {
12406  if (Resolver.IsStaticMemberFunctionFromBoundPointer())
12407  Resolver.ComplainIsStaticMemberFunctionFromBoundPointer();
12408  else
12409  CheckAddressOfMemberAccess(AddressOfExpr, FoundResult);
12410  }
12411  }
12412 
12413  if (pHadMultipleCandidates)
12414  *pHadMultipleCandidates = Resolver.hadMultipleCandidates();
12415  return Fn;
12416 }
12417 
12418 /// Given an expression that refers to an overloaded function, try to
12419 /// resolve that function to a single function that can have its address taken.
12420 /// This will modify `Pair` iff it returns non-null.
12421 ///
12422 /// This routine can only succeed if from all of the candidates in the overload
12423 /// set for SrcExpr that can have their addresses taken, there is one candidate
12424 /// that is more constrained than the rest.
12425 FunctionDecl *
12426 Sema::resolveAddressOfSingleOverloadCandidate(Expr *E, DeclAccessPair &Pair) {
12427  OverloadExpr::FindResult R = OverloadExpr::find(E);
12428  OverloadExpr *Ovl = R.Expression;
12429  bool IsResultAmbiguous = false;
12430  FunctionDecl *Result = nullptr;
12431  DeclAccessPair DAP;
12432  SmallVector<FunctionDecl *, 2> AmbiguousDecls;
12433 
12434  auto CheckMoreConstrained =
12435  [&] (FunctionDecl *FD1, FunctionDecl *FD2) -> Optional<bool> {
12436  SmallVector<const Expr *, 1> AC1, AC2;
12437  FD1->getAssociatedConstraints(AC1);
12438  FD2->getAssociatedConstraints(AC2);
12439  bool AtLeastAsConstrained1, AtLeastAsConstrained2;
12440  if (IsAtLeastAsConstrained(FD1, AC1, FD2, AC2, AtLeastAsConstrained1))
12441  return None;
12442  if (IsAtLeastAsConstrained(FD2, AC2, FD1, AC1, AtLeastAsConstrained2))
12443  return None;
12444  if (AtLeastAsConstrained1 == AtLeastAsConstrained2)
12445  return None;
12446  return AtLeastAsConstrained1;
12447  };
12448 
12449  // Don't use the AddressOfResolver because we're specifically looking for
12450  // cases where we have one overload candidate that lacks
12451  // enable_if/pass_object_size/...
12452  for (auto I = Ovl->decls_begin(), E = Ovl->decls_end(); I != E; ++I) {
12453  auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(I->getUnderlyingDecl());
12454  if (!FD)
12455  return nullptr;
12456 
12457  if (!checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(FD))
12458  continue;
12459 
12460  // We have more than one result - see if it is more constrained than the
12461  // previous one.
12462  if (Result) {
12463  Optional<bool> MoreConstrainedThanPrevious = CheckMoreConstrained(FD,
12464  Result);
12465  if (!MoreConstrainedThanPrevious) {
12466  IsResultAmbiguous = true;
12467  AmbiguousDecls.push_back(FD);
12468  continue;
12469  }
12470  if (!*MoreConstrainedThanPrevious)
12471  continue;
12472  // FD is more constrained - replace Result with it.
12473  }
12474  IsResultAmbiguous = false;
12475  DAP = I.getPair();
12476  Result = FD;
12477  }
12478 
12479  if (IsResultAmbiguous)
12480  return nullptr;
12481 
12482  if (Result) {
12483  SmallVector<const Expr *, 1> ResultAC;
12484  // We skipped over some ambiguous declarations which might be ambiguous with
12485  // the selected result.
12486  for (FunctionDecl *Skipped : AmbiguousDecls)
12487  if (!CheckMoreConstrained(Skipped, Result).hasValue())
12488  return nullptr;
12489  Pair = DAP;
12490  }
12491  return Result;
12492 }
12493 
12494 /// Given an overloaded function, tries to turn it into a non-overloaded
12495 /// function reference using resolveAddressOfSingleOverloadCandidate. This
12496 /// will perform access checks, diagnose the use of the resultant decl, and, if
12497 /// requested, potentially perform a function-to-pointer decay.
12498 ///
12499 /// Returns false if resolveAddressOfSingleOverloadCandidate fails.
12500 /// Otherwise, returns true. This may emit diagnostics and return true.
12501 bool Sema::resolveAndFixAddressOfSingleOverloadCandidate(
12502  ExprResult &SrcExpr, bool DoFunctionPointerConverion) {
12503  Expr *E = SrcExpr.get();
12504  assert(E->getType() == Context.OverloadTy && "SrcExpr must be an overload");
12505 
12506  DeclAccessPair DAP;
12507  FunctionDecl *Found = resolveAddressOfSingleOverloadCandidate(E, DAP);
12508  if (!Found || Found->isCPUDispatchMultiVersion() ||
12509  Found->isCPUSpecificMultiVersion())
12510  return false;
12511 
12512  // Emitting multiple diagnostics for a function that is both inaccessible and
12513  // unavailable is consistent with our behavior elsewhere. So, always check
12514  // for both.
12515  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Found, E->getExprLoc());
12516  CheckAddressOfMemberAccess(E, DAP);
12517  Expr *Fixed = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(E, DAP, Found);
12518  if (DoFunctionPointerConverion && Fixed->getType()->isFunctionType())
12519  SrcExpr = DefaultFunctionArrayConversion(Fixed, /*Diagnose=*/false);
12520  else
12521  SrcExpr = Fixed;
12522  return true;
12523 }
12524 
12525 /// Given an expression that refers to an overloaded function, try to
12526 /// resolve that overloaded function expression down to a single function.
12527 ///
12528 /// This routine can only resolve template-ids that refer to a single function
12529 /// template, where that template-id refers to a single template whose template
12530 /// arguments are either provided by the template-id or have defaults,
12531 /// as described in C++0x [temp.arg.explicit]p3.
12532 ///
12533 /// If no template-ids are found, no diagnostics are emitted and NULL is
12534 /// returned.
12535 FunctionDecl *
12536 Sema::ResolveSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(OverloadExpr *ovl,
12537  bool Complain,
12538  DeclAccessPair *FoundResult) {
12539  // C++ [over.over]p1:
12540  // [...] [Note: any redundant set of parentheses surrounding the
12541  // overloaded function name is ignored (5.1). ]
12542  // C++ [over.over]p1:
12543  // [...] The overloaded function name can be preceded by the &
12544  // operator.
12545 
12546  // If we didn't actually find any template-ids, we're done.
12547  if (!ovl->hasExplicitTemplateArgs())
12548  return nullptr;
12549 
12550  TemplateArgumentListInfo ExplicitTemplateArgs;
12551  ovl->copyTemplateArgumentsInto(ExplicitTemplateArgs);
12552  TemplateSpecCandidateSet FailedCandidates(ovl->getNameLoc());
12553 
12554  // Look through all of the overloaded functions, searching for one
12555  // whose type matches exactly.
12556  FunctionDecl *Matched = nullptr;
12557  for (UnresolvedSetIterator I = ovl->decls_begin(),
12558  E = ovl->decls_end(); I != E; ++I) {
12559  // C++0x [temp.arg.explicit]p3:
12560  // [...] In contexts where deduction is done and fails, or in contexts
12561  // where deduction is not done, if a template argument list is
12562  // specified and it, along with any default template arguments,
12563  // identifies a single function template specialization, then the
12564  // template-id is an lvalue for the function template specialization.
12565  FunctionTemplateDecl *FunctionTemplate
12566  = cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>((*I)->getUnderlyingDecl());
12567 
12568  // C++ [over.over]p2:
12569  // If the name is a function template, template argument deduction is
12570  // done (14.8.2.2), and if the argument deduction succeeds, the
12571  // resulting template argument list is used to generate a single
12572  // function template specialization, which is added to the set of
12573  // overloaded functions considered.
12574  FunctionDecl *Specialization = nullptr;
12575  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(FailedCandidates.getLocation());
12576  if (TemplateDeductionResult Result
12577  = DeduceTemplateArguments(FunctionTemplate, &ExplicitTemplateArgs,
12578  Specialization, Info,
12579  /*IsAddressOfFunction*/true)) {
12580  // Make a note of the failed deduction for diagnostics.
12581  // TODO: Actually use the failed-deduction info?
12582  FailedCandidates.addCandidate()
12583  .set(I.getPair(), FunctionTemplate->getTemplatedDecl(),
12584  MakeDeductionFailureInfo(Context, Result, Info));
12585  continue;
12586  }
12587 
12588  assert(Specialization && "no specialization and no error?");
12589 
12590  // Multiple matches; we can't resolve to a single declaration.
12591  if (Matched) {
12592  if (Complain) {
12593  Diag(ovl->getExprLoc(), diag::err_addr_ovl_ambiguous)
12594  << ovl->getName();
12595  NoteAllOverloadCandidates(ovl);
12596  }
12597  return nullptr;
12598  }
12599 
12600  Matched = Specialization;
12601  if (FoundResult) *FoundResult = I.getPair();
12602  }
12603 
12604  if (Matched &&
12605  completeFunctionType(*this, Matched, ovl->getExprLoc(), Complain))
12606  return nullptr;
12607 
12608  return Matched;
12609 }
12610 
12611 // Resolve and fix an overloaded expression that can be resolved
12612 // because it identifies a single function template specialization.
12613 //
12614 // Last three arguments should only be supplied if Complain = true
12615 //
12616 // Return true if it was logically possible to so resolve the
12617 // expression, regardless of whether or not it succeeded. Always
12618 // returns true if 'complain' is set.
12619 bool Sema::ResolveAndFixSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(
12620  ExprResult &SrcExpr, bool doFunctionPointerConverion,
12621  bool complain, SourceRange OpRangeForComplaining,
12622  QualType DestTypeForComplaining,
12623  unsigned DiagIDForComplaining) {
12624  assert(SrcExpr.get()->getType() == Context.OverloadTy);
12625 
12626  OverloadExpr::FindResult ovl = OverloadExpr::find(SrcExpr.get());
12627 
12628  DeclAccessPair found;
12629  ExprResult SingleFunctionExpression;
12630  if (FunctionDecl *fn = ResolveSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(
12631  ovl.Expression, /*complain*/ false, &found)) {
12632  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(fn, SrcExpr.get()->getBeginLoc())) {
12633  SrcExpr = ExprError();
12634  return true;
12635  }
12636 
12637  // It is only correct to resolve to an instance method if we're
12638  // resolving a form that's permitted to be a pointer to member.
12639  // Otherwise we'll end up making a bound member expression, which
12640  // is illegal in all the contexts we resolve like this.
12641  if (!ovl.HasFormOfMemberPointer &&
12642  isa<CXXMethodDecl>(fn) &&
12643  cast<CXXMethodDecl>(fn)->isInstance()) {
12644  if (!complain) return false;
12645 
12646  Diag(ovl.Expression->getExprLoc(),
12647  diag::err_bound_member_function)
12648  << 0 << ovl.Expression->getSourceRange();
12649 
12650  // TODO: I believe we only end up here if there's a mix of
12651  // static and non-static candidates (otherwise the expression
12652  // would have 'bound member' type, not 'overload' type).
12653  // Ideally we would note which candidate was chosen and why
12654  // the static candidates were rejected.
12655  SrcExpr = ExprError();
12656  return true;
12657  }
12658 
12659  // Fix the expression to refer to 'fn'.
12660  SingleFunctionExpression =
12661  FixOverloadedFunctionReference(SrcExpr.get(), found, fn);
12662 
12663  // If desired, do function-to-pointer decay.
12664  if (doFunctionPointerConverion) {
12665  SingleFunctionExpression =
12666  DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(SingleFunctionExpression.get());
12667  if (SingleFunctionExpression.isInvalid()) {
12668  SrcExpr = ExprError();
12669  return true;
12670  }
12671  }
12672  }
12673 
12674  if (!SingleFunctionExpression.isUsable()) {
12675  if (complain) {
12676  Diag(OpRangeForComplaining.getBegin(), DiagIDForComplaining)
12677  << ovl.Expression->getName()
12678  << DestTypeForComplaining
12679  << OpRangeForComplaining
12680  << ovl.Expression->getQualifierLoc().getSourceRange();
12681  NoteAllOverloadCandidates(SrcExpr.get());
12682 
12683  SrcExpr = ExprError();
12684  return true;
12685  }
12686 
12687  return false;
12688  }
12689 
12690  SrcExpr = SingleFunctionExpression;
12691  return true;
12692 }
12693 
12694 /// Add a single candidate to the overload set.
12695 static void AddOverloadedCallCandidate(Sema &S,
12696  DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
12697  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs,
12698  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
12699  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
12700  bool PartialOverloading,
12701  bool KnownValid) {
12702  NamedDecl *Callee = FoundDecl.getDecl();
12703  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(Callee))
12704  Callee = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(Callee)->getTargetDecl();
12705 
12706  if (FunctionDecl *Func = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Callee)) {
12707  if (ExplicitTemplateArgs) {
12708  assert(!KnownValid && "Explicit template arguments?");
12709  return;
12710  }
12711  // Prevent ill-formed function decls to be added as overload candidates.
12712  if (!isa<FunctionProtoType>(Func->getType()->getAs<FunctionType>()))
12713  return;
12714 
12715  S.AddOverloadCandidate(Func, FoundDecl, Args, CandidateSet,
12716  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false,
12717  PartialOverloading);
12718  return;
12719  }
12720 
12721  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FuncTemplate
12722  = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Callee)) {
12723  S.AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(FuncTemplate, FoundDecl,
12724  ExplicitTemplateArgs, Args, CandidateSet,
12725  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false,
12726  PartialOverloading);
12727  return;
12728  }
12729 
12730  assert(!KnownValid && "unhandled case in overloaded call candidate");
12731 }
12732 
12733 /// Add the overload candidates named by callee and/or found by argument
12734 /// dependent lookup to the given overload set.
12735 void Sema::AddOverloadedCallCandidates(UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE,
12736  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
12737  OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
12738  bool PartialOverloading) {
12739 
12740 #ifndef NDEBUG
12741  // Verify that ArgumentDependentLookup is consistent with the rules
12742  // in C++0x [basic.lookup.argdep]p3:
12743  //
12744  // Let X be the lookup set produced by unqualified lookup (3.4.1)
12745  // and let Y be the lookup set produced by argument dependent
12746  // lookup (defined as follows). If X contains
12747  //
12748  // -- a declaration of a class member, or
12749  //
12750  // -- a block-scope function declaration that is not a
12751  // using-declaration, or
12752  //
12753  // -- a declaration that is neither a function or a function
12754  // template
12755  //
12756  // then Y is empty.
12757 
12758  if (ULE->requiresADL()) {
12759  for (UnresolvedLookupExpr::decls_iterator I = ULE->decls_begin(),
12760  E = ULE->decls_end(); I != E; ++I) {
12761  assert(!(*I)->getDeclContext()->isRecord());
12762  assert(isa<UsingShadowDecl>(*I) ||
12763  !(*I)->getDeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod());
12764  assert((*I)->getUnderlyingDecl()->isFunctionOrFunctionTemplate());
12765  }
12766  }
12767 #endif
12768 
12769  // It would be nice to avoid this copy.
12770  TemplateArgumentListInfo TABuffer;
12771  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs = nullptr;
12772  if (ULE->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
12773  ULE->copyTemplateArgumentsInto(TABuffer);
12774  ExplicitTemplateArgs = &TABuffer;
12775  }
12776 
12777  for (UnresolvedLookupExpr::decls_iterator I = ULE->decls_begin(),
12778  E = ULE->decls_end(); I != E; ++I)
12779  AddOverloadedCallCandidate(*this, I.getPair(), ExplicitTemplateArgs, Args,
12780  CandidateSet, PartialOverloading,
12781  /*KnownValid*/ true);
12782 
12783  if (ULE->requiresADL())
12784  AddArgumentDependentLookupCandidates(ULE->getName(), ULE->getExprLoc(),
12785  Args, ExplicitTemplateArgs,
12786  CandidateSet, PartialOverloading);
12787 }
12788 
12789 /// Add the call candidates from the given set of lookup results to the given
12790 /// overload set. Non-function lookup results are ignored.
12791 void Sema::AddOverloadedCallCandidates(
12792  LookupResult &R, TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs,
12793  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args, OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet) {
12794  for (LookupResult::iterator I = R.begin(), E = R.end(); I != E; ++I)
12795  AddOverloadedCallCandidate(*this, I.getPair(), ExplicitTemplateArgs, Args,
12796  CandidateSet, false, /*KnownValid*/ false);
12797 }
12798 
12799 /// Determine whether a declaration with the specified name could be moved into
12800 /// a different namespace.
12801 static bool canBeDeclaredInNamespace(const DeclarationName &Name) {
12802  switch (Name.getCXXOverloadedOperator()) {
12803  case OO_New: case OO_Array_New:
12804  case OO_Delete: case OO_Array_Delete:
12805  return false;
12806 
12807  default:
12808  return true;
12809  }
12810 }
12811 
12812 /// Attempt to recover from an ill-formed use of a non-dependent name in a
12813 /// template, where the non-dependent name was declared after the template
12814 /// was defined. This is common in code written for a compilers which do not
12815 /// correctly implement two-stage name lookup.
12816 ///
12817 /// Returns true if a viable candidate was found and a diagnostic was issued.
12818 static bool DiagnoseTwoPhaseLookup(
12819  Sema &SemaRef, SourceLocation FnLoc, const CXXScopeSpec &SS,
12820  LookupResult &R, OverloadCandidateSet::CandidateSetKind CSK,
12821  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs, ArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
12822  CXXRecordDecl **FoundInClass = nullptr) {
12823  if (!SemaRef.inTemplateInstantiation() || !SS.isEmpty())
12824  return false;
12825 
12826  for (DeclContext *DC = SemaRef.CurContext; DC; DC = DC->getParent()) {
12827  if (DC->isTransparentContext())
12828  continue;
12829 
12830  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(R, DC);
12831 
12832  if (!R.empty()) {
12833  R.suppressDiagnostics();
12834 
12835  OverloadCandidateSet Candidates(FnLoc, CSK);
12836  SemaRef.AddOverloadedCallCandidates(R, ExplicitTemplateArgs, Args,
12837  Candidates);
12838 
12839  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
12840  OverloadingResult OR =
12841  Candidates.BestViableFunction(SemaRef, FnLoc, Best);
12842 
12843  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC)) {
12844  // We either found non-function declarations or a best viable function
12845  // at class scope. A class-scope lookup result disables ADL. Don't
12846  // look past this, but let the caller know that we found something that
12847  // either is, or might be, usable in this class.
12848  if (FoundInClass) {
12849  *FoundInClass = RD;
12850  if (OR == OR_Success) {
12851  R.clear();
12852  R.addDecl(Best->FoundDecl.getDecl(), Best->FoundDecl.getAccess());
12853  R.resolveKind();
12854  }
12855  }
12856  return false;
12857  }
12858 
12859  if (OR != OR_Success) {
12860  // There wasn't a unique best function or function template.
12861  return false;
12862  }
12863 
12864  // Find the namespaces where ADL would have looked, and suggest
12865  // declaring the function there instead.
12866  Sema::AssociatedNamespaceSet AssociatedNamespaces;
12867  Sema::AssociatedClassSet AssociatedClasses;
12868  SemaRef.FindAssociatedClassesAndNamespaces(FnLoc, Args,
12869  AssociatedNamespaces,
12870  AssociatedClasses);
12871  Sema::AssociatedNamespaceSet SuggestedNamespaces;
12872  if (canBeDeclaredInNamespace(R.getLookupName())) {
12873  DeclContext *Std = SemaRef.getStdNamespace();
12874  for (Sema::AssociatedNamespaceSet::iterator
12875  it = AssociatedNamespaces.begin(),
12876  end = AssociatedNamespaces.end(); it != end; ++it) {
12877  // Never suggest declaring a function within namespace 'std'.
12878  if (Std && Std->Encloses(*it))
12879  continue;
12880 
12881  // Never suggest declaring a function within a namespace with a
12882  // reserved name, like __gnu_cxx.
12883  NamespaceDecl *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(*it);
12884  if (NS &&
12885  NS->getQualifiedNameAsString().find("__") != std::string::npos)
12886  continue;
12887 
12888  SuggestedNamespaces.insert(*it);
12889  }
12890  }
12891 
12892  SemaRef.Diag(R.getNameLoc(), diag::err_not_found_by_two_phase_lookup)
12893  << R.getLookupName();
12894  if (SuggestedNamespaces.empty()) {
12895  SemaRef.Diag(Best->Function->getLocation(),
12896  diag::note_not_found_by_two_phase_lookup)
12897  << R.getLookupName() << 0;
12898  } else if (SuggestedNamespaces.size() == 1) {
12899  SemaRef.Diag(Best->Function->getLocation(),
12900  diag::note_not_found_by_two_phase_lookup)
12901  << R.getLookupName() << 1 << *SuggestedNamespaces.begin();
12902  } else {
12903  // FIXME: It would be useful to list the associated namespaces here,
12904  // but the diagnostics infrastructure doesn't provide a way to produce
12905  // a localized representation of a list of items.
12906  SemaRef.Diag(Best->Function->getLocation(),
12907  diag::note_not_found_by_two_phase_lookup)
12908  << R.getLookupName() << 2;
12909  }
12910 
12911  // Try to recover by calling this function.
12912  return true;
12913  }
12914 
12915  R.clear();
12916  }
12917 
12918  return false;
12919 }
12920 
12921 /// Attempt to recover from ill-formed use of a non-dependent operator in a
12922 /// template, where the non-dependent operator was declared after the template
12923 /// was defined.
12924 ///
12925 /// Returns true if a viable candidate was found and a diagnostic was issued.
12926 static bool
12927 DiagnoseTwoPhaseOperatorLookup(Sema &SemaRef, OverloadedOperatorKind Op,
12928  SourceLocation OpLoc,
12929  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args) {
12930  DeclarationName OpName =
12931  SemaRef.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Op);
12932  LookupResult R(SemaRef, OpName, OpLoc, Sema::LookupOperatorName);
12933  return DiagnoseTwoPhaseLookup(SemaRef, OpLoc, CXXScopeSpec(), R,
12934  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator,
12935  /*ExplicitTemplateArgs=*/nullptr, Args);
12936 }
12937 
12938 namespace {
12939 class BuildRecoveryCallExprRAII {
12940  Sema &SemaRef;
12941 public:
12942  BuildRecoveryCallExprRAII(Sema &S) : SemaRef(S) {
12943  assert(SemaRef.IsBuildingRecoveryCallExpr == false);
12944  SemaRef.IsBuildingRecoveryCallExpr = true;
12945  }
12946 
12947  ~BuildRecoveryCallExprRAII() {
12948  SemaRef.IsBuildingRecoveryCallExpr = false;
12949  }
12950 };
12951 
12952 }
12953 
12954 /// Attempts to recover from a call where no functions were found.
12955 ///
12956 /// This function will do one of three things:
12957 /// * Diagnose, recover, and return a recovery expression.
12958 /// * Diagnose, fail to recover, and return ExprError().
12959 /// * Do not diagnose, do not recover, and return ExprResult(). The caller is
12960 /// expected to diagnose as appropriate.
12961 static ExprResult
12962 BuildRecoveryCallExpr(Sema &SemaRef, Scope *S, Expr *Fn,
12963  UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE,
12964  SourceLocation LParenLoc,
12965  MutableArrayRef<Expr *> Args,
12966  SourceLocation RParenLoc,
12967  bool EmptyLookup, bool AllowTypoCorrection) {
12968  // Do not try to recover if it is already building a recovery call.
12969  // This stops infinite loops for template instantiations like
12970  //
12971  // template <typename T> auto foo(T t) -> decltype(foo(t)) {}
12972  // template <typename T> auto foo(T t) -> decltype(foo(&t)) {}
12973  if (SemaRef.IsBuildingRecoveryCallExpr)
12974  return ExprResult();
12975  BuildRecoveryCallExprRAII RCE(SemaRef);
12976 
12977  CXXScopeSpec SS;
12978  SS.Adopt(ULE->getQualifierLoc());
12979  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = ULE->getTemplateKeywordLoc();
12980 
12981  TemplateArgumentListInfo TABuffer;
12982  TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs = nullptr;
12983  if (ULE->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
12984  ULE->copyTemplateArgumentsInto(TABuffer);
12985  ExplicitTemplateArgs = &TABuffer;
12986  }
12987 
12988  LookupResult R(SemaRef, ULE->getName(), ULE->getNameLoc(),
12989  Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
12990  CXXRecordDecl *FoundInClass = nullptr;
12991  if (DiagnoseTwoPhaseLookup(SemaRef, Fn->getExprLoc(), SS, R,
12992  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal,
12993  ExplicitTemplateArgs, Args, &FoundInClass)) {
12994  // OK, diagnosed a two-phase lookup issue.
12995  } else if (EmptyLookup) {
12996  // Try to recover from an empty lookup with typo correction.
12997  R.clear();
12998  NoTypoCorrectionCCC NoTypoValidator{};
12999  FunctionCallFilterCCC FunctionCallValidator(SemaRef, Args.size(),
13000  ExplicitTemplateArgs != nullptr,
13001  dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(Fn));
13002  CorrectionCandidateCallback &Validator =
13003  AllowTypoCorrection
13004  ? static_cast<CorrectionCandidateCallback &>(FunctionCallValidator)
13005  : static_cast<CorrectionCandidateCallback &>(NoTypoValidator);
13006  if (SemaRef.DiagnoseEmptyLookup(S, SS, R, Validator, ExplicitTemplateArgs,
13007  Args))
13008  return ExprError();
13009  } else if (FoundInClass && SemaRef.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat) {
13010  // We found a usable declaration of the name in a dependent base of some
13011  // enclosing class.
13012  // FIXME: We should also explain why the candidates found by name lookup
13013  // were not viable.
13014  if (SemaRef.DiagnoseDependentMemberLookup(R))
13015  return ExprError();
13016  } else {
13017  // We had viable candidates and couldn't recover; let the caller diagnose
13018  // this.
13019  return ExprResult();
13020  }
13021 
13022  // If we get here, we should have issued a diagnostic and formed a recovery
13023  // lookup result.
13024  assert(!R.empty() && "lookup results empty despite recovery");
13025 
13026  // If recovery created an ambiguity, just bail out.
13027  if (R.isAmbiguous()) {
13028  R.suppressDiagnostics();
13029  return ExprError();
13030  }
13031 
13032  // Build an implicit member call if appropriate. Just drop the
13033  // casts and such from the call, we don't really care.
13034  ExprResult NewFn = ExprError();
13035  if ((*R.begin())->isCXXClassMember())
13036  NewFn = SemaRef.BuildPossibleImplicitMemberExpr(SS, TemplateKWLoc, R,
13037  ExplicitTemplateArgs, S);
13038  else if (ExplicitTemplateArgs || TemplateKWLoc.isValid())
13039  NewFn = SemaRef.BuildTemplateIdExpr(SS, TemplateKWLoc, R, false,
13040  ExplicitTemplateArgs);
13041  else
13042  NewFn = SemaRef.BuildDeclarationNameExpr(SS, R, false);
13043 
13044  if (NewFn.isInvalid())
13045  return ExprError();
13046 
13047  // This shouldn't cause an infinite loop because we're giving it
13048  // an expression with viable lookup results, which should never
13049  // end up here.
13050  return SemaRef.BuildCallExpr(/*Scope*/ nullptr, NewFn.get(), LParenLoc,
13051  MultiExprArg(Args.data(), Args.size()),
13052  RParenLoc);
13053 }
13054 
13055 /// Constructs and populates an OverloadedCandidateSet from
13056 /// the given function.
13057 /// \returns true when an the ExprResult output parameter has been set.
13058 bool Sema::buildOverloadedCallSet(Scope *S, Expr *Fn,
13059  UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE,
13060  MultiExprArg Args,
13061  SourceLocation RParenLoc,
13062  OverloadCandidateSet *CandidateSet,
13063  ExprResult *Result) {
13064 #ifndef NDEBUG
13065  if (ULE->requiresADL()) {
13066  // To do ADL, we must have found an unqualified name.
13067  assert(!ULE->getQualifier() && "qualified name with ADL");
13068 
13069  // We don't perform ADL for implicit declarations of builtins.
13070  // Verify that this was correctly set up.
13071  FunctionDecl *F;
13072  if (ULE->decls_begin() != ULE->decls_end() &&
13073  ULE->decls_begin() + 1 == ULE->decls_end() &&
13074  (F = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(*ULE->decls_begin())) &&
13075  F->getBuiltinID() && F->isImplicit())
13076  llvm_unreachable("performing ADL for builtin");
13077 
13078  // We don't perform ADL in C.
13079  assert(getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && "ADL enabled in C");
13080  }
13081 #endif
13082 
13083  UnbridgedCastsSet UnbridgedCasts;
13084  if (checkArgPlaceholdersForOverload(*this, Args, UnbridgedCasts)) {
13085  *Result = ExprError();
13086  return true;
13087  }
13088 
13089  // Add the functions denoted by the callee to the set of candidate
13090  // functions, including those from argument-dependent lookup.
13091  AddOverloadedCallCandidates(ULE, Args, *CandidateSet);
13092 
13093  if (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat &&
13094  CurContext->isDependentContext() && !isSFINAEContext() &&
13095  (isa<FunctionDecl>(CurContext) || isa<CXXRecordDecl>(CurContext))) {
13096 
13097  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
13098  if (CandidateSet->empty() ||
13099  CandidateSet->BestViableFunction(*this, Fn->getBeginLoc(), Best) ==
13100  OR_No_Viable_Function) {
13101  // In Microsoft mode, if we are inside a template class member function
13102  // then create a type dependent CallExpr. The goal is to postpone name
13103  // lookup to instantiation time to be able to search into type dependent
13104  // base classes.
13105  CallExpr *CE =
13106  CallExpr::Create(Context, Fn, Args, Context.DependentTy, VK_PRValue,
13107  RParenLoc, CurFPFeatureOverrides());
13108  CE->markDependentForPostponedNameLookup();
13109  *Result = CE;
13110  return true;
13111  }
13112  }
13113 
13114  if (CandidateSet->empty())
13115  return false;
13116 
13117  UnbridgedCasts.restore();
13118  return false;
13119 }
13120 
13121 // Guess at what the return type for an unresolvable overload should be.
13122 static QualType chooseRecoveryType(OverloadCandidateSet &CS,
13123  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator *Best) {
13124  llvm::Optional<QualType> Result;
13125  // Adjust Type after seeing a candidate.
13126  auto ConsiderCandidate = [&](const OverloadCandidate &Candidate) {
13127  if (!Candidate.Function)
13128  return;
13129  if (Candidate.Function->isInvalidDecl())
13130  return;
13131  QualType T = Candidate.Function->getReturnType();
13132  if (T.isNull())
13133  return;
13134  if (!Result)
13135  Result = T;
13136  else if (Result != T)
13137  Result = QualType();
13138  };
13139 
13140  // Look for an unambiguous type from a progressively larger subset.
13141  // e.g. if types disagree, but all *viable* overloads return int, choose int.
13142  //
13143  // First, consider only the best candidate.
13144  if (Best && *Best != CS.end())
13145  ConsiderCandidate(**Best);
13146  // Next, consider only viable candidates.
13147  if (!Result)
13148  for (const auto &C : CS)
13149  if (C.Viable)
13150  ConsiderCandidate(C);
13151  // Finally, consider all candidates.
13152  if (!Result)
13153  for (const auto &C : CS)
13154  ConsiderCandidate(C);
13155 
13156  if (!Result)
13157  return QualType();
13158  auto Value = Result.getValue();
13159  if (Value.isNull() || Value->isUndeducedType())
13160  return QualType();
13161  return Value;
13162 }
13163 
13164 /// FinishOverloadedCallExpr - given an OverloadCandidateSet, builds and returns
13165 /// the completed call expression. If overload resolution fails, emits
13166 /// diagnostics and returns ExprError()
13167 static ExprResult FinishOverloadedCallExpr(Sema &SemaRef, Scope *S, Expr *Fn,
13168  UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE,
13169  SourceLocation LParenLoc,
13170  MultiExprArg Args,
13171  SourceLocation RParenLoc,
13172  Expr *ExecConfig,
13173  OverloadCandidateSet *CandidateSet,
13174  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator *Best,
13175  OverloadingResult OverloadResult,
13176  bool AllowTypoCorrection) {
13177  switch (OverloadResult) {
13178  case OR_Success: {
13179  FunctionDecl *FDecl = (*Best)->Function;
13180  SemaRef.CheckUnresolvedLookupAccess(ULE, (*Best)->FoundDecl);
13181  if (SemaRef.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(FDecl, ULE->getNameLoc()))
13182  return ExprError();
13183  Fn = SemaRef.FixOverloadedFunctionReference(Fn, (*Best)->FoundDecl, FDecl);
13184  return SemaRef.BuildResolvedCallExpr(Fn, FDecl, LParenLoc, Args, RParenLoc,
13185  ExecConfig, /*IsExecConfig=*/false,
13186  (*Best)->IsADLCandidate);
13187  }
13188 
13189  case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
13190  // Try to recover by looking for viable functions which the user might
13191  // have meant to call.
13192  ExprResult Recovery = BuildRecoveryCallExpr(SemaRef, S, Fn, ULE, LParenLoc,
13193  Args, RParenLoc,
13194  CandidateSet->empty(),
13195  AllowTypoCorrection);
13196  if (Recovery.isInvalid() || Recovery.isUsable())
13197  return Recovery;
13198 
13199  // If the user passes in a function that we can't take the address of, we
13200  // generally end up emitting really bad error messages. Here, we attempt to
13201  // emit better ones.
13202  for (const Expr *Arg : Args) {
13203  if (!Arg->getType()->isFunctionType())
13204  continue;
13205  if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) {
13206  auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
13207  if (FD &&
13208  !SemaRef.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(FD, /*Complain=*/true,
13209  Arg->getExprLoc()))
13210  return ExprError();
13211  }
13212  }
13213 
13214  CandidateSet->NoteCandidates(
13215  PartialDiagnosticAt(
13216  Fn->getBeginLoc(),
13217  SemaRef.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_viable_function_in_call)
13218  << ULE->getName() << Fn->getSourceRange()),
13219  SemaRef, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
13220  break;
13221  }
13222 
13223  case OR_Ambiguous:
13224  CandidateSet->NoteCandidates(
13225  PartialDiagnosticAt(Fn->getBeginLoc(),
13226  SemaRef.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_call)
13227  << ULE->getName() << Fn->getSourceRange()),
13228  SemaRef, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args);
13229  break;
13230 
13231  case OR_Deleted: {
13232  CandidateSet->NoteCandidates(
13233  PartialDiagnosticAt(Fn->getBeginLoc(),
13234  SemaRef.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_deleted_call)
13235  << ULE->getName() << Fn->getSourceRange()),
13236  SemaRef, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
13237 
13238  // We emitted an error for the unavailable/deleted function call but keep
13239  // the call in the AST.
13240  FunctionDecl *FDecl = (*Best)->Function;
13241  Fn = SemaRef.FixOverloadedFunctionReference(Fn, (*Best)->FoundDecl, FDecl);
13242  return SemaRef.BuildResolvedCallExpr(Fn, FDecl, LParenLoc, Args, RParenLoc,
13243  ExecConfig, /*IsExecConfig=*/false,
13244  (*Best)->IsADLCandidate);
13245  }
13246  }
13247 
13248  // Overload resolution failed, try to recover.
13249  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> SubExprs = {Fn};
13250  SubExprs.append(Args.begin(), Args.end());
13251  return SemaRef.CreateRecoveryExpr(Fn->getBeginLoc(), RParenLoc, SubExprs,
13252  chooseRecoveryType(*CandidateSet, Best));
13253 }
13254 
13255 static void markUnaddressableCandidatesUnviable(Sema &S,
13256  OverloadCandidateSet &CS) {
13257  for (auto I = CS.begin(), E = CS.end(); I != E; ++I) {
13258  if (I->Viable &&
13259  !S.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(I->Function, /*Complain=*/false)) {
13260  I->Viable = false;
13261  I->FailureKind = ovl_fail_addr_not_available;
13262  }
13263  }
13264 }
13265 
13266 /// BuildOverloadedCallExpr - Given the call expression that calls Fn
13267 /// (which eventually refers to the declaration Func) and the call
13268 /// arguments Args/NumArgs, attempt to resolve the function call down
13269 /// to a specific function. If overload resolution succeeds, returns
13270 /// the call expression produced by overload resolution.
13271 /// Otherwise, emits diagnostics and returns ExprError.
13272 ExprResult Sema::BuildOverloadedCallExpr(Scope *S, Expr *Fn,
13273  UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE,
13274  SourceLocation LParenLoc,
13275  MultiExprArg Args,
13276  SourceLocation RParenLoc,
13277  Expr *ExecConfig,
13278  bool AllowTypoCorrection,
13279  bool CalleesAddressIsTaken) {
13280  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(Fn->getExprLoc(),
13281  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
13282  ExprResult result;
13283 
13284  if (buildOverloadedCallSet(S, Fn, ULE, Args, LParenLoc, &CandidateSet,
13285  &result))
13286  return result;
13287 
13288  // If the user handed us something like `(&Foo)(Bar)`, we need to ensure that
13289  // functions that aren't addressible are considered unviable.
13290  if (CalleesAddressIsTaken)
13291  markUnaddressableCandidatesUnviable(*this, CandidateSet);
13292 
13293  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
13294  OverloadingResult OverloadResult =
13295  CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, Fn->getBeginLoc(), Best);
13296 
13297  return FinishOverloadedCallExpr(*this, S, Fn, ULE, LParenLoc, Args, RParenLoc,
13298  ExecConfig, &CandidateSet, &Best,
13299  OverloadResult, AllowTypoCorrection);
13300 }
13301 
13302 static bool IsOverloaded(const UnresolvedSetImpl &Functions) {
13303  return Functions.size() > 1 ||
13304  (Functions.size() == 1 &&
13305  isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>((*Functions.begin())->getUnderlyingDecl()));
13306 }
13307 
13308 ExprResult Sema::CreateUnresolvedLookupExpr(CXXRecordDecl *NamingClass,
13309  NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNSLoc,
13310  DeclarationNameInfo DNI,
13311  const UnresolvedSetImpl &Fns,
13312  bool PerformADL) {
13313  return UnresolvedLookupExpr::Create(Context, NamingClass, NNSLoc, DNI,
13314  PerformADL, IsOverloaded(Fns),
13315  Fns.begin(), Fns.end());
13316 }
13317 
13318 /// Create a unary operation that may resolve to an overloaded
13319 /// operator.
13320 ///
13321 /// \param OpLoc The location of the operator itself (e.g., '*').
13322 ///
13323 /// \param Opc The UnaryOperatorKind that describes this operator.
13324 ///
13325 /// \param Fns The set of non-member functions that will be
13326 /// considered by overload resolution. The caller needs to build this
13327 /// set based on the context using, e.g.,
13328 /// LookupOverloadedOperatorName() and ArgumentDependentLookup(). This
13329 /// set should not contain any member functions; those will be added
13330 /// by CreateOverloadedUnaryOp().
13331 ///
13332 /// \param Input The input argument.
13333 ExprResult
13334 Sema::CreateOverloadedUnaryOp(SourceLocation OpLoc, UnaryOperatorKind Opc,
13335  const UnresolvedSetImpl &Fns,
13336  Expr *Input, bool PerformADL) {
13337  OverloadedOperatorKind Op = UnaryOperator::getOverloadedOperator(Opc);
13338  assert(Op != OO_None && "Invalid opcode for overloaded unary operator");
13339  DeclarationName OpName = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Op);
13340  // TODO: provide better source location info.
13341  DeclarationNameInfo OpNameInfo(OpName, OpLoc);
13342 
13343  if (checkPlaceholderForOverload(*this, Input))
13344  return ExprError();
13345 
13346  Expr *Args[2] = { Input, nullptr };
13347  unsigned NumArgs = 1;
13348 
13349  // For post-increment and post-decrement, add the implicit '0' as
13350  // the second argument, so that we know this is a post-increment or
13351  // post-decrement.
13352  if (Opc == UO_PostInc || Opc == UO_PostDec) {
13353  llvm::APSInt Zero(Context.getTypeSize(Context.IntTy), false);
13354  Args[1] = IntegerLiteral::Create(Context, Zero, Context.IntTy,
13355  SourceLocation());
13356  NumArgs = 2;
13357  }
13358 
13359  ArrayRef<Expr *> ArgsArray(Args, NumArgs);
13360 
13361  if (Input->isTypeDependent()) {
13362  if (Fns.empty())
13363  return UnaryOperator::Create(Context, Input, Opc, Context.DependentTy,
13364  VK_PRValue, OK_Ordinary, OpLoc, false,
13365  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
13366 
13367  CXXRecordDecl *NamingClass = nullptr; // lookup ignores member operators
13368  ExprResult Fn = CreateUnresolvedLookupExpr(
13369  NamingClass, NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), OpNameInfo, Fns);
13370  if (Fn.isInvalid())
13371  return ExprError();
13372  return CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(Context, Op, Fn.get(), ArgsArray,
13373  Context.DependentTy, VK_PRValue, OpLoc,
13374  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
13375  }
13376 
13377  // Build an empty overload set.
13378  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(OpLoc, OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator);
13379 
13380  // Add the candidates from the given function set.
13381  AddNonMemberOperatorCandidates(Fns, ArgsArray, CandidateSet);
13382 
13383  // Add operator candidates that are member functions.
13384  AddMemberOperatorCandidates(Op, OpLoc, ArgsArray, CandidateSet);
13385 
13386  // Add candidates from ADL.
13387  if (PerformADL) {
13388  AddArgumentDependentLookupCandidates(OpName, OpLoc, ArgsArray,
13389  /*ExplicitTemplateArgs*/nullptr,
13390  CandidateSet);
13391  }
13392 
13393  // Add builtin operator candidates.
13394  AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates(Op, OpLoc, ArgsArray, CandidateSet);
13395 
13396  bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
13397 
13398  // Perform overload resolution.
13399  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
13400  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, OpLoc, Best)) {
13401  case OR_Success: {
13402  // We found a built-in operator or an overloaded operator.
13403  FunctionDecl *FnDecl = Best->Function;
13404 
13405  if (FnDecl) {
13406  Expr *Base = nullptr;
13407  // We matched an overloaded operator. Build a call to that
13408  // operator.
13409 
13410  // Convert the arguments.
13411  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FnDecl)) {
13412  CheckMemberOperatorAccess(OpLoc, Args[0], nullptr, Best->FoundDecl);
13413 
13414  ExprResult InputRes =
13415  PerformObjectArgumentInitialization(Input, /*Qualifier=*/nullptr,
13416  Best->FoundDecl, Method);
13417  if (InputRes.isInvalid())
13418  return ExprError();
13419  Base = Input = InputRes.get();
13420  } else {
13421  // Convert the arguments.
13422  ExprResult InputInit
13423  = PerformCopyInitialization(InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(
13424  Context,
13425  FnDecl->getParamDecl(0)),
13426  SourceLocation(),
13427  Input);
13428  if (InputInit.isInvalid())
13429  return ExprError();
13430  Input = InputInit.get();
13431  }
13432 
13433  // Build the actual expression node.
13434  ExprResult FnExpr = CreateFunctionRefExpr(*this, FnDecl, Best->FoundDecl,
13435  Base, HadMultipleCandidates,
13436  OpLoc);
13437  if (FnExpr.isInvalid())
13438  return ExprError();
13439 
13440  // Determine the result type.
13441  QualType ResultTy = FnDecl->getReturnType();
13442  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultTy);
13443  ResultTy = ResultTy.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
13444 
13445  Args[0] = Input;
13446  CallExpr *TheCall = CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(
13447  Context, Op, FnExpr.get(), ArgsArray, ResultTy, VK, OpLoc,
13448  CurFPFeatureOverrides(), Best->IsADLCandidate);
13449 
13450  if (CheckCallReturnType(FnDecl->getReturnType(), OpLoc, TheCall, FnDecl))
13451  return ExprError();
13452 
13453  if (CheckFunctionCall(FnDecl, TheCall,
13454  FnDecl->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()))
13455  return ExprError();
13456  return CheckForImmediateInvocation(MaybeBindToTemporary(TheCall), FnDecl);
13457  } else {
13458  // We matched a built-in operator. Convert the arguments, then
13459  // break out so that we will build the appropriate built-in
13460  // operator node.
13461  ExprResult InputRes = PerformImplicitConversion(
13462  Input, Best->BuiltinParamTypes[0], Best->Conversions[0], AA_Passing,
13463  CCK_ForBuiltinOverloadedOp);
13464  if (InputRes.isInvalid())
13465  return ExprError();
13466  Input = InputRes.get();
13467  break;
13468  }
13469  }
13470 
13471  case OR_No_Viable_Function:
13472  // This is an erroneous use of an operator which can be overloaded by
13473  // a non-member function. Check for non-member operators which were
13474  // defined too late to be candidates.
13475  if (DiagnoseTwoPhaseOperatorLookup(*this, Op, OpLoc, ArgsArray))
13476  // FIXME: Recover by calling the found function.
13477  return ExprError();
13478 
13479  // No viable function; fall through to handling this as a
13480  // built-in operator, which will produce an error message for us.
13481  break;
13482 
13483  case OR_Ambiguous:
13484  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
13485  PartialDiagnosticAt(OpLoc,
13486  PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_oper_unary)
13487  << UnaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc)
13488  << Input->getType() << Input->getSourceRange()),
13489  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, ArgsArray,
13490  UnaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc), OpLoc);
13491  return ExprError();
13492 
13493  case OR_Deleted:
13494  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
13495  PartialDiagnosticAt(OpLoc, PDiag(diag::err_ovl_deleted_oper)
13496  << UnaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc)
13497  << Input->getSourceRange()),
13498  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, ArgsArray, UnaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc),
13499  OpLoc);
13500  return ExprError();
13501  }
13502 
13503  // Either we found no viable overloaded operator or we matched a
13504  // built-in operator. In either case, fall through to trying to
13505  // build a built-in operation.
13506  return CreateBuiltinUnaryOp(OpLoc, Opc, Input);
13507 }
13508 
13509 /// Perform lookup for an overloaded binary operator.
13510 void Sema::LookupOverloadedBinOp(OverloadCandidateSet &CandidateSet,
13511  OverloadedOperatorKind Op,
13512  const UnresolvedSetImpl &Fns,
13513  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args, bool PerformADL) {
13514  SourceLocation OpLoc = CandidateSet.getLocation();
13515 
13516  OverloadedOperatorKind ExtraOp =
13517  CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().AllowRewrittenCandidates
13518  ? getRewrittenOverloadedOperator(Op)
13519  : OO_None;
13520 
13521  // Add the candidates from the given function set. This also adds the
13522  // rewritten candidates using these functions if necessary.
13523  AddNonMemberOperatorCandidates(Fns, Args, CandidateSet);
13524 
13525  // Add operator candidates that are member functions.
13526  AddMemberOperatorCandidates(Op, OpLoc, Args, CandidateSet);
13527  if (CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().shouldAddReversed(Op))
13528  AddMemberOperatorCandidates(Op, OpLoc, {Args[1], Args[0]}, CandidateSet,
13529  OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed);
13530 
13531  // In C++20, also add any rewritten member candidates.
13532  if (ExtraOp) {
13533  AddMemberOperatorCandidates(ExtraOp, OpLoc, Args, CandidateSet);
13534  if (CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().shouldAddReversed(ExtraOp))
13535  AddMemberOperatorCandidates(ExtraOp, OpLoc, {Args[1], Args[0]},
13536  CandidateSet,
13537  OverloadCandidateParamOrder::Reversed);
13538  }
13539 
13540  // Add candidates from ADL. Per [over.match.oper]p2, this lookup is not
13541  // performed for an assignment operator (nor for operator[] nor operator->,
13542  // which don't get here).
13543  if (Op != OO_Equal && PerformADL) {
13544  DeclarationName OpName = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Op);
13545  AddArgumentDependentLookupCandidates(OpName, OpLoc, Args,
13546  /*ExplicitTemplateArgs*/ nullptr,
13547  CandidateSet);
13548  if (ExtraOp) {
13549  DeclarationName ExtraOpName =
13550  Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(ExtraOp);
13551  AddArgumentDependentLookupCandidates(ExtraOpName, OpLoc, Args,
13552  /*ExplicitTemplateArgs*/ nullptr,
13553  CandidateSet);
13554  }
13555  }
13556 
13557  // Add builtin operator candidates.
13558  //
13559  // FIXME: We don't add any rewritten candidates here. This is strictly
13560  // incorrect; a builtin candidate could be hidden by a non-viable candidate,
13561  // resulting in our selecting a rewritten builtin candidate. For example:
13562  //
13563  // enum class E { e };
13564  // bool operator!=(E, E) requires false;
13565  // bool k = E::e != E::e;
13566  //
13567  // ... should select the rewritten builtin candidate 'operator==(E, E)'. But
13568  // it seems unreasonable to consider rewritten builtin candidates. A core
13569  // issue has been filed proposing to removed this requirement.
13570  AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates(Op, OpLoc, Args, CandidateSet);
13571 }
13572 
13573 /// Create a binary operation that may resolve to an overloaded
13574 /// operator.
13575 ///
13576 /// \param OpLoc The location of the operator itself (e.g., '+').
13577 ///
13578 /// \param Opc The BinaryOperatorKind that describes this operator.
13579 ///
13580 /// \param Fns The set of non-member functions that will be
13581 /// considered by overload resolution. The caller needs to build this
13582 /// set based on the context using, e.g.,
13583 /// LookupOverloadedOperatorName() and ArgumentDependentLookup(). This
13584 /// set should not contain any member functions; those will be added
13585 /// by CreateOverloadedBinOp().
13586 ///
13587 /// \param LHS Left-hand argument.
13588 /// \param RHS Right-hand argument.
13589 /// \param PerformADL Whether to consider operator candidates found by ADL.
13590 /// \param AllowRewrittenCandidates Whether to consider candidates found by
13591 /// C++20 operator rewrites.
13592 /// \param DefaultedFn If we are synthesizing a defaulted operator function,
13593 /// the function in question. Such a function is never a candidate in
13594 /// our overload resolution. This also enables synthesizing a three-way
13595 /// comparison from < and == as described in C++20 [class.spaceship]p1.
13596 ExprResult Sema::CreateOverloadedBinOp(SourceLocation OpLoc,
13597  BinaryOperatorKind Opc,
13598  const UnresolvedSetImpl &Fns, Expr *LHS,
13599  Expr *RHS, bool PerformADL,
13600  bool AllowRewrittenCandidates,
13601  FunctionDecl *DefaultedFn) {
13602  Expr *Args[2] = { LHS, RHS };
13603  LHS=RHS=nullptr; // Please use only Args instead of LHS/RHS couple
13604 
13605  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)
13606  AllowRewrittenCandidates = false;
13607 
13608  OverloadedOperatorKind Op = BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOperator(Opc);
13609 
13610  // If either side is type-dependent, create an appropriate dependent
13611  // expression.
13612  if (Args[0]->isTypeDependent() || Args[1]->isTypeDependent()) {
13613  if (Fns.empty()) {
13614  // If there are no functions to store, just build a dependent
13615  // BinaryOperator or CompoundAssignment.
13616  if (BinaryOperator::isCompoundAssignmentOp(Opc))
13617  return CompoundAssignOperator::Create(
13618  Context, Args[0], Args[1], Opc, Context.DependentTy, VK_LValue,
13619  OK_Ordinary, OpLoc, CurFPFeatureOverrides(), Context.DependentTy,
13620  Context.DependentTy);
13621  return BinaryOperator::Create(
13622  Context, Args[0], Args[1], Opc, Context.DependentTy, VK_PRValue,
13623  OK_Ordinary, OpLoc, CurFPFeatureOverrides());
13624  }
13625 
13626  // FIXME: save results of ADL from here?
13627  CXXRecordDecl *NamingClass = nullptr; // lookup ignores member operators
13628  // TODO: provide better source location info in DNLoc component.
13629  DeclarationName OpName = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Op);
13630  DeclarationNameInfo OpNameInfo(OpName, OpLoc);
13631  ExprResult Fn = CreateUnresolvedLookupExpr(
13632  NamingClass, NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), OpNameInfo, Fns, PerformADL);
13633  if (Fn.isInvalid())
13634  return ExprError();
13635  return CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(Context, Op, Fn.get(), Args,
13636  Context.DependentTy, VK_PRValue, OpLoc,
13637  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
13638  }
13639 
13640  // Always do placeholder-like conversions on the RHS.
13641  if (checkPlaceholderForOverload(*this, Args[1]))
13642  return ExprError();
13643 
13644  // Do placeholder-like conversion on the LHS; note that we should
13645  // not get here with a PseudoObject LHS.
13646  assert(Args[0]->getObjectKind() != OK_ObjCProperty);
13647  if (checkPlaceholderForOverload(*this, Args[0]))
13648  return ExprError();
13649 
13650  // If this is the assignment operator, we only perform overload resolution
13651  // if the left-hand side is a class or enumeration type. This is actually
13652  // a hack. The standard requires that we do overload resolution between the
13653  // various built-in candidates, but as DR507 points out, this can lead to
13654  // problems. So we do it this way, which pretty much follows what GCC does.
13655  // Note that we go the traditional code path for compound assignment forms.
13656  if (Opc == BO_Assign && !Args[0]->getType()->isOverloadableType())
13657  return CreateBuiltinBinOp(OpLoc, Opc, Args[0], Args[1]);
13658 
13659  // If this is the .* operator, which is not overloadable, just
13660  // create a built-in binary operator.
13661  if (Opc == BO_PtrMemD)
13662  return CreateBuiltinBinOp(OpLoc, Opc, Args[0], Args[1]);
13663 
13664  // Build the overload set.
13665  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(
13666  OpLoc, OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator,
13667  OverloadCandidateSet::OperatorRewriteInfo(Op, AllowRewrittenCandidates));
13668  if (DefaultedFn)
13669  CandidateSet.exclude(DefaultedFn);
13670  LookupOverloadedBinOp(CandidateSet, Op, Fns, Args, PerformADL);
13671 
13672  bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
13673 
13674  // Perform overload resolution.
13675  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
13676  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, OpLoc, Best)) {
13677  case OR_Success: {
13678  // We found a built-in operator or an overloaded operator.
13679  FunctionDecl *FnDecl = Best->Function;
13680 
13681  bool IsReversed = Best->isReversed();
13682  if (IsReversed)
13683  std::swap(Args[0], Args[1]);
13684 
13685  if (FnDecl) {
13686  Expr *Base = nullptr;
13687  // We matched an overloaded operator. Build a call to that
13688  // operator.
13689 
13690  OverloadedOperatorKind ChosenOp =
13691  FnDecl->getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator();
13692 
13693  // C++2a [over.match.oper]p9:
13694  // If a rewritten operator== candidate is selected by overload
13695  // resolution for an operator@, its return type shall be cv bool
13696  if (Best->RewriteKind && ChosenOp == OO_EqualEqual &&
13697  !FnDecl->getReturnType()->isBooleanType()) {
13698  bool IsExtension =
13699  FnDecl->getReturnType()->isIntegralOrUnscopedEnumerationType();
13700  Diag(OpLoc, IsExtension ? diag::ext_ovl_rewrite_equalequal_not_bool
13701  : diag::err_ovl_rewrite_equalequal_not_bool)
13702  << FnDecl->getReturnType() << BinaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc)
13703  << Args[0]->getSourceRange() << Args[1]->getSourceRange();
13704  Diag(FnDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_declared_at);
13705  if (!IsExtension)
13706  return ExprError();
13707  }
13708 
13709  if (AllowRewrittenCandidates && !IsReversed &&
13710  CandidateSet.getRewriteInfo().isReversible()) {
13711  // We could have reversed this operator, but didn't. Check if some
13712  // reversed form was a viable candidate, and if so, if it had a
13713  // better conversion for either parameter. If so, this call is
13714  // formally ambiguous, and allowing it is an extension.
13715  llvm::SmallVector<FunctionDecl*, 4> AmbiguousWith;
13716  for (OverloadCandidate &Cand : CandidateSet) {
13717  if (Cand.Viable && Cand.Function && Cand.isReversed() &&
13718  haveSameParameterTypes(Context, Cand.Function, FnDecl, 2)) {
13719  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx < 2; ++ArgIdx) {
13720  if (CompareImplicitConversionSequences(
13721  *this, OpLoc, Cand.Conversions[ArgIdx],
13722  Best->Conversions[ArgIdx]) ==
13723  ImplicitConversionSequence::Better) {
13724  AmbiguousWith.push_back(Cand.Function);
13725  break;
13726  }
13727  }
13728  }
13729  }
13730 
13731  if (!AmbiguousWith.empty()) {
13732  bool AmbiguousWithSelf =
13733  AmbiguousWith.size() == 1 &&
13734  declaresSameEntity(AmbiguousWith.front(), FnDecl);
13735  Diag(OpLoc, diag::ext_ovl_ambiguous_oper_binary_reversed)
13736  << BinaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc)
13737  << Args[0]->getType() << Args[1]->getType() << AmbiguousWithSelf
13738  << Args[0]->getSourceRange() << Args[1]->getSourceRange();
13739  if (AmbiguousWithSelf) {
13740  Diag(FnDecl->getLocation(),
13741  diag::note_ovl_ambiguous_oper_binary_reversed_self);
13742  } else {
13743  Diag(FnDecl->getLocation(),
13744  diag::note_ovl_ambiguous_oper_binary_selected_candidate);
13745  for (auto *F : AmbiguousWith)
13746  Diag(F->getLocation(),
13747  diag::note_ovl_ambiguous_oper_binary_reversed_candidate);
13748  }
13749  }
13750  }
13751 
13752  // Convert the arguments.
13753  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FnDecl)) {
13754  // Best->Access is only meaningful for class members.
13755  CheckMemberOperatorAccess(OpLoc, Args[0], Args[1], Best->FoundDecl);
13756 
13757  ExprResult Arg1 =
13758  PerformCopyInitialization(
13759  InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context,
13760  FnDecl->getParamDecl(0)),
