13761  SourceLocation(), Args[1]);
13762  if (Arg1.isInvalid())
13763  return ExprError();
13764 
13765  ExprResult Arg0 =
13766  PerformObjectArgumentInitialization(Args[0], /*Qualifier=*/nullptr,
13767  Best->FoundDecl, Method);
13768  if (Arg0.isInvalid())
13769  return ExprError();
13770  Base = Args[0] = Arg0.getAs<Expr>();
13771  Args[1] = RHS = Arg1.getAs<Expr>();
13772  } else {
13773  // Convert the arguments.
13774  ExprResult Arg0 = PerformCopyInitialization(
13775  InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context,
13776  FnDecl->getParamDecl(0)),
13777  SourceLocation(), Args[0]);
13778  if (Arg0.isInvalid())
13779  return ExprError();
13780 
13781  ExprResult Arg1 =
13782  PerformCopyInitialization(
13783  InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context,
13784  FnDecl->getParamDecl(1)),
13785  SourceLocation(), Args[1]);
13786  if (Arg1.isInvalid())
13787  return ExprError();
13788  Args[0] = LHS = Arg0.getAs<Expr>();
13789  Args[1] = RHS = Arg1.getAs<Expr>();
13790  }
13791 
13792  // Build the actual expression node.
13793  ExprResult FnExpr = CreateFunctionRefExpr(*this, FnDecl,
13794  Best->FoundDecl, Base,
13795  HadMultipleCandidates, OpLoc);
13796  if (FnExpr.isInvalid())
13797  return ExprError();
13798 
13799  // Determine the result type.
13800  QualType ResultTy = FnDecl->getReturnType();
13801  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultTy);
13802  ResultTy = ResultTy.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
13803 
13804  CXXOperatorCallExpr *TheCall = CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(
13805  Context, ChosenOp, FnExpr.get(), Args, ResultTy, VK, OpLoc,
13806  CurFPFeatureOverrides(), Best->IsADLCandidate);
13807 
13808  if (CheckCallReturnType(FnDecl->getReturnType(), OpLoc, TheCall,
13809  FnDecl))
13810  return ExprError();
13811 
13812  ArrayRef<const Expr *> ArgsArray(Args, 2);
13813  const Expr *ImplicitThis = nullptr;
13814  // Cut off the implicit 'this'.
13815  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FnDecl)) {
13816  ImplicitThis = ArgsArray[0];
13817  ArgsArray = ArgsArray.slice(1);
13818  }
13819 
13820  // Check for a self move.
13821  if (Op == OO_Equal)
13822  DiagnoseSelfMove(Args[0], Args[1], OpLoc);
13823 
13824  if (ImplicitThis) {
13825  QualType ThisType = Context.getPointerType(ImplicitThis->getType());
13826  QualType ThisTypeFromDecl = Context.getPointerType(
13827  cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FnDecl)->getThisObjectType());
13828 
13829  CheckArgAlignment(OpLoc, FnDecl, "'this'", ThisType,
13830  ThisTypeFromDecl);
13831  }
13832 
13833  checkCall(FnDecl, nullptr, ImplicitThis, ArgsArray,
13834  isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FnDecl), OpLoc, TheCall->getSourceRange(),
13835  VariadicDoesNotApply);
13836 
13837  ExprResult R = MaybeBindToTemporary(TheCall);
13838  if (R.isInvalid())
13839  return ExprError();
13840 
13841  R = CheckForImmediateInvocation(R, FnDecl);
13842  if (R.isInvalid())
13843  return ExprError();
13844 
13845  // For a rewritten candidate, we've already reversed the arguments
13846  // if needed. Perform the rest of the rewrite now.
13847  if ((Best->RewriteKind & CRK_DifferentOperator) ||
13848  (Op == OO_Spaceship && IsReversed)) {
13849  if (Op == OO_ExclaimEqual) {
13850  assert(ChosenOp == OO_EqualEqual && "unexpected operator name");
13851  R = CreateBuiltinUnaryOp(OpLoc, UO_LNot, R.get());
13852  } else {
13853  assert(ChosenOp == OO_Spaceship && "unexpected operator name");
13854  llvm::APSInt Zero(Context.getTypeSize(Context.IntTy), false);
13855  Expr *ZeroLiteral =
13856  IntegerLiteral::Create(Context, Zero, Context.IntTy, OpLoc);
13857 
13858  Sema::CodeSynthesisContext Ctx;
13859  Ctx.Kind = Sema::CodeSynthesisContext::RewritingOperatorAsSpaceship;
13860  Ctx.Entity = FnDecl;
13861  pushCodeSynthesisContext(Ctx);
13862 
13863  R = CreateOverloadedBinOp(
13864  OpLoc, Opc, Fns, IsReversed ? ZeroLiteral : R.get(),
13865  IsReversed ? R.get() : ZeroLiteral, PerformADL,
13866  /*AllowRewrittenCandidates=*/false);
13867 
13868  popCodeSynthesisContext();
13869  }
13870  if (R.isInvalid())
13871  return ExprError();
13872  } else {
13873  assert(ChosenOp == Op && "unexpected operator name");
13874  }
13875 
13876  // Make a note in the AST if we did any rewriting.
13877  if (Best->RewriteKind != CRK_None)
13878  R = new (Context) CXXRewrittenBinaryOperator(R.get(), IsReversed);
13879 
13880  return R;
13881  } else {
13882  // We matched a built-in operator. Convert the arguments, then
13883  // break out so that we will build the appropriate built-in
13884  // operator node.
13885  ExprResult ArgsRes0 = PerformImplicitConversion(
13886  Args[0], Best->BuiltinParamTypes[0], Best->Conversions[0],
13887  AA_Passing, CCK_ForBuiltinOverloadedOp);
13888  if (ArgsRes0.isInvalid())
13889  return ExprError();
13890  Args[0] = ArgsRes0.get();
13891 
13892  ExprResult ArgsRes1 = PerformImplicitConversion(
13893  Args[1], Best->BuiltinParamTypes[1], Best->Conversions[1],
13894  AA_Passing, CCK_ForBuiltinOverloadedOp);
13895  if (ArgsRes1.isInvalid())
13896  return ExprError();
13897  Args[1] = ArgsRes1.get();
13898  break;
13899  }
13900  }
13901 
13902  case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
13903  // C++ [over.match.oper]p9:
13904  // If the operator is the operator , [...] and there are no
13905  // viable functions, then the operator is assumed to be the
13906  // built-in operator and interpreted according to clause 5.
13907  if (Opc == BO_Comma)
13908  break;
13909 
13910  // When defaulting an 'operator<=>', we can try to synthesize a three-way
13911  // compare result using '==' and '<'.
13912  if (DefaultedFn && Opc == BO_Cmp) {
13913  ExprResult E = BuildSynthesizedThreeWayComparison(OpLoc, Fns, Args[0],
13914  Args[1], DefaultedFn);
13915  if (E.isInvalid() || E.isUsable())
13916  return E;
13917  }
13918 
13919  // For class as left operand for assignment or compound assignment
13920  // operator do not fall through to handling in built-in, but report that
13921  // no overloaded assignment operator found
13922  ExprResult Result = ExprError();
13923  StringRef OpcStr = BinaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc);
13924  auto Cands = CandidateSet.CompleteCandidates(*this, OCD_AllCandidates,
13925  Args, OpLoc);
13926  DeferDiagsRAII DDR(*this,
13927  CandidateSet.shouldDeferDiags(*this, Args, OpLoc));
13928  if (Args[0]->getType()->isRecordType() &&
13929  Opc >= BO_Assign && Opc <= BO_OrAssign) {
13930  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_ovl_no_viable_oper)
13931  << BinaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc)
13932  << Args[0]->getSourceRange() << Args[1]->getSourceRange();
13933  if (Args[0]->getType()->isIncompleteType()) {
13934  Diag(OpLoc, diag::note_assign_lhs_incomplete)
13935  << Args[0]->getType()
13936  << Args[0]->getSourceRange() << Args[1]->getSourceRange();
13937  }
13938  } else {
13939  // This is an erroneous use of an operator which can be overloaded by
13940  // a non-member function. Check for non-member operators which were
13941  // defined too late to be candidates.
13942  if (DiagnoseTwoPhaseOperatorLookup(*this, Op, OpLoc, Args))
13943  // FIXME: Recover by calling the found function.
13944  return ExprError();
13945 
13946  // No viable function; try to create a built-in operation, which will
13947  // produce an error. Then, show the non-viable candidates.
13948  Result = CreateBuiltinBinOp(OpLoc, Opc, Args[0], Args[1]);
13949  }
13950  assert(Result.isInvalid() &&
13951  "C++ binary operator overloading is missing candidates!");
13952  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(*this, Args, Cands, OpcStr, OpLoc);
13953  return Result;
13954  }
13955 
13956  case OR_Ambiguous:
13957  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
13958  PartialDiagnosticAt(OpLoc, PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_oper_binary)
13959  << BinaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc)
13960  << Args[0]->getType()
13961  << Args[1]->getType()
13962  << Args[0]->getSourceRange()
13963  << Args[1]->getSourceRange()),
13964  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args, BinaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc),
13965  OpLoc);
13966  return ExprError();
13967 
13968  case OR_Deleted:
13969  if (isImplicitlyDeleted(Best->Function)) {
13970  FunctionDecl *DeletedFD = Best->Function;
13971  DefaultedFunctionKind DFK = getDefaultedFunctionKind(DeletedFD);
13972  if (DFK.isSpecialMember()) {
13973  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_ovl_deleted_special_oper)
13974  << Args[0]->getType() << DFK.asSpecialMember();
13975  } else {
13976  assert(DFK.isComparison());
13977  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_ovl_deleted_comparison)
13978  << Args[0]->getType() << DeletedFD;
13979  }
13980 
13981  // The user probably meant to call this special member. Just
13982  // explain why it's deleted.
13983  NoteDeletedFunction(DeletedFD);
13984  return ExprError();
13985  }
13986  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
13987  PartialDiagnosticAt(
13988  OpLoc, PDiag(diag::err_ovl_deleted_oper)
13989  << getOperatorSpelling(Best->Function->getDeclName()
13990  .getCXXOverloadedOperator())
13991  << Args[0]->getSourceRange()
13992  << Args[1]->getSourceRange()),
13993  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Args, BinaryOperator::getOpcodeStr(Opc),
13994  OpLoc);
13995  return ExprError();
13996  }
13997 
13998  // We matched a built-in operator; build it.
13999  return CreateBuiltinBinOp(OpLoc, Opc, Args[0], Args[1]);
14000 }
14001 
14002 ExprResult Sema::BuildSynthesizedThreeWayComparison(
14003  SourceLocation OpLoc, const UnresolvedSetImpl &Fns, Expr *LHS, Expr *RHS,
14004  FunctionDecl *DefaultedFn) {
14005  const ComparisonCategoryInfo *Info =
14006  Context.CompCategories.lookupInfoForType(DefaultedFn->getReturnType());
14007  // If we're not producing a known comparison category type, we can't
14008  // synthesize a three-way comparison. Let the caller diagnose this.
14009  if (!Info)
14010  return ExprResult((Expr*)nullptr);
14011 
14012  // If we ever want to perform this synthesis more generally, we will need to
14013  // apply the temporary materialization conversion to the operands.
14014  assert(LHS->isGLValue() && RHS->isGLValue() &&
14015  "cannot use prvalue expressions more than once");
14016  Expr *OrigLHS = LHS;
14017  Expr *OrigRHS = RHS;
14018 
14019  // Replace the LHS and RHS with OpaqueValueExprs; we're going to refer to
14020  // each of them multiple times below.
14021  LHS = new (Context)
14022  OpaqueValueExpr(LHS->getExprLoc(), LHS->getType(), LHS->getValueKind(),
14023  LHS->getObjectKind(), LHS);
14024  RHS = new (Context)
14025  OpaqueValueExpr(RHS->getExprLoc(), RHS->getType(), RHS->getValueKind(),
14026  RHS->getObjectKind(), RHS);
14027 
14028  ExprResult Eq = CreateOverloadedBinOp(OpLoc, BO_EQ, Fns, LHS, RHS, true, true,
14029  DefaultedFn);
14030  if (Eq.isInvalid())
14031  return ExprError();
14032 
14033  ExprResult Less = CreateOverloadedBinOp(OpLoc, BO_LT, Fns, LHS, RHS, true,
14034  true, DefaultedFn);
14035  if (Less.isInvalid())
14036  return ExprError();
14037 
14038  ExprResult Greater;
14039  if (Info->isPartial()) {
14040  Greater = CreateOverloadedBinOp(OpLoc, BO_LT, Fns, RHS, LHS, true, true,
14041  DefaultedFn);
14042  if (Greater.isInvalid())
14043  return ExprError();
14044  }
14045 
14046  // Form the list of comparisons we're going to perform.
14047  struct Comparison {
14048  ExprResult Cmp;
14049  ComparisonCategoryResult Result;
14050  } Comparisons[4] =
14051  { {Eq, Info->isStrong() ? ComparisonCategoryResult::Equal
14052  : ComparisonCategoryResult::Equivalent},
14053  {Less, ComparisonCategoryResult::Less},
14054  {Greater, ComparisonCategoryResult::Greater},
14055  {ExprResult(), ComparisonCategoryResult::Unordered},
14056  };
14057 
14058  int I = Info->isPartial() ? 3 : 2;
14059 
14060  // Combine the comparisons with suitable conditional expressions.
14061  ExprResult Result;
14062  for (; I >= 0; --I) {
14063  // Build a reference to the comparison category constant.
14064  auto *VI = Info->lookupValueInfo(Comparisons[I].Result);
14065  // FIXME: Missing a constant for a comparison category. Diagnose this?
14066  if (!VI)
14067  return ExprResult((Expr*)nullptr);
14068  ExprResult ThisResult =
14069  BuildDeclarationNameExpr(CXXScopeSpec(), DeclarationNameInfo(), VI->VD);
14070  if (ThisResult.isInvalid())
14071  return ExprError();
14072 
14073  // Build a conditional unless this is the final case.
14074  if (Result.get()) {
14075  Result = ActOnConditionalOp(OpLoc, OpLoc, Comparisons[I].Cmp.get(),
14076  ThisResult.get(), Result.get());
14077  if (Result.isInvalid())
14078  return ExprError();
14079  } else {
14080  Result = ThisResult;
14081  }
14082  }
14083 
14084  // Build a PseudoObjectExpr to model the rewriting of an <=> operator, and to
14085  // bind the OpaqueValueExprs before they're (repeatedly) used.
14086  Expr *SyntacticForm = BinaryOperator::Create(
14087  Context, OrigLHS, OrigRHS, BO_Cmp, Result.get()->getType(),
14088  Result.get()->getValueKind(), Result.get()->getObjectKind(), OpLoc,
14089  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
14090  Expr *SemanticForm[] = {LHS, RHS, Result.get()};
14091  return PseudoObjectExpr::Create(Context, SyntacticForm, SemanticForm, 2);
14092 }
14093 
14094 static bool PrepareArgumentsForCallToObjectOfClassType(
14095  Sema &S, SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &MethodArgs, CXXMethodDecl *Method,
14096  MultiExprArg Args, SourceLocation LParenLoc) {
14097 
14098  const auto *Proto = Method->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
14099  unsigned NumParams = Proto->getNumParams();
14100  unsigned NumArgsSlots =
14101  MethodArgs.size() + std::max<unsigned>(Args.size(), NumParams);
14102  // Build the full argument list for the method call (the implicit object
14103  // parameter is placed at the beginning of the list).
14104  MethodArgs.reserve(MethodArgs.size() + NumArgsSlots);
14105  bool IsError = false;
14106  // Initialize the implicit object parameter.
14107  // Check the argument types.
14108  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumParams; i++) {
14109  Expr *Arg;
14110  if (i < Args.size()) {
14111  Arg = Args[i];
14112  ExprResult InputInit =
14113  S.PerformCopyInitialization(InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(
14114  S.Context, Method->getParamDecl(i)),
14115  SourceLocation(), Arg);
14116  IsError |= InputInit.isInvalid();
14117  Arg = InputInit.getAs<Expr>();
14118  } else {
14119  ExprResult DefArg =
14120  S.BuildCXXDefaultArgExpr(LParenLoc, Method, Method->getParamDecl(i));
14121  if (DefArg.isInvalid()) {
14122  IsError = true;
14123  break;
14124  }
14125  Arg = DefArg.getAs<Expr>();
14126  }
14127 
14128  MethodArgs.push_back(Arg);
14129  }
14130  return IsError;
14131 }
14132 
14133 ExprResult Sema::CreateOverloadedArraySubscriptExpr(SourceLocation LLoc,
14134  SourceLocation RLoc,
14135  Expr *Base,
14136  MultiExprArg ArgExpr) {
14137  SmallVector<Expr *, 2> Args;
14138  Args.push_back(Base);
14139  for (auto e : ArgExpr) {
14140  Args.push_back(e);
14141  }
14142  DeclarationName OpName =
14143  Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(OO_Subscript);
14144 
14145  SourceRange Range = ArgExpr.empty()
14146  ? SourceRange{}
14147  : SourceRange(ArgExpr.front()->getBeginLoc(),
14148  ArgExpr.back()->getEndLoc());
14149 
14150  // If either side is type-dependent, create an appropriate dependent
14151  // expression.
14152  if (Expr::hasAnyTypeDependentArguments(Args)) {
14153 
14154  CXXRecordDecl *NamingClass = nullptr; // lookup ignores member operators
14155  // CHECKME: no 'operator' keyword?
14156  DeclarationNameInfo OpNameInfo(OpName, LLoc);
14157  OpNameInfo.setCXXOperatorNameRange(SourceRange(LLoc, RLoc));
14158  ExprResult Fn = CreateUnresolvedLookupExpr(
14159  NamingClass, NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), OpNameInfo, UnresolvedSet<0>());
14160  if (Fn.isInvalid())
14161  return ExprError();
14162  // Can't add any actual overloads yet
14163 
14164  return CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(Context, OO_Subscript, Fn.get(), Args,
14165  Context.DependentTy, VK_PRValue, RLoc,
14166  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
14167  }
14168 
14169  // Handle placeholders
14170  UnbridgedCastsSet UnbridgedCasts;
14171  if (checkArgPlaceholdersForOverload(*this, Args, UnbridgedCasts)) {
14172  return ExprError();
14173  }
14174  // Build an empty overload set.
14175  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(LLoc, OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator);
14176 
14177  // Subscript can only be overloaded as a member function.
14178 
14179  // Add operator candidates that are member functions.
14180  AddMemberOperatorCandidates(OO_Subscript, LLoc, Args, CandidateSet);
14181 
14182  // Add builtin operator candidates.
14183  if (Args.size() == 2)
14184  AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates(OO_Subscript, LLoc, Args, CandidateSet);
14185 
14186  bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
14187 
14188  // Perform overload resolution.
14189  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
14190  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, LLoc, Best)) {
14191  case OR_Success: {
14192  // We found a built-in operator or an overloaded operator.
14193  FunctionDecl *FnDecl = Best->Function;
14194 
14195  if (FnDecl) {
14196  // We matched an overloaded operator. Build a call to that
14197  // operator.
14198 
14199  CheckMemberOperatorAccess(LLoc, Args[0], ArgExpr, Best->FoundDecl);
14200 
14201  // Convert the arguments.
14202  CXXMethodDecl *Method = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FnDecl);
14203  SmallVector<Expr *, 2> MethodArgs;
14204  ExprResult Arg0 = PerformObjectArgumentInitialization(
14205  Args[0], /*Qualifier=*/nullptr, Best->FoundDecl, Method);
14206  if (Arg0.isInvalid())
14207  return ExprError();
14208 
14209  MethodArgs.push_back(Arg0.get());
14210  bool IsError = PrepareArgumentsForCallToObjectOfClassType(
14211  *this, MethodArgs, Method, ArgExpr, LLoc);
14212  if (IsError)
14213  return ExprError();
14214 
14215  // Build the actual expression node.
14216  DeclarationNameInfo OpLocInfo(OpName, LLoc);
14217  OpLocInfo.setCXXOperatorNameRange(SourceRange(LLoc, RLoc));
14218  ExprResult FnExpr = CreateFunctionRefExpr(
14219  *this, FnDecl, Best->FoundDecl, Base, HadMultipleCandidates,
14220  OpLocInfo.getLoc(), OpLocInfo.getInfo());
14221  if (FnExpr.isInvalid())
14222  return ExprError();
14223 
14224  // Determine the result type
14225  QualType ResultTy = FnDecl->getReturnType();
14226  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultTy);
14227  ResultTy = ResultTy.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
14228 
14229  CXXOperatorCallExpr *TheCall = CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(
14230  Context, OO_Subscript, FnExpr.get(), MethodArgs, ResultTy, VK, RLoc,
14231  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
14232  if (CheckCallReturnType(FnDecl->getReturnType(), LLoc, TheCall, FnDecl))
14233  return ExprError();
14234 
14235  if (CheckFunctionCall(Method, TheCall,
14236  Method->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()))
14237  return ExprError();
14238 
14239  return CheckForImmediateInvocation(MaybeBindToTemporary(TheCall),
14240  FnDecl);
14241  } else {
14242  // We matched a built-in operator. Convert the arguments, then
14243  // break out so that we will build the appropriate built-in
14244  // operator node.
14245  ExprResult ArgsRes0 = PerformImplicitConversion(
14246  Args[0], Best->BuiltinParamTypes[0], Best->Conversions[0],
14247  AA_Passing, CCK_ForBuiltinOverloadedOp);
14248  if (ArgsRes0.isInvalid())
14249  return ExprError();
14250  Args[0] = ArgsRes0.get();
14251 
14252  ExprResult ArgsRes1 = PerformImplicitConversion(
14253  Args[1], Best->BuiltinParamTypes[1], Best->Conversions[1],
14254  AA_Passing, CCK_ForBuiltinOverloadedOp);
14255  if (ArgsRes1.isInvalid())
14256  return ExprError();
14257  Args[1] = ArgsRes1.get();
14258 
14259  break;
14260  }
14261  }
14262 
14263  case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
14264  PartialDiagnostic PD =
14265  CandidateSet.empty()
14266  ? (PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_oper)
14267  << Args[0]->getType() << /*subscript*/ 0
14268  << Args[0]->getSourceRange() << Range)
14269  : (PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_viable_subscript)
14270  << Args[0]->getType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange() << Range);
14271  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(PartialDiagnosticAt(LLoc, PD), *this,
14272  OCD_AllCandidates, ArgExpr, "[]", LLoc);
14273  return ExprError();
14274  }
14275 
14276  case OR_Ambiguous:
14277  if (Args.size() == 2) {
14278  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14279  PartialDiagnosticAt(
14280  LLoc, PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_oper_binary)
14281  << "[]" << Args[0]->getType() << Args[1]->getType()
14282  << Args[0]->getSourceRange() << Range),
14283  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args, "[]", LLoc);
14284  } else {
14285  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14286  PartialDiagnosticAt(LLoc,
14287  PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_subscript_call)
14288  << Args[0]->getType()
14289  << Args[0]->getSourceRange() << Range),
14290  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args, "[]", LLoc);
14291  }
14292  return ExprError();
14293 
14294  case OR_Deleted:
14295  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14296  PartialDiagnosticAt(LLoc, PDiag(diag::err_ovl_deleted_oper)
14297  << "[]" << Args[0]->getSourceRange()
14298  << Range),
14299  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Args, "[]", LLoc);
14300  return ExprError();
14301  }
14302 
14303  // We matched a built-in operator; build it.
14304  return CreateBuiltinArraySubscriptExpr(Args[0], LLoc, Args[1], RLoc);
14305 }
14306 
14307 /// BuildCallToMemberFunction - Build a call to a member
14308 /// function. MemExpr is the expression that refers to the member
14309 /// function (and includes the object parameter), Args/NumArgs are the
14310 /// arguments to the function call (not including the object
14311 /// parameter). The caller needs to validate that the member
14312 /// expression refers to a non-static member function or an overloaded
14313 /// member function.
14314 ExprResult Sema::BuildCallToMemberFunction(Scope *S, Expr *MemExprE,
14315  SourceLocation LParenLoc,
14316  MultiExprArg Args,
14317  SourceLocation RParenLoc,
14318  Expr *ExecConfig, bool IsExecConfig,
14319  bool AllowRecovery) {
14320  assert(MemExprE->getType() == Context.BoundMemberTy ||
14321  MemExprE->getType() == Context.OverloadTy);
14322 
14323  // Dig out the member expression. This holds both the object
14324  // argument and the member function we're referring to.
14325  Expr *NakedMemExpr = MemExprE->IgnoreParens();
14326 
14327  // Determine whether this is a call to a pointer-to-member function.
14328  if (BinaryOperator *op = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(NakedMemExpr)) {
14329  assert(op->getType() == Context.BoundMemberTy);
14330  assert(op->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemD || op->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI);
14331 
14332  QualType fnType =
14333  op->getRHS()->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>()->getPointeeType();
14334 
14335  const FunctionProtoType *proto = fnType->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
14336  QualType resultType = proto->getCallResultType(Context);
14337  ExprValueKind valueKind = Expr::getValueKindForType(proto->getReturnType());
14338 
14339  // Check that the object type isn't more qualified than the
14340  // member function we're calling.
14341  Qualifiers funcQuals = proto->getMethodQuals();
14342 
14343  QualType objectType = op->getLHS()->getType();
14344  if (op->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI)
14345  objectType = objectType->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
14346  Qualifiers objectQuals = objectType.getQualifiers();
14347 
14348  Qualifiers difference = objectQuals - funcQuals;
14349  difference.removeObjCGCAttr();
14350  difference.removeAddressSpace();
14351  if (difference) {
14352  std::string qualsString = difference.getAsString();
14353  Diag(LParenLoc, diag::err_pointer_to_member_call_drops_quals)
14354  << fnType.getUnqualifiedType()
14355  << qualsString
14356  << (qualsString.find(' ') == std::string::npos ? 1 : 2);
14357  }
14358 
14359  CXXMemberCallExpr *call = CXXMemberCallExpr::Create(
14360  Context, MemExprE, Args, resultType, valueKind, RParenLoc,
14361  CurFPFeatureOverrides(), proto->getNumParams());
14362 
14363  if (CheckCallReturnType(proto->getReturnType(), op->getRHS()->getBeginLoc(),
14364  call, nullptr))
14365  return ExprError();
14366 
14367  if (ConvertArgumentsForCall(call, op, nullptr, proto, Args, RParenLoc))
14368  return ExprError();
14369 
14370  if (CheckOtherCall(call, proto))
14371  return ExprError();
14372 
14373  return MaybeBindToTemporary(call);
14374  }
14375 
14376  // We only try to build a recovery expr at this level if we can preserve
14377  // the return type, otherwise we return ExprError() and let the caller
14378  // recover.
14379  auto BuildRecoveryExpr = [&](QualType Type) {
14380  if (!AllowRecovery)
14381  return ExprError();
14382  std::vector<Expr *> SubExprs = {MemExprE};
14383  llvm::append_range(SubExprs, Args);
14384  return CreateRecoveryExpr(MemExprE->getBeginLoc(), RParenLoc, SubExprs,
14385  Type);
14386  };
14387  if (isa<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(NakedMemExpr))
14388  return CallExpr::Create(Context, MemExprE, Args, Context.VoidTy, VK_PRValue,
14389  RParenLoc, CurFPFeatureOverrides());
14390 
14391  UnbridgedCastsSet UnbridgedCasts;
14392  if (checkArgPlaceholdersForOverload(*this, Args, UnbridgedCasts))
14393  return ExprError();
14394 
14395  MemberExpr *MemExpr;
14396  CXXMethodDecl *Method = nullptr;
14397  DeclAccessPair FoundDecl = DeclAccessPair::make(nullptr, AS_public);
14398  NestedNameSpecifier *Qualifier = nullptr;
14399  if (isa<MemberExpr>(NakedMemExpr)) {
14400  MemExpr = cast<MemberExpr>(NakedMemExpr);
14401  Method = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(MemExpr->getMemberDecl());
14402  FoundDecl = MemExpr->getFoundDecl();
14403  Qualifier = MemExpr->getQualifier();
14404  UnbridgedCasts.restore();
14405  } else {
14406  UnresolvedMemberExpr *UnresExpr = cast<UnresolvedMemberExpr>(NakedMemExpr);
14407  Qualifier = UnresExpr->getQualifier();
14408 
14409  QualType ObjectType = UnresExpr->getBaseType();
14410  Expr::Classification ObjectClassification
14411  = UnresExpr->isArrow()? Expr::Classification::makeSimpleLValue()
14412  : UnresExpr->getBase()->Classify(Context);
14413 
14414  // Add overload candidates
14415  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(UnresExpr->getMemberLoc(),
14416  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
14417 
14418  // FIXME: avoid copy.
14419  TemplateArgumentListInfo TemplateArgsBuffer, *TemplateArgs = nullptr;
14420  if (UnresExpr->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
14421  UnresExpr->copyTemplateArgumentsInto(TemplateArgsBuffer);
14422  TemplateArgs = &TemplateArgsBuffer;
14423  }
14424 
14425  for (UnresolvedMemberExpr::decls_iterator I = UnresExpr->decls_begin(),
14426  E = UnresExpr->decls_end(); I != E; ++I) {
14427 
14428  NamedDecl *Func = *I;
14429  CXXRecordDecl *ActingDC = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Func->getDeclContext());
14430  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(Func))
14431  Func = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(Func)->getTargetDecl();
14432 
14433 
14434  // Microsoft supports direct constructor calls.
14435  if (getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt && isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Func)) {
14436  AddOverloadCandidate(cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Func), I.getPair(), Args,
14437  CandidateSet,
14438  /*SuppressUserConversions*/ false);
14439  } else if ((Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Func))) {
14440  // If explicit template arguments were provided, we can't call a
14441  // non-template member function.
14442  if (TemplateArgs)
14443  continue;
14444 
14445  AddMethodCandidate(Method, I.getPair(), ActingDC, ObjectType,
14446  ObjectClassification, Args, CandidateSet,
14447  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false);
14448  } else {
14449  AddMethodTemplateCandidate(
14450  cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Func), I.getPair(), ActingDC,
14451  TemplateArgs, ObjectType, ObjectClassification, Args, CandidateSet,
14452  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false);
14453  }
14454  }
14455 
14456  DeclarationName DeclName = UnresExpr->getMemberName();
14457 
14458  UnbridgedCasts.restore();
14459 
14460  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
14461  bool Succeeded = false;
14462  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, UnresExpr->getBeginLoc(),
14463  Best)) {
14464  case OR_Success:
14465  Method = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Best->Function);
14466  FoundDecl = Best->FoundDecl;
14467  CheckUnresolvedMemberAccess(UnresExpr, Best->FoundDecl);
14468  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Best->FoundDecl, UnresExpr->getNameLoc()))
14469  break;
14470  // If FoundDecl is different from Method (such as if one is a template
14471  // and the other a specialization), make sure DiagnoseUseOfDecl is
14472  // called on both.
14473  // FIXME: This would be more comprehensively addressed by modifying
14474  // DiagnoseUseOfDecl to accept both the FoundDecl and the decl
14475  // being used.
14476  if (Method != FoundDecl.getDecl() &&
14477  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Method, UnresExpr->getNameLoc()))
14478  break;
14479  Succeeded = true;
14480  break;
14481 
14482  case OR_No_Viable_Function:
14483  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14484  PartialDiagnosticAt(
14485  UnresExpr->getMemberLoc(),
14486  PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_viable_member_function_in_call)
14487  << DeclName << MemExprE->getSourceRange()),
14488  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
14489  break;
14490  case OR_Ambiguous:
14491  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14492  PartialDiagnosticAt(UnresExpr->getMemberLoc(),
14493  PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_member_call)
14494  << DeclName << MemExprE->getSourceRange()),
14495  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args);
14496  break;
14497  case OR_Deleted:
14498  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14499  PartialDiagnosticAt(UnresExpr->getMemberLoc(),
14500  PDiag(diag::err_ovl_deleted_member_call)
14501  << DeclName << MemExprE->getSourceRange()),
14502  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
14503  break;
14504  }
14505  // Overload resolution fails, try to recover.
14506  if (!Succeeded)
14507  return BuildRecoveryExpr(chooseRecoveryType(CandidateSet, &Best));
14508 
14509  MemExprE = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(MemExprE, FoundDecl, Method);
14510 
14511  // If overload resolution picked a static member, build a
14512  // non-member call based on that function.
14513  if (Method->isStatic()) {
14514  return BuildResolvedCallExpr(MemExprE, Method, LParenLoc, Args, RParenLoc,
14515  ExecConfig, IsExecConfig);
14516  }
14517 
14518  MemExpr = cast<MemberExpr>(MemExprE->IgnoreParens());
14519  }
14520 
14521  QualType ResultType = Method->getReturnType();
14522  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultType);
14523  ResultType = ResultType.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
14524 
14525  assert(Method && "Member call to something that isn't a method?");
14526  const auto *Proto = Method->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
14527  CXXMemberCallExpr *TheCall = CXXMemberCallExpr::Create(
14528  Context, MemExprE, Args, ResultType, VK, RParenLoc,
14529  CurFPFeatureOverrides(), Proto->getNumParams());
14530 
14531  // Check for a valid return type.
14532  if (CheckCallReturnType(Method->getReturnType(), MemExpr->getMemberLoc(),
14533  TheCall, Method))
14534  return BuildRecoveryExpr(ResultType);
14535 
14536  // Convert the object argument (for a non-static member function call).
14537  // We only need to do this if there was actually an overload; otherwise
14538  // it was done at lookup.
14539  if (!Method->isStatic()) {
14540  ExprResult ObjectArg =
14541  PerformObjectArgumentInitialization(MemExpr->getBase(), Qualifier,
14542  FoundDecl, Method);
14543  if (ObjectArg.isInvalid())
14544  return ExprError();
14545  MemExpr->setBase(ObjectArg.get());
14546  }
14547 
14548  // Convert the rest of the arguments
14549  if (ConvertArgumentsForCall(TheCall, MemExpr, Method, Proto, Args,
14550  RParenLoc))
14551  return BuildRecoveryExpr(ResultType);
14552 
14553  DiagnoseSentinelCalls(Method, LParenLoc, Args);
14554 
14555  if (CheckFunctionCall(Method, TheCall, Proto))
14556  return ExprError();
14557 
14558  // In the case the method to call was not selected by the overloading
14559  // resolution process, we still need to handle the enable_if attribute. Do
14560  // that here, so it will not hide previous -- and more relevant -- errors.
14561  if (auto *MemE = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(NakedMemExpr)) {
14562  if (const EnableIfAttr *Attr =
14563  CheckEnableIf(Method, LParenLoc, Args, true)) {
14564  Diag(MemE->getMemberLoc(),
14565  diag::err_ovl_no_viable_member_function_in_call)
14566  << Method << Method->getSourceRange();
14567  Diag(Method->getLocation(),
14568  diag::note_ovl_candidate_disabled_by_function_cond_attr)
14569  << Attr->getCond()->getSourceRange() << Attr->getMessage();
14570  return ExprError();
14571  }
14572  }
14573 
14574  if ((isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(CurContext) ||
14575  isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(CurContext)) &&
14576  TheCall->getMethodDecl()->isPure()) {
14577  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = TheCall->getMethodDecl();
14578 
14579  if (isa<CXXThisExpr>(MemExpr->getBase()->IgnoreParenCasts()) &&
14580  MemExpr->performsVirtualDispatch(getLangOpts())) {
14581  Diag(MemExpr->getBeginLoc(),
14582  diag::warn_call_to_pure_virtual_member_function_from_ctor_dtor)
14583  << MD->getDeclName() << isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(CurContext)
14584  << MD->getParent();
14585 
14586  Diag(MD->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_previous_decl) << MD->getDeclName();
14587  if (getLangOpts().AppleKext)
14588  Diag(MemExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_pure_qualified_call_kext)
14589  << MD->getParent() << MD->getDeclName();
14590  }
14591  }
14592 
14593  if (CXXDestructorDecl *DD =
14594  dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(TheCall->getMethodDecl())) {
14595  // a->A::f() doesn't go through the vtable, except in AppleKext mode.
14596  bool CallCanBeVirtual = !MemExpr->hasQualifier() || getLangOpts().AppleKext;
14597  CheckVirtualDtorCall(DD, MemExpr->getBeginLoc(), /*IsDelete=*/false,
14598  CallCanBeVirtual, /*WarnOnNonAbstractTypes=*/true,
14599  MemExpr->getMemberLoc());
14600  }
14601 
14602  return CheckForImmediateInvocation(MaybeBindToTemporary(TheCall),
14603  TheCall->getMethodDecl());
14604 }
14605 
14606 /// BuildCallToObjectOfClassType - Build a call to an object of class
14607 /// type (C++ [over.call.object]), which can end up invoking an
14608 /// overloaded function call operator (@c operator()) or performing a
14609 /// user-defined conversion on the object argument.
14610 ExprResult
14611 Sema::BuildCallToObjectOfClassType(Scope *S, Expr *Obj,
14612  SourceLocation LParenLoc,
14613  MultiExprArg Args,
14614  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
14615  if (checkPlaceholderForOverload(*this, Obj))
14616  return ExprError();
14617  ExprResult Object = Obj;
14618 
14619  UnbridgedCastsSet UnbridgedCasts;
14620  if (checkArgPlaceholdersForOverload(*this, Args, UnbridgedCasts))
14621  return ExprError();
14622 
14623  assert(Object.get()->getType()->isRecordType() &&
14624  "Requires object type argument");
14625 
14626  // C++ [over.call.object]p1:
14627  // If the primary-expression E in the function call syntax
14628  // evaluates to a class object of type "cv T", then the set of
14629  // candidate functions includes at least the function call
14630  // operators of T. The function call operators of T are obtained by
14631  // ordinary lookup of the name operator() in the context of
14632  // (E).operator().
14633  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(LParenLoc,
14634  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator);
14635  DeclarationName OpName = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(OO_Call);
14636 
14637  if (RequireCompleteType(LParenLoc, Object.get()->getType(),
14638  diag::err_incomplete_object_call, Object.get()))
14639  return true;
14640 
14641  const auto *Record = Object.get()->getType()->castAs<RecordType>();
14642  LookupResult R(*this, OpName, LParenLoc, LookupOrdinaryName);
14643  LookupQualifiedName(R, Record->getDecl());
14644  R.suppressDiagnostics();
14645 
14646  for (LookupResult::iterator Oper = R.begin(), OperEnd = R.end();
14647  Oper != OperEnd; ++Oper) {
14648  AddMethodCandidate(Oper.getPair(), Object.get()->getType(),
14649  Object.get()->Classify(Context), Args, CandidateSet,
14650  /*SuppressUserConversion=*/false);
14651  }
14652 
14653  // C++ [over.call.object]p2:
14654  // In addition, for each (non-explicit in C++0x) conversion function
14655  // declared in T of the form
14656  //
14657  // operator conversion-type-id () cv-qualifier;
14658  //
14659  // where cv-qualifier is the same cv-qualification as, or a
14660  // greater cv-qualification than, cv, and where conversion-type-id
14661  // denotes the type "pointer to function of (P1,...,Pn) returning
14662  // R", or the type "reference to pointer to function of
14663  // (P1,...,Pn) returning R", or the type "reference to function
14664  // of (P1,...,Pn) returning R", a surrogate call function [...]
14665  // is also considered as a candidate function. Similarly,
14666  // surrogate call functions are added to the set of candidate
14667  // functions for each conversion function declared in an
14668  // accessible base class provided the function is not hidden
14669  // within T by another intervening declaration.
14670  const auto &Conversions =
14671  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Record->getDecl())->getVisibleConversionFunctions();
14672  for (auto I = Conversions.begin(), E = Conversions.end(); I != E; ++I) {
14673  NamedDecl *D = *I;
14674  CXXRecordDecl *ActingContext = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getDeclContext());
14675  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D))
14676  D = cast<UsingShadowDecl>(D)->getTargetDecl();
14677 
14678  // Skip over templated conversion functions; they aren't
14679  // surrogates.
14680  if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D))
14681  continue;
14682 
14683  CXXConversionDecl *Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D);
14684  if (!Conv->isExplicit()) {
14685  // Strip the reference type (if any) and then the pointer type (if
14686  // any) to get down to what might be a function type.
14687  QualType ConvType = Conv->getConversionType().getNonReferenceType();
14688  if (const PointerType *ConvPtrType = ConvType->getAs<PointerType>())
14689  ConvType = ConvPtrType->getPointeeType();
14690 
14691  if (const FunctionProtoType *Proto = ConvType->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
14692  {
14693  AddSurrogateCandidate(Conv, I.getPair(), ActingContext, Proto,
14694  Object.get(), Args, CandidateSet);
14695  }
14696  }
14697  }
14698 
14699  bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
14700 
14701  // Perform overload resolution.
14702  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
14703  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, Object.get()->getBeginLoc(),
14704  Best)) {
14705  case OR_Success:
14706  // Overload resolution succeeded; we'll build the appropriate call
14707  // below.
14708  break;
14709 
14710  case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
14711  PartialDiagnostic PD =
14712  CandidateSet.empty()
14713  ? (PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_oper)
14714  << Object.get()->getType() << /*call*/ 1
14715  << Object.get()->getSourceRange())
14716  : (PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_viable_object_call)
14717  << Object.get()->getType() << Object.get()->getSourceRange());
14718  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14719  PartialDiagnosticAt(Object.get()->getBeginLoc(), PD), *this,
14720  OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
14721  break;
14722  }
14723  case OR_Ambiguous:
14724  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14725  PartialDiagnosticAt(Object.get()->getBeginLoc(),
14726  PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_object_call)
14727  << Object.get()->getType()
14728  << Object.get()->getSourceRange()),
14729  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args);
14730  break;
14731 
14732  case OR_Deleted:
14733  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14734  PartialDiagnosticAt(Object.get()->getBeginLoc(),
14735  PDiag(diag::err_ovl_deleted_object_call)
14736  << Object.get()->getType()
14737  << Object.get()->getSourceRange()),
14738  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
14739  break;
14740  }
14741 
14742  if (Best == CandidateSet.end())
14743  return true;
14744 
14745  UnbridgedCasts.restore();
14746 
14747  if (Best->Function == nullptr) {
14748  // Since there is no function declaration, this is one of the
14749  // surrogate candidates. Dig out the conversion function.
14750  CXXConversionDecl *Conv
14751  = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(
14752  Best->Conversions[0].UserDefined.ConversionFunction);
14753 
14754  CheckMemberOperatorAccess(LParenLoc, Object.get(), nullptr,
14755  Best->FoundDecl);
14756  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Best->FoundDecl, LParenLoc))
14757  return ExprError();
14758  assert(Conv == Best->FoundDecl.getDecl() &&
14759  "Found Decl & conversion-to-functionptr should be same, right?!");
14760  // We selected one of the surrogate functions that converts the
14761  // object parameter to a function pointer. Perform the conversion
14762  // on the object argument, then let BuildCallExpr finish the job.
14763 
14764  // Create an implicit member expr to refer to the conversion operator.
14765  // and then call it.
14766  ExprResult Call = BuildCXXMemberCallExpr(Object.get(), Best->FoundDecl,
14767  Conv, HadMultipleCandidates);
14768  if (Call.isInvalid())
14769  return ExprError();
14770  // Record usage of conversion in an implicit cast.
14771  Call = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(
14772  Context, Call.get()->getType(), CK_UserDefinedConversion, Call.get(),
14773  nullptr, VK_PRValue, CurFPFeatureOverrides());
14774 
14775  return BuildCallExpr(S, Call.get(), LParenLoc, Args, RParenLoc);
14776  }
14777 
14778  CheckMemberOperatorAccess(LParenLoc, Object.get(), nullptr, Best->FoundDecl);
14779 
14780  // We found an overloaded operator(). Build a CXXOperatorCallExpr
14781  // that calls this method, using Object for the implicit object
14782  // parameter and passing along the remaining arguments.
14783  CXXMethodDecl *Method = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Best->Function);
14784 
14785  // An error diagnostic has already been printed when parsing the declaration.
14786  if (Method->isInvalidDecl())
14787  return ExprError();
14788 
14789  const auto *Proto = Method->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
14790  unsigned NumParams = Proto->getNumParams();
14791 
14792  DeclarationNameInfo OpLocInfo(
14793  Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(OO_Call), LParenLoc);
14794  OpLocInfo.setCXXOperatorNameRange(SourceRange(LParenLoc, RParenLoc));
14795  ExprResult NewFn = CreateFunctionRefExpr(*this, Method, Best->FoundDecl,
14796  Obj, HadMultipleCandidates,
14797  OpLocInfo.getLoc(),
14798  OpLocInfo.getInfo());
14799  if (NewFn.isInvalid())
14800  return true;
14801 
14802  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> MethodArgs;
14803  MethodArgs.reserve(NumParams + 1);
14804 
14805  bool IsError = false;
14806 
14807  // Initialize the implicit object parameter.
14808  ExprResult ObjRes =
14809  PerformObjectArgumentInitialization(Object.get(), /*Qualifier=*/nullptr,
14810  Best->FoundDecl, Method);
14811  if (ObjRes.isInvalid())
14812  IsError = true;
14813  else
14814  Object = ObjRes;
14815  MethodArgs.push_back(Object.get());
14816 
14817  IsError |= PrepareArgumentsForCallToObjectOfClassType(
14818  *this, MethodArgs, Method, Args, LParenLoc);
14819 
14820  // If this is a variadic call, handle args passed through "...".
14821  if (Proto->isVariadic()) {
14822  // Promote the arguments (C99 6.5.2.2p7).
14823  for (unsigned i = NumParams, e = Args.size(); i < e; i++) {
14824  ExprResult Arg = DefaultVariadicArgumentPromotion(Args[i], VariadicMethod,
14825  nullptr);
14826  IsError |= Arg.isInvalid();
14827  MethodArgs.push_back(Arg.get());
14828  }
14829  }
14830 
14831  if (IsError)
14832  return true;
14833 
14834  DiagnoseSentinelCalls(Method, LParenLoc, Args);
14835 
14836  // Once we've built TheCall, all of the expressions are properly owned.
14837  QualType ResultTy = Method->getReturnType();
14838  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultTy);
14839  ResultTy = ResultTy.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
14840 
14841  CXXOperatorCallExpr *TheCall = CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(
14842  Context, OO_Call, NewFn.get(), MethodArgs, ResultTy, VK, RParenLoc,
14843  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
14844 
14845  if (CheckCallReturnType(Method->getReturnType(), LParenLoc, TheCall, Method))
14846  return true;
14847 
14848  if (CheckFunctionCall(Method, TheCall, Proto))
14849  return true;
14850 
14851  return CheckForImmediateInvocation(MaybeBindToTemporary(TheCall), Method);
14852 }
14853 
14854 /// BuildOverloadedArrowExpr - Build a call to an overloaded @c operator->
14855 /// (if one exists), where @c Base is an expression of class type and
14856 /// @c Member is the name of the member we're trying to find.
14857 ExprResult
14858 Sema::BuildOverloadedArrowExpr(Scope *S, Expr *Base, SourceLocation OpLoc,
14859  bool *NoArrowOperatorFound) {
14860  assert(Base->getType()->isRecordType() &&
14861  "left-hand side must have class type");
14862 
14863  if (checkPlaceholderForOverload(*this, Base))
14864  return ExprError();
14865 
14866  SourceLocation Loc = Base->getExprLoc();
14867 
14868  // C++ [over.ref]p1:
14869  //
14870  // [...] An expression x->m is interpreted as (x.operator->())->m
14871  // for a class object x of type T if T::operator->() exists and if
14872  // the operator is selected as the best match function by the
14873  // overload resolution mechanism (13.3).
14874  DeclarationName OpName =
14875  Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(OO_Arrow);
14876  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(Loc, OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator);
14877 
14878  if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, Base->getType(),
14879  diag::err_typecheck_incomplete_tag, Base))
14880  return ExprError();
14881 
14882  LookupResult R(*this, OpName, OpLoc, LookupOrdinaryName);
14883  LookupQualifiedName(R, Base->getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
14884  R.suppressDiagnostics();
14885 
14886  for (LookupResult::iterator Oper = R.begin(), OperEnd = R.end();
14887  Oper != OperEnd; ++Oper) {
14888  AddMethodCandidate(Oper.getPair(), Base->getType(), Base->Classify(Context),
14889  None, CandidateSet, /*SuppressUserConversion=*/false);
14890  }
14891 
14892  bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
14893 
14894  // Perform overload resolution.
14895  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
14896  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, OpLoc, Best)) {
14897  case OR_Success:
14898  // Overload resolution succeeded; we'll build the call below.
14899  break;
14900 
14901  case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
14902  auto Cands = CandidateSet.CompleteCandidates(*this, OCD_AllCandidates, Base);
14903  if (CandidateSet.empty()) {
14904  QualType BaseType = Base->getType();
14905  if (NoArrowOperatorFound) {
14906  // Report this specific error to the caller instead of emitting a
14907  // diagnostic, as requested.
14908  *NoArrowOperatorFound = true;
14909  return ExprError();
14910  }
14911  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_arrow)
14912  << BaseType << Base->getSourceRange();
14913  if (BaseType->isRecordType() && !BaseType->isPointerType()) {
14914  Diag(OpLoc, diag::note_typecheck_member_reference_suggestion)
14915  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(OpLoc, ".");
14916  }
14917  } else
14918  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_ovl_no_viable_oper)
14919  << "operator->" << Base->getSourceRange();
14920  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(*this, Base, Cands);
14921  return ExprError();
14922  }
14923  case OR_Ambiguous:
14924  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14925  PartialDiagnosticAt(OpLoc, PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_oper_unary)
14926  << "->" << Base->getType()
14927  << Base->getSourceRange()),
14928  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Base);
14929  return ExprError();
14930 
14931  case OR_Deleted:
14932  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14933  PartialDiagnosticAt(OpLoc, PDiag(diag::err_ovl_deleted_oper)
14934  << "->" << Base->getSourceRange()),
14935  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Base);
14936  return ExprError();
14937  }
14938 
14939  CheckMemberOperatorAccess(OpLoc, Base, nullptr, Best->FoundDecl);
14940 
14941  // Convert the object parameter.
14942  CXXMethodDecl *Method = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Best->Function);
14943  ExprResult BaseResult =
14944  PerformObjectArgumentInitialization(Base, /*Qualifier=*/nullptr,
14945  Best->FoundDecl, Method);
14946  if (BaseResult.isInvalid())
14947  return ExprError();
14948  Base = BaseResult.get();
14949 
14950  // Build the operator call.
14951  ExprResult FnExpr = CreateFunctionRefExpr(*this, Method, Best->FoundDecl,
14952  Base, HadMultipleCandidates, OpLoc);
14953  if (FnExpr.isInvalid())
14954  return ExprError();
14955 
14956  QualType ResultTy = Method->getReturnType();
14957  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultTy);
14958  ResultTy = ResultTy.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
14959  CXXOperatorCallExpr *TheCall =
14960  CXXOperatorCallExpr::Create(Context, OO_Arrow, FnExpr.get(), Base,
14961  ResultTy, VK, OpLoc, CurFPFeatureOverrides());
14962 
14963  if (CheckCallReturnType(Method->getReturnType(), OpLoc, TheCall, Method))
14964  return ExprError();
14965 
14966  if (CheckFunctionCall(Method, TheCall,
14967  Method->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()))
14968  return ExprError();
14969 
14970  return CheckForImmediateInvocation(MaybeBindToTemporary(TheCall), Method);
14971 }
14972 
14973 /// BuildLiteralOperatorCall - Build a UserDefinedLiteral by creating a call to
14974 /// a literal operator described by the provided lookup results.
14975 ExprResult Sema::BuildLiteralOperatorCall(LookupResult &R,
14976  DeclarationNameInfo &SuffixInfo,
14977  ArrayRef<Expr*> Args,
14978  SourceLocation LitEndLoc,
14979  TemplateArgumentListInfo *TemplateArgs) {
14980  SourceLocation UDSuffixLoc = SuffixInfo.getCXXLiteralOperatorNameLoc();
14981 
14982  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(UDSuffixLoc,
14983  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
14984  AddNonMemberOperatorCandidates(R.asUnresolvedSet(), Args, CandidateSet,
14985  TemplateArgs);
14986 
14987  bool HadMultipleCandidates = (CandidateSet.size() > 1);
14988 
14989  // Perform overload resolution. This will usually be trivial, but might need
14990  // to perform substitutions for a literal operator template.
14991  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
14992  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(*this, UDSuffixLoc, Best)) {
14993  case OR_Success:
14994  case OR_Deleted:
14995  break;
14996 
14997  case OR_No_Viable_Function:
14998  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
14999  PartialDiagnosticAt(UDSuffixLoc,
15000  PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_viable_function_in_call)
15001  << R.getLookupName()),
15002  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
15003  return ExprError();
15004 
15005  case OR_Ambiguous:
15006  CandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
15007  PartialDiagnosticAt(R.getNameLoc(), PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_call)
15008  << R.getLookupName()),
15009  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args);
15010  return ExprError();
15011  }
15012 
15013  FunctionDecl *FD = Best->Function;
15014  ExprResult Fn = CreateFunctionRefExpr(*this, FD, Best->FoundDecl,
15015  nullptr, HadMultipleCandidates,
15016  SuffixInfo.getLoc(),
15017  SuffixInfo.getInfo());
15018  if (Fn.isInvalid())
15019  return true;
15020 
15021  // Check the argument types. This should almost always be a no-op, except
15022  // that array-to-pointer decay is applied to string literals.
15023  Expr *ConvArgs[2];
15024  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0, N = Args.size(); ArgIdx != N; ++ArgIdx) {
15025  ExprResult InputInit = PerformCopyInitialization(
15026  InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context, FD->getParamDecl(ArgIdx)),
15027  SourceLocation(), Args[ArgIdx]);
15028  if (InputInit.isInvalid())
15029  return true;
15030  ConvArgs[ArgIdx] = InputInit.get();
15031  }
15032 
15033  QualType ResultTy = FD->getReturnType();
15034  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultTy);
15035  ResultTy = ResultTy.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
15036 
15037  UserDefinedLiteral *UDL = UserDefinedLiteral::Create(
15038  Context, Fn.get(), llvm::makeArrayRef(ConvArgs, Args.size()), ResultTy,
15039  VK, LitEndLoc, UDSuffixLoc, CurFPFeatureOverrides());
15040 
15041  if (CheckCallReturnType(FD->getReturnType(), UDSuffixLoc, UDL, FD))
15042  return ExprError();
15043 
15044  if (CheckFunctionCall(FD, UDL, nullptr))
15045  return ExprError();
15046 
15047  return CheckForImmediateInvocation(MaybeBindToTemporary(UDL), FD);
15048 }
15049 
15050 /// Build a call to 'begin' or 'end' for a C++11 for-range statement. If the
15051 /// given LookupResult is non-empty, it is assumed to describe a member which
15052 /// will be invoked. Otherwise, the function will be found via argument
15053 /// dependent lookup.
15054 /// CallExpr is set to a valid expression and FRS_Success returned on success,
15055 /// otherwise CallExpr is set to ExprError() and some non-success value
15056 /// is returned.
15057 Sema::ForRangeStatus
15058 Sema::BuildForRangeBeginEndCall(SourceLocation Loc,
15059  SourceLocation RangeLoc,
15060  const DeclarationNameInfo &NameInfo,
15061  LookupResult &MemberLookup,
15062  OverloadCandidateSet *CandidateSet,
15063  Expr *Range, ExprResult *CallExpr) {
15064  Scope *S = nullptr;
15065 
15066  CandidateSet->clear(OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
15067  if (!MemberLookup.empty()) {
15068  ExprResult MemberRef =
15069  BuildMemberReferenceExpr(Range, Range->getType(), Loc,
15070  /*IsPtr=*/false, CXXScopeSpec(),
15071  /*TemplateKWLoc=*/SourceLocation(),
15072  /*FirstQualifierInScope=*/nullptr,
15073  MemberLookup,
15074  /*TemplateArgs=*/nullptr, S);
15075  if (MemberRef.isInvalid()) {
15076  *CallExpr = ExprError();
15077  return FRS_DiagnosticIssued;
15078  }
15079  *CallExpr = BuildCallExpr(S, MemberRef.get(), Loc, None, Loc, nullptr);
15080  if (CallExpr->isInvalid()) {
15081  *CallExpr = ExprError();
15082  return FRS_DiagnosticIssued;
15083  }
15084  } else {
15085  ExprResult FnR = CreateUnresolvedLookupExpr(/*NamingClass=*/nullptr,
15086  NestedNameSpecifierLoc(),
15087  NameInfo, UnresolvedSet<0>());
15088  if (FnR.isInvalid())
15089  return FRS_DiagnosticIssued;
15090  UnresolvedLookupExpr *Fn = cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(FnR.get());
15091 
15092  bool CandidateSetError = buildOverloadedCallSet(S, Fn, Fn, Range, Loc,
15093  CandidateSet, CallExpr);
15094  if (CandidateSet->empty() || CandidateSetError) {
15095  *CallExpr = ExprError();
15096  return FRS_NoViableFunction;
15097  }
15098  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
15099  OverloadingResult OverloadResult =
15100  CandidateSet->BestViableFunction(*this, Fn->getBeginLoc(), Best);
15101 
15102  if (OverloadResult == OR_No_Viable_Function) {
15103  *CallExpr = ExprError();
15104  return FRS_NoViableFunction;
15105  }
15106  *CallExpr = FinishOverloadedCallExpr(*this, S, Fn, Fn, Loc, Range,
15107  Loc, nullptr, CandidateSet, &Best,
15108  OverloadResult,
15109  /*AllowTypoCorrection=*/false);
15110  if (CallExpr->isInvalid() || OverloadResult != OR_Success) {
15111  *CallExpr = ExprError();
15112  return FRS_DiagnosticIssued;
15113  }
15114  }
15115  return FRS_Success;
15116 }
15117 
15118 
15119 /// FixOverloadedFunctionReference - E is an expression that refers to
15120 /// a C++ overloaded function (possibly with some parentheses and
15121 /// perhaps a '&' around it). We have resolved the overloaded function
15122 /// to the function declaration Fn, so patch up the expression E to
15123 /// refer (possibly indirectly) to Fn. Returns the new expr.
15124 Expr *Sema::FixOverloadedFunctionReference(Expr *E, DeclAccessPair Found,
15125  FunctionDecl *Fn) {
15126  if (ParenExpr *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
15127  Expr *SubExpr = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(PE->getSubExpr(),
15128  Found, Fn);
15129  if (SubExpr == PE->getSubExpr())
15130  return PE;
15131 
15132  return new (Context) ParenExpr(PE->getLParen(), PE->getRParen(), SubExpr);
15133  }
15134 
15135  if (ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
15136  Expr *SubExpr = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(ICE->getSubExpr(),
15137  Found, Fn);
15138  assert(Context.hasSameType(ICE->getSubExpr()->getType(),
15139  SubExpr->getType()) &&
15140  "Implicit cast type cannot be determined from overload");
15141  assert(ICE->path_empty() && "fixing up hierarchy conversion?");
15142  if (SubExpr == ICE->getSubExpr())
15143  return ICE;
15144 
15145  return ImplicitCastExpr::Create(Context, ICE->getType(), ICE->getCastKind(),
15146  SubExpr, nullptr, ICE->getValueKind(),
15147  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
15148  }
15149 
15150  if (auto *GSE = dyn_cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)) {
15151  if (!GSE->isResultDependent()) {
15152  Expr *SubExpr =
15153  FixOverloadedFunctionReference(GSE->getResultExpr(), Found, Fn);
15154  if (SubExpr == GSE->getResultExpr())
15155  return GSE;
15156 
15157  // Replace the resulting type information before rebuilding the generic
15158  // selection expression.
15159  ArrayRef<Expr *> A = GSE->getAssocExprs();
15160  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> AssocExprs(A.begin(), A.end());
15161  unsigned ResultIdx = GSE->getResultIndex();
15162  AssocExprs[ResultIdx] = SubExpr;
15163 
15164  return GenericSelectionExpr::Create(
15165  Context, GSE->getGenericLoc(), GSE->getControllingExpr(),
15166  GSE->getAssocTypeSourceInfos(), AssocExprs, GSE->getDefaultLoc(),
15167  GSE->getRParenLoc(), GSE->containsUnexpandedParameterPack(),
15168  ResultIdx);
15169  }
15170  // Rather than fall through to the unreachable, return the original generic
15171  // selection expression.
15172  return GSE;
15173  }
15174 
15175  if (UnaryOperator *UnOp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
15176  assert(UnOp->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf &&
15177  "Can only take the address of an overloaded function");
15178  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn)) {
15179  if (Method->isStatic()) {
15180  // Do nothing: static member functions aren't any different
15181  // from non-member functions.
15182  } else {
15183  // Fix the subexpression, which really has to be an
15184  // UnresolvedLookupExpr holding an overloaded member function
15185  // or template.
15186  Expr *SubExpr = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(UnOp->getSubExpr(),
15187  Found, Fn);
15188  if (SubExpr == UnOp->getSubExpr())
15189  return UnOp;
15190 
15191  assert(isa<DeclRefExpr>(SubExpr)
15192  && "fixed to something other than a decl ref");
15193  assert(cast<DeclRefExpr>(SubExpr)->getQualifier()
15194  && "fixed to a member ref with no nested name qualifier");
15195 
15196  // We have taken the address of a pointer to member
15197  // function. Perform the computation here so that we get the
15198  // appropriate pointer to member type.
15199  QualType ClassType
15200  = Context.getTypeDeclType(cast<RecordDecl>(Method->getDeclContext()));
15201  QualType MemPtrType
15202  = Context.getMemberPointerType(Fn->getType(), ClassType.getTypePtr());
15203  // Under the MS ABI, lock down the inheritance model now.
15204  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft())
15205  (void)isCompleteType(UnOp->getOperatorLoc(), MemPtrType);
15206 
15207  return UnaryOperator::Create(
15208  Context, SubExpr, UO_AddrOf, MemPtrType, VK_PRValue, OK_Ordinary,
15209  UnOp->getOperatorLoc(), false, CurFPFeatureOverrides());
15210  }
15211  }
15212  Expr *SubExpr = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(UnOp->getSubExpr(),
15213  Found, Fn);
15214  if (SubExpr == UnOp->getSubExpr())
15215  return UnOp;
15216 
15217  return UnaryOperator::Create(
15218  Context, SubExpr, UO_AddrOf, Context.getPointerType(SubExpr->getType()),
15219  VK_PRValue, OK_Ordinary, UnOp->getOperatorLoc(), false,
15220  CurFPFeatureOverrides());
15221  }
15222 
15223  if (UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE = dyn_cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E)) {
15224  // FIXME: avoid copy.
15225  TemplateArgumentListInfo TemplateArgsBuffer, *TemplateArgs = nullptr;
15226  if (ULE->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
15227  ULE->copyTemplateArgumentsInto(TemplateArgsBuffer);
15228  TemplateArgs = &TemplateArgsBuffer;
15229  }
15230 
15231  DeclRefExpr *DRE =
15232  BuildDeclRefExpr(Fn, Fn->getType(), VK_LValue, ULE->getNameInfo(),
15233  ULE->getQualifierLoc(), Found.getDecl(),
15234  ULE->getTemplateKeywordLoc(), TemplateArgs);
15235  DRE->setHadMultipleCandidates(ULE->getNumDecls() > 1);
15236  return DRE;
15237  }
15238 
15239  if (UnresolvedMemberExpr *MemExpr = dyn_cast<UnresolvedMemberExpr>(E)) {
15240  // FIXME: avoid copy.
15241  TemplateArgumentListInfo TemplateArgsBuffer, *TemplateArgs = nullptr;
15242  if (MemExpr->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
15243  MemExpr->copyTemplateArgumentsInto(TemplateArgsBuffer);
15244  TemplateArgs = &TemplateArgsBuffer;
15245  }
15246 
15247  Expr *Base;
15248 
15249  // If we're filling in a static method where we used to have an
15250  // implicit member access, rewrite to a simple decl ref.
15251  if (MemExpr->isImplicitAccess()) {
15252  if (cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn)->isStatic()) {
15253  DeclRefExpr *DRE = BuildDeclRefExpr(
15254  Fn, Fn->getType(), VK_LValue, MemExpr->getNameInfo(),
15255  MemExpr->getQualifierLoc(), Found.getDecl(),
15256  MemExpr->getTemplateKeywordLoc(), TemplateArgs);
15257  DRE->setHadMultipleCandidates(MemExpr->getNumDecls() > 1);
15258  return DRE;
15259  } else {
15260  SourceLocation Loc = MemExpr->getMemberLoc();
15261  if (MemExpr->getQualifier())
15262  Loc = MemExpr->getQualifierLoc().getBeginLoc();
15263  Base =
15264  BuildCXXThisExpr(Loc, MemExpr->getBaseType(), /*IsImplicit=*/true);
15265  }
15266  } else
15267  Base = MemExpr->getBase();
15268 
15269  ExprValueKind valueKind;
15270  QualType type;
15271  if (cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn)->isStatic()) {
15272  valueKind = VK_LValue;
15273  type = Fn->getType();
15274  } else {
15275  valueKind = VK_PRValue;
15276  type = Context.BoundMemberTy;
15277  }
15278 
15279  return BuildMemberExpr(
15280  Base, MemExpr->isArrow(), MemExpr->getOperatorLoc(),
15281  MemExpr->getQualifierLoc(), MemExpr->getTemplateKeywordLoc(), Fn, Found,
15282  /*HadMultipleCandidates=*/true, MemExpr->getMemberNameInfo(),
15283  type, valueKind, OK_Ordinary, TemplateArgs);
15284  }
15285 
15286  llvm_unreachable("Invalid reference to overloaded function");
15287 }
15288 
15289 ExprResult Sema::FixOverloadedFunctionReference(ExprResult E,
15290  DeclAccessPair Found,
15291  FunctionDecl *Fn) {
15292  return FixOverloadedFunctionReference(E.get(), Found, Fn);
15293 }
15294 
15295 bool clang::shouldEnforceArgLimit(bool PartialOverloading,
15296  FunctionDecl *Function) {
15297  if (!PartialOverloading || !Function)
15298  return true;
15299  if (Function->isVariadic())
15300  return false;
15301  if (const auto *Proto =
15302  dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(Function->getFunctionType()))
15303  if (Proto->isTemplateVariadic())
15304  return false;
15305  if (auto *Pattern = Function->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
15306  if (const auto *Proto =
15307  dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(Pattern->getFunctionType()))
15308  if (Proto->isTemplateVariadic())
15309  return false;
15310  return true;
15311 }
